text_query: Show the distinct director of films with market estimation in the year of 1995.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Director FROM film AS T1 JOIN film_market_estimation AS T2 ON T1.Film_ID  =  T2.Film_ID WHERE T2.Year  =  1995

text_query: How many different locations does each school have?

text_query: Show all artist names who didn't have an exhibition in 2004.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM artist EXCEPT SELECT T2.name FROM exhibition AS T1 JOIN artist AS T2 ON T1.artist_id  =  T2.artist_id WHERE T1.year  =  2004

text_query: Find the grade studying in room 105.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT grade FROM list WHERE classroom  =  105

text_query: Which city has most number of arriving flights?
sql_command: SELECT T1.City FROM AIRPORTS AS T1 JOIN FLIGHTS AS T2 ON T1.AirportCode  =  T2.DestAirport GROUP BY T1.City ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Which game type has least number of games?
sql_command: SELECT gtype FROM Video_games GROUP BY gtype ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name of companies whose revenue is between 100 and 150.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM manufacturers WHERE revenue BETWEEN 100 AND 150

text_query: display the emails of the employees who have no commission percentage and salary within the range 7000 to 12000 and works in that department which number is 50.
sql_command: SELECT email FROM employees WHERE commission_pct  =  "null" AND salary BETWEEN 7000 AND 12000 AND department_id = 50

text_query: Report all advisors that advise more than 2 students.
sql_command: SELECT Advisor FROM STUDENT GROUP BY Advisor HAVING COUNT(*)  >  2

text_query: Find the names of all English songs.
sql_command: SELECT song_name FROM song WHERE languages  =  "english"

text_query: List the teams of the players with the top 5 largest ages.
sql_command: SELECT Team FROM player ORDER BY Age DESC LIMIT 5

text_query: What are all the possible breed type and size type combinations?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT breed_code ,  size_code FROM dogs

text_query: What are the code and description of the least frequent detention type ?
sql_command: SELECT T1.detention_type_code ,  T2.detention_type_description FROM Detention AS T1 JOIN Ref_Detention_Type AS T2 ON T1.detention_type_code  =  T2.detention_type_code GROUP BY T1.detention_type_code ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the primary conference of the school that has the lowest acc percent score in the competition?
sql_command: SELECT t1.Primary_conference FROM university AS t1 JOIN basketball_match AS t2 ON t1.school_id  =  t2.school_id ORDER BY t2.acc_percent LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name of the user who tweeted more than once, and number of tweets tweeted by them.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  count(*) FROM user_profiles AS T1 JOIN tweets AS T2 ON T1.uid  =  T2.uid GROUP BY T2.uid HAVING count(*)  >  1

text_query: how many programs are broadcast in each time section of the day?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  time_of_day FROM broadcast GROUP BY time_of_day

text_query: Which college has any student who is a goalie and succeeded in the tryout.
sql_command: SELECT cName FROM  tryout WHERE decision  =  'yes' AND pPos  =  'goalie'

text_query: What are the numbers of constructors for different nationalities?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  nationality FROM constructors GROUP BY nationality

text_query: Show the total number of rooms of the apartments in the building with short name "Columbus Square".
sql_command: SELECT sum(T2.room_count) FROM Apartment_Buildings AS T1 JOIN Apartments AS T2 ON T1.building_id  =  T2.building_id WHERE T1.building_short_name  =  "Columbus Square"

text_query: What are all the makers and models?
sql_command: SELECT Maker ,  Model FROM MODEL_LIST;

text_query: How is the math course described?
sql_command: SELECT course_description FROM Courses WHERE course_name  =  'math'

text_query: Which countries have more than two members?
sql_command: SELECT Country FROM member GROUP BY Country HAVING COUNT(*)  >  2

text_query: Find the total hours of the projects that scientists named Michael Rogers or Carol Smith are assigned to.
sql_command: SELECT sum(T2.hours) FROM assignedto AS T1 JOIN projects AS T2 ON T1.project  =  T2.code JOIN scientists AS T3 ON T1.scientist  =  T3.SSN WHERE T3.name  =  'Michael Rogers' OR T3.name  =  'Carol Smith'

text_query: What is Weekly Rank of TV series with Episode "A Love of a Lifetime"?
sql_command: SELECT Weekly_Rank FROM TV_series WHERE Episode = "A Love of a Lifetime";

text_query: List the names of gymnasts in ascending order by their heights.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name FROM gymnast AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.Gymnast_ID  =  T2.People_ID ORDER BY T2.Height ASC

text_query: How many campuses are there in Los Angeles county?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM campuses WHERE county  =  "Los Angeles"

text_query: Find the total hours of all projects.
sql_command: SELECT sum(hours) FROM projects

text_query: Show names and seatings, ordered by seating for all tracks opened after 2000.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  seating FROM track WHERE year_opened  >  2000 ORDER BY seating

text_query: Return all reviewer names and movie names together in a single list.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM Reviewer UNION SELECT title FROM Movie

text_query: What are the names of reviewers who had rated 3 star and 4 star?
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Reviewer AS T2 ON T1.rID  =  T2.rID WHERE T1.stars  =  3 INTERSECT SELECT T2.name FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Reviewer AS T2 ON T1.rID  =  T2.rID WHERE T1.stars  =  4

text_query: Find the name of department has the highest amount of students?
sql_command: SELECT dept_name FROM student GROUP BY dept_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Sort employee names by their age in ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM employee ORDER BY age

text_query: List each test result and its count in descending order of count.
sql_command: SELECT test_result ,  COUNT(*) FROM Student_Tests_Taken GROUP BY test_result ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC

text_query: List the name, nationality and id of all male architects ordered by their names lexicographically.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  nationality ,  id FROM architect WHERE gender  =  'male' ORDER BY name

text_query: Please show the different statuses of cities and the average population of cities with each status.
sql_command: SELECT Status ,  avg(Population) FROM city GROUP BY Status

text_query: Show the draft pick numbers and draft classes of players whose positions are defenders.
sql_command: SELECT Draft_Pick_Number ,  Draft_Class FROM match_season WHERE POSITION  =  "Defender"

text_query: Find the name and attribute ID of the attribute definitions with attribute value 0.
sql_command: SELECT t1.attribute_name ,  t1.attribute_id FROM Attribute_Definitions AS t1 JOIN Catalog_Contents_Additional_Attributes AS t2 ON t1.attribute_id  =  t2.attribute_id WHERE t2.attribute_value  =  0

text_query: Find the number of different airports which are the destinations of the American Airlines.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT dst_apid) FROM airlines AS T1 JOIN routes AS T2 ON T1.alid  =  T2.alid WHERE T1.name  =  'American Airlines'

text_query: Show the names of high school students and their corresponding number of friends.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name ,  count(*) FROM Friend AS T1 JOIN Highschooler AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.id GROUP BY T1.student_id

text_query: Find the semester when both Master students and Bachelor students got enrolled in.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T2.semester_id FROM Degree_Programs AS T1 JOIN Student_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.degree_program_id  =  T2.degree_program_id WHERE degree_summary_name  =  'Master' INTERSECT SELECT DISTINCT T2.semester_id FROM Degree_Programs AS T1 JOIN Student_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.degree_program_id  =  T2.degree_program_id WHERE degree_summary_name  =  'Bachelor'

text_query: Show names of climbers and the names of mountains they climb.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name ,  T2.Name FROM climber AS T1 JOIN mountain AS T2 ON T1.Mountain_ID  =  T2.Mountain_ID

text_query: Find the total checking and saving balance of all accounts sorted by the total balance in ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT T1.balance + T2.balance FROM checking AS T1 JOIN savings AS T2 ON T1.custid  =  T2.custid ORDER BY T1.balance + T2.balance

text_query: How many templates have template type code CV?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Templates WHERE template_type_code  =  "CV"

text_query: Find the name and city of the airport which is the destination of the most number of routes.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  T1.city ,  T2.dst_apid FROM airports AS T1 JOIN routes AS T2 ON T1.apid  =  T2.dst_apid GROUP BY T2.dst_apid ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is department name and office for the professor whose last name is Heffington?
sql_command: SELECT T3.dept_name  ,  T2.prof_office FROM employee AS T1 JOIN professor AS T2 ON T1.emp_num  =  T2.emp_num JOIN department AS T3 ON T2.dept_code  =  T3.dept_code WHERE T1.emp_lname  =  'Heffington'

text_query: What are the names of representatives and the dates of elections they participated in.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name ,  T1.Date FROM election AS T1 JOIN representative AS T2 ON T1.Representative_ID  =  T2.Representative_ID

text_query: How many buildings are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM building

text_query: List the name and country of origin for all singers who have produced songs with rating above 9.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.artist_name ,  T1.country FROM artist AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.artist_name  =  T2.artist_name WHERE T2.rating  >  9

text_query: Show all video games with type Collectible card game.
sql_command: SELECT gname FROM Video_games WHERE gtype  =  "Collectible card game"

text_query: Find the number of distinct projects.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT name) FROM projects

text_query: For all the faults of different parts, what are all the decriptions of the skills required to fix them? List the name of the faults and the skill description.
sql_command: SELECT T1.fault_short_name ,  T3.skill_description FROM Part_Faults AS T1 JOIN Skills_Required_To_Fix AS T2 ON T1.part_fault_id  =  T2.part_fault_id JOIN Skills AS T3 ON T2.skill_id  =  T3.skill_id

text_query: Find the id of the customers who have order status both "On Road" and "Shipped".
sql_command: SELECT T1.customer_id FROM customers AS T1 JOIN orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id WHERE T2.order_status = "On Road" INTERSECT SELECT T1.customer_id FROM customers AS T1 JOIN orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id WHERE T2.order_status = "Shipped"

text_query: Find the names of all the tracks that contain the word "you".
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM TRACK WHERE Name LIKE '%you%'

text_query: List the amount and donor name for the largest amount of donation.
sql_command: SELECT amount ,  donator_name FROM endowment ORDER BY amount DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: In which year were most of ships built?
sql_command: SELECT built_year FROM ship GROUP BY built_year ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are flight numbers of flights departing from City "Aberdeen "?
sql_command: SELECT T1.FlightNo FROM FLIGHTS AS T1 JOIN AIRPORTS AS T2 ON T1.SourceAirport   =  T2.AirportCode WHERE T2.City  =  "Aberdeen"

text_query: Please list all songs in volumes in ascending alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT Song FROM volume ORDER BY Song

text_query: Show me all the restaurants.
sql_command: SELECT ResName FROM Restaurant;

text_query: What are the distinct grant amount for the grants where the documents were sent before '1986-08-26 20:49:27' and grant were ended after '1989-03-16 18:27:16'?
sql_command: SELECT T1.grant_amount FROM Grants AS T1 JOIN Documents AS T2 ON T1.grant_id  =  T2.grant_id WHERE T2.sent_date  <  '1986-08-26 20:49:27' INTERSECT SELECT grant_amount FROM grants WHERE grant_end_date  >  '1989-03-16 18:27:16'

text_query: Show the zip code of the county with name "Howard".
sql_command: SELECT Zip_code FROM county WHERE County_name  =  "Howard"

text_query: List all students' first names and last names who majored in 600.
sql_command: SELECT Fname , Lname FROM Student WHERE Major  =  600;

text_query: Please show the date of ceremony of the volumes that last more than 2 weeks on top.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Date_of_ceremony FROM music_festival AS T1 JOIN volume AS T2 ON T1.Volume  =  T2.Volume_ID WHERE T2.Weeks_on_Top  >  2

text_query: What are the login names of the students with family name "Ward"?
sql_command: SELECT login_name FROM Students WHERE family_name  =  "Ward"

text_query: the names of models that launched between 2002 and 2004.
sql_command: SELECT Model_name FROM chip_model WHERE Launch_year BETWEEN 2002 AND 2004;

text_query: Find the id of the item whose title is "orange".
sql_command: SELECT i_id FROM item WHERE title  =  "orange"

text_query: Find the number of orchestras whose record format is "CD" or "DVD".

sql_command: SELECT YEAR FROM degrees GROUP BY YEAR ORDER BY sum(degrees) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the population and life expectancies in Brazil?
sql_command: SELECT Population ,  LifeExpectancy FROM country WHERE Name  =  "Brazil"

text_query: How many tracks do we have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM track

text_query: Which document type is described with the prefix 'Initial'?
sql_command: SELECT document_type_code FROM Document_Types WHERE document_description LIKE 'Initial%'

text_query: What is the partition id of the user named "Iron Man".
sql_command: SELECT partitionid FROM user_profiles WHERE name  =  'Iron Man'

text_query: Find the number of products for each manufacturer, showing the name of each company.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  T2.name FROM products AS T1 JOIN manufacturers AS T2 ON T1.Manufacturer  =  T2.code GROUP BY T2.name

text_query: Return all distinct detention type codes.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT detention_type_code FROM Detention

text_query: List all region names in alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT region_name FROM region ORDER BY region_name

text_query: What is the reviewer id of Daniel Lewis?
sql_command: SELECT rID FROM Reviewer WHERE name  =  "Daniel Lewis"

text_query: Find the id of the candidate who got the lowest oppose rate.
sql_command: SELECT Candidate_ID FROM candidate ORDER BY oppose_rate LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the total credit does each department offer?

sql_command: SELECT T3.venue FROM city AS T1 JOIN hosting_city AS T2 ON T1.city_id = T2.host_city JOIN MATCH AS T3 ON T2.match_id = T3.match_id WHERE T1.city = "Nanjing ( Jiangsu )" AND T3.competition = "1994 FIFA World Cup qualification"

text_query: When did customer with first name as Carole and last name as Bernhard became a customer?

text_query: List the most common result of the musicals.

text_query: Which city has the lowest GDP? Please list the city name and its GDP.
sql_command: SELECT city ,  GDP FROM city ORDER BY GDP LIMIT 1

text_query: How many products are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Products

text_query: How many films have the word 'Dummy' in their titles?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM film WHERE title LIKE "%Dummy%"

text_query: Show all the planned delivery dates and actual delivery dates of bookings.
sql_command: SELECT Planned_Delivery_Date ,  Actual_Delivery_Date FROM BOOKINGS

text_query: How many instruments does the song "Le Pop" use?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT instrument) FROM instruments AS T1 JOIN songs AS T2 ON T1.songid  =  T2.songid WHERE title  =  "Le Pop"

text_query: What are the names of the tourist attractions and the dates when the tourists named Vincent or Vivian visited there?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name ,  T3.Visit_Date FROM Tourist_Attractions AS T1 JOIN VISITORS AS T2 JOIN VISITS AS T3 ON T1.Tourist_Attraction_ID  =  T3.Tourist_Attraction_ID AND T2.Tourist_ID  =  T3.Tourist_ID WHERE T2.Tourist_Details  =  "Vincent" OR T2.Tourist_Details  =  "Vivian"

sql_command: SELECT year_opened FROM track WHERE seating BETWEEN 4000 AND 5000

text_query: How many members are not living in Hartford?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM member WHERE address != 'Hartford'

text_query: Find the average age of losers and winners of all matches.
sql_command: SELECT avg(loser_age) ,  avg(winner_age) FROM matches

text_query: What are the names of the nations with the 3 lowest populations?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM country ORDER BY Population ASC LIMIT 3

text_query: Show all student IDs with the number of sports and total number of games played
sql_command: SELECT StuID ,  count(*) ,  sum(gamesplayed) FROM Sportsinfo GROUP BY StuID

text_query: What are the distinct billing countries of the invoices?
sql_command: SELECT distinct(BillingCountry) FROM INVOICE

text_query: How many allergies are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT allergy) FROM Allergy_type

sql_command: SELECT name FROM member WHERE member_id NOT IN (SELECT member_id FROM membership_register_branch)

text_query: What is the maximum, minimum and average market share of the listed browsers?
sql_command: SELECT max(market_share) ,  min(market_share) ,  avg(market_share) FROM browser

text_query: What are the first names and last names of the students that minor in the department with DNO 140.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Fname ,  T2.Lname FROM MINOR_IN AS T1 JOIN STUDENT AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  T2.StuID WHERE T1.DNO  =  140

text_query: Find the patient who has the most recent undergoing treatment?
sql_command: SELECT patient FROM undergoes ORDER BY dateundergoes LIMIT 1

text_query: Find all the ids and dates of the logs for the problem whose id is 10.
sql_command: SELECT problem_log_id ,  log_entry_date FROM problem_log WHERE problem_id = 10

text_query: Find the names of the clubs that have at least a member from the city with city code "HOU".
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT t1.clubname FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid JOIN student AS t3 ON t2.stuid  =  t3.stuid WHERE t3.city_code  =  "HOU"

text_query: Please show the most common occupation of players.
sql_command: SELECT Occupation FROM player GROUP BY Occupation ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the names of courses taught by the tutor who has personal name "Julio".
sql_command: SELECT T2.course_name FROM Course_Authors_and_Tutors AS T1 JOIN Courses AS T2 ON T1.author_id  =  T2.author_id WHERE T1.personal_name  =  "Julio"

text_query: How many unique labels are there for albums?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT label) FROM albums

text_query: In which year were most departments established?
sql_command: SELECT creation FROM department GROUP BY creation ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the average grade point of student whose last name is Smith.
sql_command: SELECT avg(T2.gradepoint) FROM ENROLLED_IN AS T1 JOIN GRADECONVERSION AS T2 JOIN STUDENT AS T3 ON T1.Grade  =  T2.lettergrade AND T1.StuID  =  T3.StuID WHERE T3.LName  =  "Smith"

text_query: List official names of cities in descending order of population.
sql_command: SELECT Official_Name FROM city ORDER BY Population DESC

text_query: For each classroom report the grade that is taught in it. Report just the classroom number and the grade number.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT classroom ,  grade FROM list

text_query: List the names of all left-footed players who have overall rating between 85 and 90.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.player_name FROM Player AS T1 JOIN Player_Attributes AS T2 ON T1.player_api_id = T2.player_api_id WHERE T2.preferred_foot  =  "left" AND T2.overall_rating  >=  85 AND T2.overall_rating  <=  90

text_query: What are the ids and names of the architects who built at least 3 bridges ?
sql_command: SELECT T1.id ,  T1.name FROM architect AS T1 JOIN bridge AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.architect_id GROUP BY T1.id HAVING count(*)  >=  3

text_query: What is the id, name and nationality of the architect who built most mills?
sql_command: SELECT T1.id ,  T1.name ,  T1.nationality FROM architect AS T1 JOIN mill AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.architect_id GROUP BY T1.id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show all artist name, age, and country ordered by the yeared they joined.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  age ,  country FROM artist ORDER BY Year_Join

text_query: What is the average access count of documents?
sql_command: SELECT avg(access_count) FROM documents

text_query: What are the lengths and heights of roller coasters?
sql_command: SELECT LENGTH ,  Height FROM roller_coaster

text_query: How many counties are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM county_public_safety

text_query: Show the names of phones that are on market with number of shops greater than 50.
sql_command: SELECT T3.Name FROM phone_market AS T1 JOIN market AS T2 ON T1.Market_ID  =  T2.Market_ID JOIN phone AS T3 ON T1.Phone_ID  =  T3.Phone_ID WHERE T2.Num_of_shops  >  50

sql_command: SELECT T1.duration ,  T1.file_size ,  T1.formats FROM files AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.f_id  =  T2.f_id WHERE T2.genre_is  =  "pop" ORDER BY T2.song_name

text_query: Show the status shared by cities with population bigger than 1500 and smaller than 500.

text_query: What is the description of role code ED?
sql_command: SELECT role_description FROM ROLES WHERE role_code = "ED";

text_query: What are the dates of the latest logon of the students with family name "Jaskolski" or "Langosh"?

text_query: Show the delegates and the names of the party they belong to.

text_query: Show all template type codes and number of templates for each.

text_query: What are the id of problems reported by the staff named Dameon Frami or Jolie Weber?
sql_command: SELECT product_id FROM problems AS T1 JOIN staff AS T2 ON T1.reported_by_staff_id = T2.staff_id WHERE T2.staff_first_name = "Dameon" AND T2.staff_last_name = "Frami" UNION SELECT product_id FROM problems AS T1 JOIN staff AS T2 ON T1.reported_by_staff_id = T2.staff_id WHERE T2.staff_first_name = "Jolie" AND T2.staff_last_name = "Weber"

text_query: Show the name and location for all tracks.

text_query: List the most common type of artworks.

text_query: What is the total number of countries where Spanish is spoken by the largest percentage of people?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,   max(Percentage) FROM countrylanguage WHERE LANGUAGE  =  "Spanish" GROUP BY CountryCode

text_query: what is the name and position of the head whose department has least number of employees?
sql_command: SELECT T2.name ,  T2.position FROM department AS T1 JOIN physician AS T2 ON T1.head  =  T2.EmployeeID GROUP BY departmentID ORDER BY count(departmentID) LIMIT 1;

text_query: List countries that have more than one swimmer.
sql_command: SELECT nationality ,  count(*) FROM swimmer GROUP BY nationality HAVING count(*)  >  1

text_query: Show all allergy type with number of students affected.
sql_command: SELECT T2.allergytype ,  count(*) FROM Has_allergy AS T1 JOIN Allergy_type AS T2 ON T1.allergy  =  T2.allergy GROUP BY T2.allergytype

text_query: list in alphabetic order all course names and their instructors' names in year 2008.
sql_command: SELECT T1.title ,  T3.name FROM course AS T1 JOIN teaches AS T2 ON T1.course_id  =  T2.course_id JOIN instructor AS T3 ON T2.id  =  T3.id WHERE YEAR  =  2008 ORDER BY T1.title

text_query: List the grape, winery and year of the wines whose price is bigger than 100 ordered by year.
sql_command: SELECT Grape ,  Winery ,  YEAR FROM WINE WHERE Price  >   100 ORDER BY YEAR

text_query: Find the total number of students and total number of instructors for each department.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT T2.id) ,  count(DISTINCT T3.id) ,  T3.dept_name FROM department AS T1 JOIN student AS T2 ON T1.dept_name  =  T2.dept_name JOIN instructor AS T3 ON T1.dept_name  =  T3.dept_name GROUP BY T3.dept_name

text_query: Which engineer has visited the most times? Show the engineer id, first name and last name.
sql_command: SELECT T1.engineer_id ,  T1.first_name ,  T1.last_name FROM Maintenance_Engineers AS T1 JOIN Engineer_Visits AS T2 GROUP BY T1.engineer_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the speeds of the longest roller coaster?
sql_command: SELECT Speed FROM roller_coaster ORDER BY LENGTH DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the team names of the universities whose enrollments are smaller than the average enrollment size.
sql_command: SELECT t2.team_name FROM university AS t1 JOIN basketball_match AS t2 ON t1.school_id  =  t2.school_id WHERE enrollment  <  (SELECT avg(enrollment) FROM university)

text_query: What are the names of the cameras that have taken picture of the most mountains?
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM photos AS T1 JOIN camera_lens AS T2 ON T1.camera_lens_id  =  T2.id GROUP BY T2.id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the number of routes from the United States to Canada.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM routes WHERE dst_apid IN (SELECT apid FROM airports WHERE country  =  'Canada') AND src_apid IN (SELECT apid FROM airports WHERE country  =  'United States')

text_query: What is the total amount of payment?
sql_command: SELECT sum(Amount_Payment) FROM Payments

text_query: which countries' tv channels are playing some cartoon written by Todd Casey?
sql_command: SELECT T1.country FROM TV_Channel AS T1 JOIN cartoon AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.Channel WHERE T2.written_by  =  'Todd Casey'

text_query: Which state has the most customers?
sql_command: SELECT state FROM customers GROUP BY state ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

text_query: List the council tax ids and their related cmi cross references of all the parking fines.
sql_command: SELECT council_tax_id ,  cmi_cross_ref_id FROM parking_fines

text_query: What is the document type description for document type named Film?
sql_command: SELECT document_type_description FROM Ref_document_types WHERE document_type_name  =  "Film"

text_query: Find the name and position of physicians who prescribe some medication whose brand is X?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.name ,  T1.position FROM physician AS T1 JOIN prescribes AS T2 ON T1.employeeid = T2.physician JOIN medication AS T3 ON T3.code = T2.medication WHERE T3.Brand  =  "X"

text_query: What is the first name and job id for all employees in the Finance department?
sql_command: SELECT T1.first_name ,  T1.job_id FROM employees AS T1 JOIN departments AS T2 ON T1.department_id  =  T2.department_id WHERE T2.department_name  =  'Finance'

text_query: What are the percentage of hispanics in cities with the black percentage higher than 10?
sql_command: SELECT Hispanic FROM city WHERE Black  >  10

text_query: What is the aircraft name for the flight with number 99
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM Flight AS T1 JOIN Aircraft AS T2 ON T1.aid  =  T2.aid WHERE T1.flno  =  99

text_query: Show all region code and region name sorted by the codes.
sql_command: SELECT region_code ,  region_name FROM region ORDER BY region_code

text_query: List the first and last name of the students who do not have any food type allergy.
sql_command: SELECT fname ,  lname FROM Student WHERE StuID NOT IN (SELECT T1.StuID FROM Has_allergy AS T1 JOIN Allergy_Type AS T2 ON T1.Allergy  =  T2.Allergy WHERE T2.allergytype  =  "food")

text_query: What are the dates in which the mean sea level pressure was between 30.3 and 31?
sql_command: SELECT date FROM weather WHERE mean_sea_level_pressure_inches BETWEEN 30.3 AND 31

text_query: Find all procedures which cost more than 1000 or which physician John Wen was trained in.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM procedures WHERE cost  >  1000 UNION SELECT T3.name FROM physician AS T1 JOIN trained_in AS T2 ON T1.employeeid  =  T2.physician JOIN procedures AS T3 ON T3.code  =  T2.treatment WHERE T1.name  =  "John Wen"

text_query: Find the year and semester when offers the largest number of courses.
sql_command: SELECT semester ,  YEAR FROM SECTION GROUP BY semester ,  YEAR ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the ids and first names of the 3 teachers that have the most number of assessment notes?
sql_command: SELECT T1.teacher_id ,  T2.first_name FROM Assessment_Notes AS T1 JOIN Teachers AS T2 ON T1.teacher_id  =  T2.teacher_id GROUP BY T1.teacher_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: List all the information about course authors and tutors in alphabetical order of the personal name.
sql_command: SELECT * FROM Course_Authors_and_Tutors ORDER BY personal_name

text_query: list the name, job title of all people ordered by their names.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  job FROM Person ORDER BY name

text_query: Find the number of male (sex is 'M') students who have some food type allery.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Student WHERE sex  =  "M" AND StuID IN (SELECT StuID FROM Has_allergy AS T1 JOIN Allergy_Type AS T2 ON T1.Allergy  =  T2.Allergy WHERE T2.allergytype  =  "food")

text_query: How many CSU campuses are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM campuses

text_query: How many classes are professor whose last name is Graztevski has?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM employee AS T1 JOIN CLASS AS T2 ON T1.EMP_NUM  =  T2.PROF_NUM WHERE T1.EMP_LNAME  =  'Graztevski'

text_query: Show the reign and days held of wrestlers.
sql_command: SELECT Reign ,  Days_held FROM wrestler

text_query: Find the cell mobile number of the candidates whose assessment code is "Fail"?
sql_command: SELECT T3.cell_mobile_number FROM candidates AS T1 JOIN candidate_assessments AS T2 ON T1.candidate_id = T2.candidate_id JOIN people AS T3 ON T1.candidate_id = T3.person_id WHERE T2.asessment_outcome_code = "Fail"

text_query: Which major has between 2 and 30 number of students? List major and the number of students.
sql_command: SELECT Major ,  count(*) FROM Student GROUP BY Major HAVING count(Major) BETWEEN 2 AND 30;

text_query: How many games were played in park "Columbia Park" in 1907?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM home_game AS T1 JOIN park AS T2 ON T1.park_id  =  T2.park_id WHERE T1.year = 1907 AND T2.park_name = 'Columbia Park';

text_query: Show all sport name and the number of students.
sql_command: SELECT sportname ,  count(*) FROM Sportsinfo GROUP BY sportname

text_query: Show the school name and driver name for all school buses.
sql_command: SELECT T2.school ,  T3.name FROM school_bus AS T1 JOIN school AS T2 ON T1.school_id  =  T2.school_id JOIN driver AS T3 ON T1.driver_id  =  T3.driver_id

text_query: Find the appelations that produce wines after the year of 2008 but not in Central Coast area.
sql_command: SELECT Appelation FROM WINE WHERE YEAR  >  2008 EXCEPT SELECT Appelation FROM APPELLATIONS WHERE Area  =  "Central Coast"

text_query: Which film has the highest rental rate? And what is the rate?
sql_command: SELECT title ,  rental_rate FROM film ORDER BY rental_rate DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show different colleges along with the number of authors of submission from each college.
sql_command: SELECT College ,  COUNT(*) FROM submission GROUP BY College

text_query: Show the official names of the cities that have hosted more than one competition.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Official_Name FROM city AS T1 JOIN farm_competition AS T2 ON T1.City_ID  =  T2.Host_city_ID GROUP BY T2.Host_city_ID HAVING COUNT(*)  >  1

text_query: find the ids of reviewers who did not give 4 star.
sql_command: SELECT rID FROM Rating EXCEPT SELECT rID FROM Rating WHERE stars  =  4

text_query: How many female students (sex is F) whose age is below 25?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM student WHERE sex  =  'F' AND age  <  25

text_query: List the employees who have not showed up in any circulation history of documents. List the employee's name.
sql_command: SELECT employee_name FROM Employees EXCEPT SELECT Employees.employee_name FROM Employees JOIN Circulation_History ON Circulation_History.employee_id = Employees.employee_id

text_query: How many different industries are the companies in?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT Industry) FROM Companies

text_query: How many different kinds of information sources are there for injury accidents?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT SOURCE) FROM injury_accident

text_query: What is the name of the marketing region that the store Rob Dinning belongs to?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Marketing_Region_Name FROM Marketing_Regions AS T1 JOIN Stores AS T2 ON T1.Marketing_Region_Code  =  T2.Marketing_Region_Code WHERE T2.Store_Name  =  "Rob Dinning"

text_query: Find the name, city, country, and altitude (or elevation) of the airports in the city of New York.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  city ,  country ,  elevation FROM airports WHERE city  =  'New York'

text_query: Please list all album titles in alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT Title FROM ALBUM ORDER BY Title

text_query: List all open years when at least two shops are opened.
sql_command: SELECT open_year FROM branch GROUP BY open_year HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: Show the most frequently used carrier of the phones.
sql_command: SELECT Carrier FROM phone GROUP BY Carrier ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the titles of books that are not published.
sql_command: SELECT Title FROM book WHERE Book_ID NOT IN (SELECT Book_ID FROM publication)

text_query: Show the product type codes which have at least two products.
sql_command: SELECT product_type_code FROM products GROUP BY product_type_code HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: Show the maximum share count of transactions where the amount is smaller than 10000
sql_command: SELECT max(share_count) FROM TRANSACTIONS WHERE amount_of_transaction  <  10000

text_query: What are the descriptions and names of the courses that have student enrollment bigger than 2?
sql_command: SELECT T1.course_description ,  T1.course_name FROM Courses AS T1 JOIN Student_Course_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.course_id  =  T2.course_id GROUP BY T1.course_name HAVING COUNT(*)  >  2

text_query: How many enzymes do not have any interactions?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM enzyme WHERE id NOT IN ( SELECT enzyme_id FROM medicine_enzyme_interaction );

text_query: Find the name of customers who did not pay with Cash.
sql_command: SELECT customer_name FROM customers WHERE payment_method != 'Cash'

text_query: What are the title and issues of the books?
sql_command: SELECT Title ,  Issues FROM book

text_query: List all the login names and family names of course author and tutors.
sql_command: SELECT login_name ,  family_name FROM Course_Authors_and_Tutors

text_query: What is the number of distinct continents where Chinese is spoken?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT( DISTINCT Continent) FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "Chinese"

text_query: Find the names of all instructors whose name includes the substring “dar”.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM instructor WHERE name LIKE '%dar%'

text_query: What are the birthdays of people in ascending order of height?
sql_command: SELECT Birth_Date FROM People ORDER BY Height ASC

text_query: What is the total point count of the youngest gymnast?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Total_Points FROM gymnast AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.Gymnast_ID  =  T2.People_ID ORDER BY T2.Age ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the characteristic name used by most number of the products?
sql_command: SELECT t3.characteristic_name FROM products AS t1 JOIN product_characteristics AS t2 ON t1.product_id  =  t2.product_id JOIN CHARACTERISTICS AS t3 ON t2.characteristic_id  =  t3.characteristic_id GROUP BY t3.characteristic_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many apartments do not have any facility?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Apartments WHERE apt_id NOT IN (SELECT apt_id FROM Apartment_Facilities)

text_query: How many markets have number of cities smaller than 300?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM market WHERE Number_cities  <  300

text_query: List member names and their party names.
sql_command: SELECT T1.member_name ,  T2.party_name FROM Member AS T1 JOIN party AS T2 ON T1.party_id  =  T2.party_id

text_query: What is the number of distinct publication dates?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT (DISTINCT Publication_Date) FROM publication

text_query: How many services has each resident requested? List the resident id, details, and the count in descending order of the count.
sql_command: SELECT T1.resident_id ,  T1.other_details ,  count(*) FROM Residents AS T1 JOIN Residents_Services AS T2 ON T1.resident_id  =  T2.resident_id GROUP BY T1.resident_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC

text_query: Find the average credit score of the customers who have some loan.
sql_command: SELECT avg(credit_score) FROM customer WHERE cust_id IN (SELECT cust_id FROM loan)

text_query: List the information of all instructors ordered by their salary in ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT * FROM instructor ORDER BY salary

text_query: Show the school name and type for schools without a school bus.
sql_command: SELECT school ,  TYPE FROM school WHERE school_id NOT IN (SELECT school_id FROM school_bus)

text_query: Show all directors.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT directed_by FROM film

text_query: How many available features are there in total?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Other_Available_Features

text_query: Show the names of people, and dates and venues of debates they are on the negative side, ordered in ascending alphabetical order of name.
sql_command: SELECT T3.Name ,  T2.Date ,  T2.Venue FROM debate_people AS T1 JOIN debate AS T2 ON T1.Debate_ID  =  T2.Debate_ID JOIN people AS T3 ON T1.Negative  =  T3.People_ID ORDER BY T3.Name ASC

text_query: What is the age of the friend of Zach with longest year relationship?
sql_command: SELECT T1.age FROM Person AS T1 JOIN PersonFriend AS T2 ON T1.name  =  T2.friend WHERE T2.name =  'Zach' AND T2.year  =  (SELECT max(YEAR) FROM PersonFriend WHERE name =  'Zach')

text_query: List the total number of horses on farms in ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT Total_Horses FROM farm ORDER BY Total_Horses ASC

text_query: Find the name of the program that is broadcast most frequently.
sql_command: SELECT t1.name FROM program AS t1 JOIN broadcast AS t2 ON t1.program_id  =  t2.program_id GROUP BY t2.program_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the state in the US with the most invoices.
sql_command: SELECT billing_state ,  COUNT(*) FROM invoices WHERE billing_country  =  "USA" GROUP BY billing_state ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1;

text_query: Show all game ids and the number of hours played.
sql_command: SELECT gameid ,  sum(hours_played) FROM Plays_games GROUP BY gameid

text_query: List the name of all the distinct customers who have orders with status "Packing".
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.customer_name FROM customers AS T1 JOIN orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id WHERE T2.order_status = "Packing"

text_query: How many addresses are in the district of California?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM address WHERE district  =  'California'

text_query: How many distinct governors are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT Governor) FROM party

text_query: What is the average length in feet of the bridges?
sql_command: SELECT avg(length_feet) FROM bridge

text_query: Find the different first names and cities of the students who have allergy to milk or cat.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.fname ,  T1.city_code FROM Student AS T1 JOIN Has_Allergy AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid WHERE T2.Allergy  =  "Milk" OR T2.Allergy  =  "Cat"

text_query: What are the distinct publishers of publications with price higher than 5000000?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT Publisher FROM publication WHERE Price  >  5000000

text_query: Show aircraft names and number of flights for each aircraft.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name ,  count(*) FROM Flight AS T1 JOIN Aircraft AS T2 ON T1.aid  =  T2.aid GROUP BY T1.aid

text_query: Find the cities which were once a host city after 2010?
sql_command: SELECT T1.city FROM city AS T1 JOIN hosting_city AS T2 ON T1.city_id = T2.host_city WHERE T2.year  >  2010

text_query: How many captains are in each rank?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  rank FROM captain GROUP BY rank

text_query: List the name of all tracks in the playlists of Movies.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM tracks AS T1 JOIN playlist_tracks AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.track_id JOIN playlists AS T3 ON T3.id = T2.playlist_id WHERE T3.name = "Movies";

text_query: How many events have each participants attended? List the participant id, type and the number.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Participant_ID ,  T1.Participant_Type_Code ,  count(*) FROM Participants AS T1 JOIN Participants_in_Events AS T2 ON T1.Participant_ID  =  T2.Participant_ID GROUP BY T1.Participant_ID

text_query: Show the location code, the starting date and ending data in that location for all the documents.
sql_command: SELECT location_code ,  date_in_location_from ,  date_in_locaton_to FROM Document_locations

text_query: List the area and county of all appelations.
sql_command: SELECT Area ,  County FROM APPELLATIONS

text_query: What is the customer id of the customer who has the most orders?
sql_command: SELECT T1.customer_id FROM customers AS T1 JOIN orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id GROUP BY T1.customer_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the name of rooms with king or queen bed.
sql_command: SELECT roomName FROM Rooms WHERE bedType  =  "King" OR bedType  =  "Queen";

text_query: What is the total number of enrollment of schools that do not have any goalie player?
sql_command: SELECT sum(enr) FROM college WHERE cName NOT IN (SELECT cName FROM tryout WHERE pPos  =  "goalie")

text_query: List all statement ids and statement details.
sql_command: SELECT STATEMENT_ID ,  statement_details FROM Statements

text_query: Find the number of students whose city code is NYC and who have class senator votes in the spring election cycle.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM STUDENT AS T1 JOIN VOTING_RECORD AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  Class_Senator_Vote WHERE T1.city_code  =  "NYC" AND T2.Election_Cycle  =  "Spring"

text_query: Find the organisation ids and details of the organisations which are involved in
sql_command: SELECT T2.organisation_id ,  T2.organisation_details FROM Grants AS T1 JOIN Organisations AS T2 ON T1.organisation_id  =  T2.organisation_id GROUP BY T2.organisation_id HAVING sum(T1.grant_amount)  >  6000

text_query: Find the total and average amount paid in claim headers.
sql_command: SELECT sum(amount_piad) ,  avg(amount_piad) FROM claim_headers

text_query: What is the description of the color for most products?
sql_command: SELECT t2.color_description FROM products AS t1 JOIN ref_colors AS t2 ON t1.color_code  =  t2.color_code GROUP BY t2.color_description ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the minimum, average, and maximum age of all students.
sql_command: SELECT min(age) ,  avg(age) ,  max(age) FROM Student

text_query: Find the ids and names of members who are under age 30 or with black membership card.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  member_id FROM member WHERE Membership_card  =  'Black' OR age  <  30

text_query: Show names of people whose nationality is not "Russia".
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM people WHERE Nationality != "Russia"

text_query: How many activities do we have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Activity

text_query: Show different nationalities along with the number of hosts of each nationality.
sql_command: SELECT Nationality ,  COUNT(*) FROM HOST GROUP BY Nationality

text_query: Show all locations that have train stations with at least 15 platforms and train stations with more than 25 total passengers.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT LOCATION FROM station WHERE number_of_platforms  >=  15 AND total_passengers  >  25

text_query: Find names of all students who took some course and got A or C.
sql_command: SELECT T1.stu_fname ,  T1.stu_lname FROM student AS T1 JOIN enroll AS T2 ON T1.stu_num  =  T2.stu_num WHERE T2.enroll_grade  =  'C' OR T2.enroll_grade  =  'A'

text_query: How many lessons taught by staff whose first name has letter 'a' in it?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Lessons AS T1 JOIN Staff AS T2 ON T1.staff_id = T2.staff_id WHERE T2.first_name LIKE "%a%"

text_query: what are the name of players who get more than the average points.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM player WHERE points  >  (SELECT avg(points) FROM player)

text_query: Find the names of the artists who are from UK and have produced English songs.
sql_command: SELECT artist_name FROM artist WHERE country  =  "UK" INTERSECT SELECT artist_name FROM song WHERE languages  =  "english"

text_query: Find all manufacturers' names and their headquarters, sorted by the ones with highest revenue first.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  headquarter FROM manufacturers ORDER BY revenue DESC

text_query: Find the names of all instructors in computer science department
sql_command: SELECT name FROM instructor WHERE dept_name  =  'Comp. Sci.'

text_query: Find the first name and country code of the player who did the most number of tours.
sql_command: SELECT T1.country_code ,  T1.first_name FROM players AS T1 JOIN rankings AS T2 ON T1.player_id  =  T2.player_id ORDER BY T2.tours DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Report the first name and last name of all the teachers.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT firstname ,  lastname FROM teachers

text_query: List the ids, names and market shares of all browsers.
sql_command: SELECT id ,  name ,  market_share FROM browser

text_query: How many airlines does Russia has?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM airlines WHERE country  =  'Russia'

text_query: Show details of all investors if they make any transaction with share count greater than 100.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Investor_details FROM  INVESTORS AS T1 JOIN TRANSACTIONS AS T2 ON T1.investor_id  =  T2.investor_id WHERE T2.share_count  >  100

text_query: List the names of the customers who have once bought product "food".
sql_command: SELECT T1.customer_name FROM customers AS T1 JOIN orders AS T2 JOIN order_items AS T3 JOIN products AS T4 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id AND T2.order_id = T3.order_id AND T3.product_id = T4.product_id WHERE T4.product_name = "food" GROUP BY T1.customer_id HAVING count(*)  >=  1

text_query: What is the most common singer citizenship ?
sql_command: select citizenship from singer group by citizenship order by count(*) desc limit 1

text_query: What are the resident details containing the substring 'Miss'?
sql_command: SELECT other_details FROM Residents WHERE other_details LIKE '%Miss%'

text_query: List the names of poker players ordered by the final tables made in ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name FROM people AS T1 JOIN poker_player AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID ORDER BY T2.Final_Table_Made

text_query: Find the average hours of all projects.
sql_command: SELECT avg(hours) FROM projects

text_query: Find the first name and office of history professor who did not get a Ph.D. degree.
sql_command: SELECT T2.emp_fname ,  T1.prof_office FROM professor AS T1 JOIN employee AS T2 ON T1.emp_num  =  T2.emp_num JOIN department AS T3 ON T1.dept_code  =  T3.dept_code WHERE T3.dept_name  =  'History' AND T1.prof_high_degree != 'Ph.D.'

text_query: Which model of the car has the minimum horsepower?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id ORDER BY T2.horsepower ASC LIMIT 1;

text_query: In zip code 94107, on which day neither Fog nor Rain was not observed?
sql_command: SELECT date FROM weather WHERE zip_code  =  94107 AND EVENTS != "Fog" AND EVENTS != "Rain"

text_query: Which professionals have done at least two treatments? List the professional's id, role, and first name.
sql_command: SELECT T1.professional_id ,  T1.role_code ,  T1.first_name FROM Professionals AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 ON T1.professional_id  =  T2.professional_id GROUP BY T1.professional_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: How many games are held after season 2007?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM game WHERE season  >  2007

text_query: Who are the advisors for students that live in a city with city code "BAL"?
sql_command: SELECT Advisor FROM STUDENT WHERE city_code  =  "BAL"

text_query: What is the TV Channel of TV series with Episode "A Love of a Lifetime"? List the TV Channel's series name.
sql_command: SELECT T1.series_name FROM TV_Channel AS T1 JOIN TV_series AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.Channel WHERE T2.Episode = "A Love of a Lifetime";

text_query: Find the name of the department which has the highest average salary of professors.
sql_command: SELECT dept_name FROM instructor GROUP BY dept_name ORDER BY avg(salary) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the id and weight of all pets whose age is older than 1.
sql_command: SELECT petid ,  weight FROM pets WHERE pet_age  >  1

text_query: What are the names and descriptions of the products that are of 'Cutlery' type and have daily hire cost lower than 20?
sql_command: SELECT product_name ,  product_description FROM products_for_hire WHERE product_type_code  =  'Cutlery' AND daily_hire_cost  <  20

text_query: Which grade has the most high schoolers?
sql_command: SELECT grade FROM Highschooler GROUP BY grade ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many accounts does each customer have? List the number and customer id.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  customer_id FROM Accounts GROUP BY customer_id

text_query: What are the different nationalities of pilots? Show each nationality and the number of pilots of each nationality.
sql_command: SELECT Nationality ,  COUNT(*) FROM pilot GROUP BY Nationality

text_query: Find employee with ID and name of the country presently where (s)he is working.

sql_command: SELECT store_id FROM customer GROUP BY store_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find all the songs that do not have a lead vocal.

text_query: What is the carrier of the most expensive phone?
sql_command: SELECT Carrier FROM phone ORDER BY Price DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the names of representatives in descending order of votes?

text_query: What document type codes do we have?

text_query: Find the id of instructors who taught a class in Fall 2009 but not in Spring 2010.

text_query: List the names of counties in descending order of population.

text_query: Find the student ID and personal name of the student with at least two enrollments.

sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  count(*) FROM user_profiles AS T1 JOIN tweets AS T2 ON T1.uid  =  T2.uid GROUP BY T2.uid

sql_command: SELECT t1.name FROM ship AS t1 JOIN captain AS t2 ON t1.ship_id  =  t2.ship_id WHERE t2.rank  =  'Midshipman' INTERSECT SELECT t1.name FROM ship AS t1 JOIN captain AS t2 ON t1.ship_id  =  t2.ship_id WHERE t2.rank  =  'Lieutenant'

text_query: Show institution types, along with the number of institutions and total enrollment for each type.

sql_command: SELECT T1.Name ,  T2.Name FROM actor AS T1 JOIN musical AS T2 ON T1.Musical_ID  =  T2.Musical_ID

text_query: What are the maximum and average height of the mountains?
sql_command: SELECT max(height) ,  avg(height) FROM mountain

text_query: List the names of 5 users followed by the largest number of other users.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM user_profiles ORDER BY followers DESC LIMIT 5

sql_command: SELECT policy_type_code FROM available_policies GROUP BY policy_type_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many female students have milk or egg allergies?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM has_allergy AS T1 JOIN Student AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  T2.StuID WHERE T2.sex  =  "F" AND T1.allergy  =  "Milk" OR T1.allergy  =  "Eggs"

text_query: what are name and phone number of patients who had more than one appointment?
sql_command: SELECT name ,  phone FROM appointment AS T1 JOIN patient AS T2 ON T1.patient  =  T2.ssn GROUP BY T1.patient HAVING count(*)  >  1

text_query: List the locations of schools in ascending order of enrollment.
sql_command: SELECT LOCATION FROM school ORDER BY Enrollment ASC

sql_command: SELECT T1.campus FROM campuses AS T1 JOIN faculty AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.campus WHERE T2.year  =  2002 AND faculty  >  (SELECT max(faculty) FROM campuses AS T1 JOIN faculty AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.campus WHERE T2.year  =  2002 AND T1.county  =  "Orange")

text_query: Find the names of all the customers and staff members.

sql_command: SELECT instrument FROM instruments AS T1 JOIN songs AS T2 ON T1.songid  =  T2.songid WHERE title  =  "Le Pop"

sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Video_games WHERE gtype  =  "Massively multiplayer online game"

sql_command: SELECT first_name ,  last_name FROM Customers;

text_query: Find the distinct last names of all the students who have president votes and whose advisor is 8741.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.LName FROM STUDENT AS T1 JOIN VOTING_RECORD AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  PRESIDENT_Vote INTERSECT SELECT DISTINCT LName FROM STUDENT WHERE Advisor  =  "8741"

text_query: Find the id and local authority of the station with has the highest average high temperature.
sql_command: SELECT t2.id ,  t2.local_authority FROM weekly_weather AS t1 JOIN station AS t2 ON t1.station_id  =  t2.id GROUP BY t1.station_id ORDER BY avg(high_temperature) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the branch names of banks in the New York state.
sql_command: SELECT bname FROM bank WHERE state  =  'New York'

text_query: What are the name, latitude, and city of the station with the lowest latitude?
sql_command: SELECT name ,  lat ,  city FROM station ORDER BY lat LIMIT 1

text_query: Return the minister who left office at the latest time.
sql_command: SELECT minister FROM party ORDER BY left_office DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the version number and template type code for the template with version number later than 5?
sql_command: SELECT version_number ,  template_type_code FROM Templates WHERE version_number  >  5

text_query: List the name of actors whose age is not 20.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM actor WHERE Age != 20

text_query: What is the description of the product named "Chocolate"?
sql_command: SELECT product_description FROM products WHERE product_name  =  "Chocolate"

text_query: Find all the vocal types.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT TYPE FROM vocals

text_query: Find the products which have problems reported by both Lacey Bosco and Kenton Champlin?
sql_command: SELECT T2.product_name FROM problems AS T1 JOIN product AS T2 JOIN staff AS T3 ON T1.product_id = T2.product_id AND T1.reported_by_staff_id = T3.staff_id WHERE T3.staff_first_name = "Lacey" AND T3.staff_last_name = "Bosco" INTERSECT SELECT T2.product_name FROM problems AS T1 JOIN product AS T2 JOIN staff AS T3 ON T1.product_id = T2.product_id AND T1.reported_by_staff_id = T3.staff_id WHERE T3.staff_first_name = "Kenton" AND T3.staff_last_name = "Champlin"

text_query: Show first name and id for all customers with at least 2 accounts.
sql_command: SELECT T2.customer_first_name ,  T1.customer_id FROM Accounts AS T1 JOIN Customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id GROUP BY T1.customer_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: What is the maximum, minimum and average years spent working on a school bus?
sql_command: SELECT max(years_working) ,  min(years_working) ,  avg(years_working) FROM school_bus

text_query: What are the names of the airports which are not in the country 'Iceland'?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM airport WHERE country != 'Iceland'

text_query: List the names of teachers who have not been arranged to teach courses.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM teacher WHERE Teacher_id NOT IN (SELECT Teacher_id FROM course_arrange)

text_query: Who performed the song named "Badlands"? Show the first name and the last name.
sql_command: SELECT T2.firstname ,  T2.lastname FROM Performance AS T1 JOIN Band AS T2 ON T1.bandmate  =  T2.id JOIN Songs AS T3 ON T3.SongId  =  T1.SongId WHERE T3.Title  =  "Badlands"

text_query: Find the average life expectancy and total population for each continent where the average life expectancy is shorter than 72?
sql_command: SELECT sum(Population) ,  avg(LifeExpectancy) ,  Continent FROM country GROUP BY Continent HAVING avg(LifeExpectancy)  <  72

text_query: List the name of the stadium where both the player 'Walter Samuel' and the player 'Thiago Motta' got injured.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM game AS T1 JOIN stadium AS T2 ON T1.stadium_id  =  T2.id JOIN injury_accident AS T3 ON T1.id  =  T3.game_id WHERE T3.player  =  'Walter Samuel' INTERSECT SELECT T2.name FROM game AS T1 JOIN stadium AS T2 ON T1.stadium_id  =  T2.id JOIN injury_accident AS T3 ON T1.id  =  T3.game_id WHERE T3.player  =  'Thiago Motta'

text_query: What are the heights of perpetrators in descending order of the number of people they injured?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Height FROM people AS T1 JOIN perpetrator AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID ORDER BY T2.Injured DESC

text_query: Find the last names of the teachers that teach fifth grade.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T2.lastname FROM list AS T1 JOIN teachers AS T2 ON T1.classroom  =  T2.classroom WHERE grade  =  5

text_query: Which building has most faculty members?
sql_command: SELECT building FROM Faculty GROUP BY building ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the distinct ranges of the mountains with the top 3 prominence.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT Range FROM mountain ORDER BY Prominence DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: Show all branch names with the number of members in each branch registered after 2015.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name ,  count(*) FROM membership_register_branch AS T1 JOIN branch AS T2 ON T1.branch_id  =  T2.branch_id WHERE T1.register_year  >  2015 GROUP BY T2.branch_id

text_query: Which district has the least area?
sql_command: SELECT district_name FROM district ORDER BY city_area ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name and ID of the product whose total order quantity is the largest.
sql_command: SELECT t2.product_details ,  t2.product_id FROM order_items AS t1 JOIN products AS t2 ON t1.product_id  =  t2.product_id GROUP BY t1.product_id ORDER BY sum(t1.order_quantity) LIMIT 1

text_query: List the first and last name of students who are not living in the city with code HKG, and sorted the results by their ages.
sql_command: SELECT fname ,  lname FROM student WHERE city_code != 'HKG' ORDER BY age

text_query: What are the first name and last name of Linda Smith's advisor?
sql_command: SELECT T1.fname ,  T1.lname FROM Faculty AS T1 JOIN Student AS T2 ON T1.FacID  =  T2.advisor WHERE T2.fname  =  "Linda" AND T2.lname  =  "Smith"

text_query: Find all the payment dates for the payments with an amount larger than 10 and the payments handled by a staff person with the first name Elsa.
sql_command: SELECT payment_date FROM payment WHERE amount  >  10 UNION SELECT T1.payment_date FROM payment AS T1 JOIN staff AS T2 ON T1.staff_id  =  T2.staff_id WHERE T2.first_name  =  'Elsa'

text_query: List all schools and their nicknames in the order of founded year.
sql_command: SELECT school ,  nickname FROM university ORDER BY founded

text_query: Which country does Airline "JetBlue Airways" belong to?
sql_command: SELECT Country FROM AIRLINES WHERE Airline  =  "JetBlue Airways"

text_query: Show the headquarters that have at least two companies.
sql_command: SELECT Headquarters FROM company GROUP BY Headquarters HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  2

text_query: Please show the nominee who has been nominated the greatest number of times.
sql_command: SELECT Nominee FROM musical GROUP BY Nominee ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name and total checking and savings balance of the accounts whose savings balance is lower than corresponding checking balance.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  T3.balance + T2.balance FROM accounts AS T1 JOIN checking AS T2 ON T1.custid  =  T2.custid JOIN savings AS T3 ON T1.custid  =  T3.custid WHERE T3.balance  <  T2.balance

text_query: Show the description of transaction type with code "PUR".
sql_command: SELECT transaction_type_description FROM Ref_Transaction_Types WHERE transaction_type_code	  =  "PUR"

text_query: Find the number of concerts happened in the stadium with the highest capacity .
sql_command: select count(*) from concert where stadium_id = (select stadium_id from stadium order by capacity desc limit 1)

text_query: For the cars with 4 cylinders, which model has the largest horsepower?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id WHERE T2.Cylinders  =  4 ORDER BY T2.horsepower DESC LIMIT 1;

text_query: Which vocal type did the musician with last name "Heilo" played in the song with title "Der Kapitan"?
sql_command: SELECT TYPE FROM vocals AS T1 JOIN songs AS T2 ON T1.songid  =  T2.songid JOIN band AS T3 ON T1.bandmate  =  T3.id WHERE T3.lastname  =  "Heilo" AND T2.title  =  "Der Kapitan"

text_query: Find the total rating ratio for each channel owner.
sql_command: SELECT sum(Rating_in_percent) ,  OWNER FROM channel GROUP BY OWNER

text_query: Find the number of pets whose weight is heavier than 10.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM pets WHERE weight  >  10

text_query: Name all the products with next entry ID greater than 8.
sql_command: SELECT catalog_entry_name FROM catalog_contents WHERE next_entry_id  >  8

text_query: List the names of customers who have once canceled the purchase of the product "food" (the item status is "Cancel").
sql_command: SELECT T1.customer_name FROM customers AS T1 JOIN orders AS T2 JOIN order_items AS T3 JOIN products AS T4 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id AND T2.order_id = T3.order_id AND T3.product_id = T4.product_id WHERE T3.order_item_status = "Cancel" AND T4.product_name = "food" GROUP BY T1.customer_id HAVING count(*)  >=  1

text_query: What are the name, independence year, and surface area of the country with the smallest population?
sql_command: SELECT Name ,  SurfaceArea ,  IndepYear FROM country ORDER BY Population LIMIT 1

text_query: Show all flight numbers with aircraft Airbus A340-300.
sql_command: SELECT T1.flno FROM Flight AS T1 JOIN Aircraft AS T2 ON T1.aid  =  T2.aid WHERE T2.name  =  "Airbus A340-300"

text_query: How many artists do we have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM artist

text_query: List the names and origins of people who are not body builders.
sql_command: SELECT Name ,  birth_place FROM people EXCEPT SELECT T1.Name ,  T1.birth_place FROM people AS T1 JOIN body_builder AS T2 ON T1.people_id  =  T2.people_id

text_query: How many clubs does "Linda Smith" belong to?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid JOIN student AS t3 ON t2.stuid  =  t3.stuid WHERE t3.fname  =  "Linda" AND t3.lname  =  "Smith"

text_query: What is the name and the average gpa of department whose students have the highest average gpa?
sql_command: SELECT T2.dept_name ,  avg(T1.stu_gpa) FROM student AS T1 JOIN department AS T2 ON T1.dept_code  =  T2.dept_code GROUP BY T1.dept_code ORDER BY avg(T1.stu_gpa) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What campus had more than 400 total enrollment but more than 200 full time enrollment in year 1956?
sql_command: SELECT T1.campus FROM campuses AS t1 JOIN enrollments AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.campus WHERE t2.year  =  1956 AND totalenrollment_ay  >  400 AND FTE_AY  >  200

text_query: For each classroom, report the classroom number and the number of grades using it.
sql_command: SELECT classroom ,  count(DISTINCT grade) FROM list GROUP BY classroom

text_query: Count the products that have the color description "white" or have the characteristic name "hot".
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM products AS t1 JOIN product_characteristics AS t2 ON t1.product_id  =  t2.product_id JOIN CHARACTERISTICS AS t3 ON t2.characteristic_id  =  t3.characteristic_id JOIN ref_colors AS t4 ON t1.color_code  =  t4.color_code WHERE t4.color_description  =  "white" OR t3.characteristic_name  =  "hot"

text_query: What is the average age of the visitors whose membership level is not higher than 4?
sql_command: SELECT avg(age) FROM visitor WHERE Level_of_membership  <=  4

text_query: Show other account details for account with name 338.
sql_command: SELECT other_account_details FROM Accounts WHERE account_name  =  "338"

text_query: List the names of departments where some physicians are primarily affiliated with.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T2.name FROM affiliated_with AS T1 JOIN department AS T2 ON T1.department = T2.departmentid WHERE PrimaryAffiliation  =  1

text_query: What is the average unit price of tracks that belong to Jazz genre?
sql_command: SELECT AVG(UnitPrice) FROM GENRE AS T1 JOIN TRACK AS T2 ON T1.GenreId  =  T2.GenreId WHERE T1.Name  =  "Jazz"

text_query: What is average lesson price taught by staff with first name as Janessa and last name as Sawayn?
sql_command: SELECT avg(price) FROM Lessons AS T1 JOIN Staff AS T2 ON T1.staff_id = T2.staff_id WHERE T2.first_name = "Janessa" AND T2.last_name = "Sawayn";

text_query: Find the id and name of customers whose address contains WY state and do not use credit card for payment.
sql_command: SELECT customer_id ,  customer_name FROM customers WHERE customer_address LIKE "%WY%" AND payment_method_code != "Credit Card"

text_query: What are the phones and emails of workshop groups in which services are performed?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Store_Phone ,  T1.Store_Email_Address FROM Drama_Workshop_Groups AS T1 JOIN Services AS T2 ON T1.Workshop_Group_ID  =  T2.Workshop_Group_ID

text_query: Show ids, first names, last names, and phones for all customers.
sql_command: SELECT customer_id ,  customer_first_name ,  customer_last_name ,  customer_phone FROM Customers

text_query: Who is enrolled in a Bachelor degree program? List the first name, middle name, last name.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.first_name ,  T1.middle_name ,  T1.last_name FROM Students AS T1 JOIN Student_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.student_id JOIN Degree_Programs AS T3 ON T2.degree_program_id  =  T3.degree_program_id WHERE T3.degree_summary_name  =  'Bachelor'

text_query: Find the id and first name of the student that has the most number of assessment notes?
sql_command: SELECT T1.student_id ,  T2.first_name FROM Assessment_Notes AS T1 JOIN Students AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.student_id GROUP BY T1.student_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many aircrafts are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM aircraft

text_query: Find the names of all reviewers who rated Gone with the Wind.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T3.name FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID JOIN Reviewer AS T3 ON T1.rID  =  T3.rID WHERE T2.title  =  'Gone with the Wind'

text_query: Report the distinct president vote and the vice president vote.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT President_Vote ,  VICE_President_Vote FROM VOTING_RECORD

text_query: Which school has the smallest amount of professors?
sql_command: SELECT T1.school_code FROM department AS T1 JOIN professor AS T2 ON T1.dept_code  =  T2.dept_code GROUP BY T1.school_code ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the names of customers who use payment method "Cash"?
sql_command: SELECT customer_name FROM customers WHERE payment_method  =  "Cash"

text_query: What is the average age for each gender?
sql_command: SELECT avg(age) ,  gender FROM Person GROUP BY gender

text_query: List the names of editors that are not on any journal committee.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM editor WHERE editor_id NOT IN (SELECT editor_id FROM journal_committee)

text_query: What is the last name of the author that has published the most papers?
sql_command: SELECT t1.lname FROM authors AS t1 JOIN authorship AS t2 ON t1.authid  =  t2.authid JOIN papers AS t3 ON t2.paperid  =  t3.paperid GROUP BY t1.fname ,  t1.lname ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the names of Japanese constructors that have once earned more than 5 points?
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM constructors AS T1 JOIN constructorstandings AS T2 ON T1.constructorid = T2.constructorid WHERE T1.nationality = "Japanese" AND T2.points > 5

text_query: How many distinct types of accounts are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT acc_type) FROM customer

text_query: Select the average price of each manufacturer's products, showing the manufacturer's name.
sql_command: SELECT avg(T1.Price) ,  T2.name FROM products AS T1 JOIN Manufacturers AS T2 ON T1.manufacturer  =  T2.code GROUP BY T2.name

text_query: What are the id and zip code of the address with the highest monthly rental?
sql_command: SELECT T2.address_id ,  T1.zip_postcode FROM Addresses AS T1 JOIN Student_Addresses AS T2 ON T1.address_id  =  T2.address_id ORDER BY monthly_rental DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many females does this network has?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Person WHERE gender  =  'female'

text_query: Show the location name and code with the least documents.
sql_command: SELECT T2.location_name ,  T1.location_code FROM Document_locations AS T1 JOIN Ref_locations AS T2 ON T1.location_code  =  T2.location_code GROUP BY T1.location_code ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many poker players are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM poker_player

text_query: List the names of all distinct wines that are made of red color grape.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T2.Name FROM GRAPES AS T1 JOIN WINE AS T2 ON T1.Grape  =  T2.Grape WHERE T1.Color  =  "Red"

text_query: What is the average gpa of the students enrolled in the course with code ACCT-211?
sql_command: SELECT avg(T2.stu_gpa) FROM enroll AS T1 JOIN student AS T2 ON T1.stu_num  =  T2.stu_num JOIN CLASS AS T3 ON T1.class_code  =  T3.class_code WHERE T3.crs_code  =  'ACCT-211'

text_query: List the customer event id and the corresponding move in date and property id.
sql_command: SELECT customer_event_id ,  date_moved_in ,  property_id FROM customer_events

text_query: Show the name, home city, and age for all drivers.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  home_city ,  age FROM driver

text_query: Find all the addresses in East Julianaside, Texas or in Gleasonmouth, Arizona.
sql_command: SELECT address_content FROM addresses WHERE city  =  "East Julianaside" AND state_province_county  =  "Texas" UNION SELECT address_content FROM addresses WHERE city  =  "Gleasonmouth" AND state_province_county  =  "Arizona"

text_query: How many invoices do we have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Invoices

text_query: What is the entry name of the most expensive catalog (in USD)?
sql_command: SELECT catalog_entry_name FROM catalog_contents ORDER BY price_in_dollars DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List all restaurant types.
sql_command: SELECT ResTypeName FROM Restaurant_Type;

text_query: Show the players and the years played.
sql_command: SELECT Player ,  Years_Played FROM player

text_query: Find the names of stadiums which have never had any event.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM stadium WHERE id NOT IN (SELECT stadium_id FROM event)

text_query: Find the distinct names of all races held between 2014 and 2017?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT name FROM races WHERE YEAR BETWEEN 2014 AND 2017

text_query: What are the ids of templates with template type code PP or PPT?
sql_command: SELECT template_id FROM Templates WHERE template_type_code  =  "PP" OR template_type_code  =  "PPT"

text_query: Show the account name and other account detail for all accounts by the customer with first name Meaghan and last name Keeling.
sql_command: SELECT T1.account_name ,  T1.other_account_details FROM Accounts AS T1 JOIN Customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE T2.customer_first_name  =  "Meaghan" AND T2.customer_last_name  =  "Keeling"

text_query: Show all male student ids who don't play football.
sql_command: SELECT StuID FROM Student WHERE sex  =  'M' EXCEPT SELECT StuID FROM Sportsinfo WHERE sportname  =  "Football"

text_query: Show the manager name with most number of gas stations opened after 2000.
sql_command: SELECT manager_name FROM gas_station WHERE open_year  >  2000 GROUP BY manager_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the investor that has invested in the most number of entrepreneurs?
sql_command: SELECT Investor FROM entrepreneur GROUP BY Investor ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show all storm names affecting region "Denmark".
sql_command: SELECT T3.name FROM affected_region AS T1 JOIN region AS T2 ON T1.region_id  =  T2.region_id JOIN storm AS T3 ON T1.storm_id  =  T3.storm_id WHERE T2.region_name  =  'Denmark'

text_query: Retrieve the average age of members of the club "Tennis Club".
sql_command: SELECT avg(t3.age) FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid JOIN student AS t3 ON t2.stuid  =  t3.stuid WHERE t1.clubname  =  "Tennis Club"

text_query: What are the albums produced in year 2010?
sql_command: SELECT * FROM Albums WHERE YEAR  =  2010

text_query: Show all ministers and parties they belong to in descending order of the time they took office.
sql_command: SELECT minister ,  party_name FROM party ORDER BY took_office DESC

text_query: What is the total and maximum duration of trips with bike id 636?
sql_command: SELECT sum(duration) ,  max(duration) FROM trip WHERE bike_id  =  636

text_query: Show all distinct building descriptions.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT building_description FROM Apartment_Buildings

text_query: What are the distinct address type codes for all customer addresses?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT address_type_code FROM customer_addresses

text_query: How many faculty lines are there in the university that conferred the least number of degrees in year 2001?
sql_command: SELECT T2.faculty FROM campuses AS T1 JOIN faculty AS T2 ON T1.id  =  t2.campus JOIN degrees AS T3 ON T1.id  =  t3.campus AND t2.year  =  t3.year WHERE t2.year  =  2001 ORDER BY t3.degrees LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the number of different product types.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT product_type_code) FROM products

text_query: What is the location of the festival with the largest number of audience?
sql_command: SELECT LOCATION FROM festival_detail ORDER BY Num_of_Audience DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the average share count of transactions each each investor, ordered by average share count.
sql_command: SELECT investor_id ,  avg(share_count) FROM TRANSACTIONS GROUP BY investor_id ORDER BY avg(share_count)

text_query: Show the names of members and the locations of colleges they go to in ascending alphabetical order of member names.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name ,  T1.College_Location FROM college AS T1 JOIN member AS T2 ON T1.College_ID  =  T2.College_ID ORDER BY T2.Name ASC

text_query: Show all member names who are not in charge of any event.
sql_command: SELECT member_name FROM member EXCEPT SELECT T1.member_name FROM member AS T1 JOIN party_events AS T2 ON T1.member_id  =  T2.member_in_charge_id

text_query: List all the names of schools with an endowment amount smaller than or equal to 10.
sql_command: SELECT T2.school_name FROM endowment AS T1 JOIN school AS T2 ON T1.school_id  =  T2.school_id GROUP BY T1.school_id HAVING sum(T1.amount)  <=  10

text_query: Find the name and email of the users who have more than 1000 followers.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  email FROM user_profiles WHERE followers  >  1000

text_query: Find the government form name and total population for each government form whose average life expectancy is longer than 72.
sql_command: SELECT sum(Population) ,  GovernmentForm FROM country GROUP BY GovernmentForm HAVING avg(LifeExpectancy)  >  72

text_query: What are the distinct Famous release dates?
sql_command: SELECT distinct(Famous_Release_date) FROM artist

text_query: Find the city and state of the bank branch named morningside.
sql_command: SELECT city ,  state FROM bank WHERE bname  =  'morningside'

text_query: Find the name, age, and job title of persons who are friends with Alice for the longest years.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  T1.age ,  T1.job FROM Person AS T1 JOIN PersonFriend AS T2 ON T1.name  =  T2.name WHERE T2.friend =  'Alice' AND T2.year  =  (SELECT max(YEAR) FROM PersonFriend WHERE friend =  'Alice')

text_query: Show all transaction ids with transaction code 'PUR'.
sql_command: SELECT transaction_id FROM TRANSACTIONS WHERE transaction_type_code  =  'PUR'

text_query: Which paper is published in an institution in "USA" and have "Turon" as its second author?
sql_command: SELECT t3.title FROM authors AS t1 JOIN authorship AS t2 ON t1.authid  =  t2.authid JOIN papers AS t3 ON t2.paperid  =  t3.paperid JOIN inst AS t4 ON t2.instid  =  t4.instid WHERE t4.country  =  "USA" AND t2.authorder  =  2 AND t1.lname  =  "Turon"

text_query: What are names of stations that have average bike availability above 10 and are not located in San Jose city?
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM station AS T1 JOIN status AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.station_id GROUP BY T2.station_id HAVING avg(bikes_available)  >  10 EXCEPT SELECT name FROM station WHERE city  =  "San Jose"

text_query: how many programs are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM program

text_query: Which distinct car models are the produced after 1980?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.model FROM MODEL_LIST AS T1 JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T2 ON T1.model  =  T2.model JOIN CARS_DATA AS T3 ON T2.MakeId  =  T3.id WHERE T3.year  >  1980;

text_query: display the full name (first and last), hire date, salary, and department number for those employees whose first name does not containing the letter M.
sql_command: SELECT first_name ,  last_name ,  hire_date ,  salary ,  department_id FROM employees WHERE first_name NOT LIKE '%M%'

sql_command: SELECT LOCATION ,  COUNT(*) FROM performance GROUP BY LOCATION

text_query: List the names of the city with the top 5 white percentages.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM city ORDER BY White DESC LIMIT 5

text_query: What is the total number of languages used in Aruba?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(T2.Language) FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T1.Name  =  "Aruba"

text_query: List the nominees that have been nominated more than two musicals.
sql_command: SELECT Nominee FROM musical GROUP BY Nominee HAVING COUNT(*)  >  2

sql_command: SELECT LOCATION FROM cinema WHERE openning_year  >=  2010 GROUP BY LOCATION ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the average enrollment number?
sql_command: SELECT avg(enr) FROM College
