sql_command: SELECT email_address ,  date_of_birth FROM Customers WHERE first_name = "Carole"

text_query: Show each school name, its budgeted amount, and invested amount in year 2002 or after.
sql_command: SELECT T2.school_name ,  T1.budgeted ,  T1.invested FROM budget AS T1 JOIN school AS T2 ON T1.school_id  =  T2.school_id WHERE T1.year  >=  2002

text_query: How many students does LORIA ONDERSMA teaches?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM list AS T1 JOIN teachers AS T2 ON T1.classroom  =  T2.classroom WHERE T2.firstname  =  "LORIA" AND T2.lastname  =  "ONDERSMA"

text_query: Find the name and gender of the staff who has been assigned the job of Sales Person but never Clerical Staff.
sql_command: SELECT T1.staff_name ,  T1.staff_gender FROM staff AS T1 JOIN Staff_Department_Assignments AS T2 ON T1.staff_id  =  T2.staff_id WHERE T2.job_title_code  =  "Sales Person" EXCEPT SELECT T1.staff_name ,  T1.staff_gender FROM staff AS T1 JOIN Staff_Department_Assignments AS T2 ON T1.staff_id  =  T2.staff_id WHERE T2.job_title_code  =  "Clerical Staff"

text_query: Find the number of trains for each station, as well as the station network name and services.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  t1.network_name ,  t1.services FROM station AS t1 JOIN route AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.station_id GROUP BY t2.station_id

text_query: What is the name and description for document type code RV?
sql_command: SELECT document_type_name ,  document_type_description FROM Ref_document_types WHERE document_type_code  =  "RV"

text_query: Show titles of songs and names of singers.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Title ,  T1.Name FROM singer AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.Singer_ID  =  T2.Singer_ID

text_query: Find the names of all reviewers who have ratings with a NULL value for the date.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT name FROM Reviewer AS T1 JOIN Rating AS T2 ON T1.rID  =  T2.rID WHERE ratingDate  =  "null"

text_query: Show all video game types and the number of video games in each type.
sql_command: SELECT gtype ,  count(*) FROM Video_games GROUP BY gtype

text_query: List every album ordered by album title in ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT title FROM albums ORDER BY title;

text_query: What are the students' first names who have both cats and dogs as pets?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Fname FROM student AS T1 JOIN has_pet AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid JOIN pets AS T3 ON T3.petid  =  T2.petid WHERE T3.pettype  =  'cat' INTERSECT SELECT T1.Fname FROM student AS T1 JOIN has_pet AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid JOIN pets AS T3 ON T3.petid  =  T2.petid WHERE T3.pettype  =  'dog'

text_query: Compute the number of products with a price larger than or equal to $180.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM products WHERE price >= 180

text_query: What is minimum and maximum share of TV series?
sql_command: SELECT max(SHARE) , min(SHARE) FROM TV_series;

text_query: Find the names of schools that have more than one donator with donation amount above 8.5.
sql_command: SELECT T2.School_name FROM endowment AS T1 JOIN school AS T2 ON T1.school_id  =  T2.school_id WHERE T1.amount  >  8.5 GROUP BY T1.school_id HAVING count(*)  >  1

text_query: What are the product ids for the problems reported by Christop Berge with closure authorised by Ashley Medhurst?
sql_command: SELECT product_id FROM problems AS T1 JOIN staff AS T2 ON T1.reported_by_staff_id = T2.staff_id WHERE T2.staff_first_name = "Christop" AND T2.staff_last_name = "Berge" INTERSECT SELECT product_id FROM problems AS T1 JOIN staff AS T2 ON T1.closure_authorised_by_staff_id = T2.staff_id WHERE T2.staff_first_name = "Ashley" AND T2.staff_last_name = "Medhurst"

text_query: List the all the assets make, model, details by the disposed date ascendingly.
sql_command: SELECT asset_make ,  asset_model ,  asset_details FROM Assets ORDER BY asset_disposed_date ASC

text_query: Find the physicians who are trained in a procedure that costs more than 5000.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM physician AS T1 JOIN trained_in AS T2 ON T1.employeeid  =  T2.physician JOIN procedures AS T3 ON T3.code  =  T2.treatment WHERE T3.cost  >  5000

text_query: Find the name of the department that has the biggest number of students minored in?
sql_command: SELECT T1.DName FROM DEPARTMENT AS T1 JOIN MINOR_IN AS T2 ON T1.DNO  =  T2.DNO GROUP BY T2.DNO ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the list of attribute data types possessed by more than 3 attribute definitions.
sql_command: SELECT attribute_data_type FROM Attribute_Definitions GROUP BY attribute_data_type HAVING count(*)  >  3

text_query: Show name and distance for all aircrafts.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  distance FROM Aircraft

text_query: Show the card type codes and the number of transactions.
sql_command: SELECT T2.card_type_code ,  count(*) FROM Financial_transactions AS T1 JOIN Customers_cards AS T2 ON T1.card_id  =  T2.card_id GROUP BY T2.card_type_code

text_query: Find the rooms of faculties with rank professor who live in building NEB.
sql_command: SELECT Room FROM FACULTY WHERE Rank  =  "Professor" AND Building  =  "NEB"

text_query: List the addresses of all the course authors or tutors.
sql_command: SELECT address_line_1 FROM Course_Authors_and_Tutors

text_query: List the name, location, mascot for all schools.
sql_command: SELECT school_name ,  LOCATION ,  mascot FROM school

text_query: Find out the top 10 customers by total number of orders. List customers' first and last name and the number of total orders.
sql_command: SELECT T1.first_name ,  T1.last_name ,  COUNT(*) FROM customers AS T1 JOIN invoices AS T2 ON T2.customer_id  =  T1.id GROUP BY T1.id ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 10;

text_query: Find the names of all procedures such that the cost is less than 5000 and physician John Wen was trained in.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM procedures WHERE cost  <  5000 INTERSECT SELECT T3.name FROM physician AS T1 JOIN trained_in AS T2 ON T1.employeeid  =  T2.physician JOIN procedures AS T3 ON T3.code  =  T2.treatment WHERE T1.name  =  "John Wen"

text_query: Find the name and email for the users who have more than one follower.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  T1.email FROM user_profiles AS T1 JOIN follows AS T2 ON T1.uid  =  T2.f1 GROUP BY T2.f1 HAVING count(*)  >  1

text_query: Show the names of members that have a rank in round higher than 3.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name FROM member AS T1 JOIN round AS T2 ON T1.Member_ID  =  T2.Member_ID WHERE T2.Rank_in_Round  >  3

text_query: Find the number of routes operated by American Airlines.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM airlines AS T1 JOIN routes AS T2 ON T1.alid  =  T2.alid WHERE T1.name  =  'American Airlines'

text_query: Find the first name of student who is taking classes from accounting and Computer Info. Systems departments
sql_command: SELECT T1.stu_fname FROM student AS T1 JOIN enroll AS T2 ON T1.stu_num  =  T2.stu_num JOIN CLASS AS T3 ON T2.class_code  =  T3.class_code JOIN course AS T4 ON T3.crs_code  =  T4.crs_code JOIN department AS T5 ON T5.dept_code  =  T4.dept_code WHERE T5.dept_name  =  'Accounting' INTERSECT SELECT T1.stu_fname FROM student AS T1 JOIN enroll AS T2 ON T1.stu_num  =  T2.stu_num JOIN CLASS AS T3 ON T2.class_code  =  T3.class_code JOIN course AS T4 ON T3.crs_code  =  T4.crs_code JOIN department AS T5 ON T5.dept_code  =  T4.dept_code WHERE T5.dept_name  =  'Computer Info. Systems'

text_query: Find the personal names of students not enrolled in any course.
sql_command: SELECT personal_name FROM Students EXCEPT SELECT T1.personal_name FROM Students AS T1 JOIN Student_Course_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.student_id

text_query: How many cities are in Australia?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM city AS T1 JOIN country AS T2 ON T1.country_id  =  T2.country_id WHERE T2.country  =  'Australia'

text_query: What are the record companies of orchestras in descending order of years in which they were founded?
sql_command: SELECT Record_Company FROM orchestra ORDER BY Year_of_Founded DESC

text_query: Show the name of aircrafts with top three lowest distances.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM Aircraft ORDER BY distance LIMIT 3

text_query: What are the total number of the audiences who visited any of the festivals?
sql_command: SELECT sum(Num_of_Audience) FROM festival_detail

text_query: What is the average longitude of stations that never had bike availability more than 10?
sql_command: SELECT avg(long) FROM station WHERE id NOT IN (SELECT station_id FROM status GROUP BY station_id HAVING max(bikes_available)  >  10)

text_query: Which papers have "Stephanie Weirich" as an author?
sql_command: SELECT t3.title FROM authors AS t1 JOIN authorship AS t2 ON t1.authid  =  t2.authid JOIN papers AS t3 ON t2.paperid  =  t3.paperid WHERE t1.fname  =  "Stephanie" AND t1.lname  =  "Weirich"

text_query: Show all the ranks and the number of male and female faculty for each rank.
sql_command: SELECT rank ,  sex ,  count(*) FROM Faculty GROUP BY rank ,  sex

text_query: What are the name and typical buying and selling prices of the products that have color described as "yellow"?
sql_command: SELECT t1.product_name ,  t1.typical_buying_price ,  t1.typical_selling_price FROM products AS t1 JOIN ref_colors AS t2 ON t1.color_code  =  t2.color_code WHERE t2.color_description  =  "yellow"

text_query: Find the average number of staff working for the museums that were open before 2009.
sql_command: SELECT avg(num_of_staff) FROM museum WHERE open_year  <  2009

text_query: What are all the distinct payment types?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT payment_type_code FROM payments

text_query: What are the names and years of the movies that has the top 3 highest rating star?
sql_command: SELECT T2.title ,  T2.year FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID ORDER BY T1.stars DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: How many courses in total are listed?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Courses

text_query: How many papers have "Atsushi Ohori" published?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM authors AS t1 JOIN authorship AS t2 ON t1.authid  =  t2.authid JOIN papers AS t3 ON t2.paperid  =  t3.paperid WHERE  t1.fname  =  "Atsushi" AND t1.lname  =  "Ohori"

text_query: Who are the top 3 players in terms of overall rating?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.player_name FROM Player AS T1 JOIN Player_Attributes AS T2 ON T1.player_api_id  =  T2.player_api_id ORDER BY overall_rating DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: Find the average number of followers for the users who do not have any tweet.
sql_command: SELECT avg(followers) FROM user_profiles WHERE UID NOT IN (SELECT UID FROM tweets)

text_query: Find the title of the course that is offered by more than one department.
sql_command: SELECT title FROM course GROUP BY title HAVING count(*)  >  1

text_query: Show the name and date for each race and its track name.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  T1.date ,  T2.name FROM race AS T1 JOIN track AS T2 ON T1.track_id  =  T2.track_id

text_query: Which allergy has most number of students affected?
sql_command: SELECT Allergy FROM Has_allergy GROUP BY Allergy ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the smallest weight of the car produced with 8 cylinders on 1974 ?
sql_command: select min(weight) from cars_data where cylinders  =  8 and year  =  1974

text_query: Show all main industry for all companies.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT main_industry FROM company

text_query: What is the name of the claim processing stage that most of the claims are on?
sql_command: SELECT t2.claim_status_name FROM claims_processing AS t1 JOIN claims_processing_stages AS t2 ON t1.claim_stage_id  =  t2.claim_stage_id GROUP BY t1.claim_stage_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Are the customers holding coupons with amount 500 bad or good?
sql_command: SELECT T1.good_or_bad_customer FROM customers AS T1 JOIN discount_coupons AS T2 ON T1.coupon_id  =  T2.coupon_id WHERE T2.coupon_amount  =  500

text_query: Which catalog publisher has published the most catalogs?
sql_command: SELECT catalog_publisher FROM catalogs GROUP BY catalog_publisher ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the delegate from district 1 in election.
sql_command: SELECT Delegate FROM election WHERE District  =  1

text_query: list the local authorities and services provided by all stations.
sql_command: SELECT local_authority ,  services FROM station

text_query: Show all ages and corresponding number of students.
sql_command: SELECT age ,  count(*) FROM Student GROUP BY age

text_query: Show the names of editors and the theme of journals for which they serve on committees.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name ,  T3.Theme FROM journal_committee AS T1 JOIN editor AS T2 ON T1.Editor_ID  =  T2.Editor_ID JOIN journal AS T3 ON T1.Journal_ID  =  T3.Journal_ID

text_query: What are the numbers of wines for different grapes?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  Grape FROM WINE GROUP BY Grape

text_query: Show all student ids who are older than 20.
sql_command: SELECT StuID FROM Student WHERE age  >  20

text_query: Show the average amount of transactions for different investors.
sql_command: SELECT investor_id ,  avg(amount_of_transaction) FROM TRANSACTIONS GROUP BY investor_id

text_query: What are the countries of perpetrators? Show each country and the corresponding number of perpetrators there.
sql_command: SELECT Country ,  COUNT(*) FROM perpetrator GROUP BY Country

text_query: Please show different types of artworks with the corresponding number of artworks of each type.
sql_command: SELECT TYPE ,  COUNT(*) FROM artwork GROUP BY TYPE

text_query: How many players were in the team Boston Red Stockings in 2000?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM salary AS T1 JOIN team AS T2 ON T1.team_id  =  T2.team_id_br WHERE T2.name  = 'Boston Red Stockings' AND T1.year  =  2000

text_query: Find the names of stadiums that the most swimmers have been to.
sql_command: SELECT t3.name FROM record AS t1 JOIN event AS t2 ON t1.event_id  =  t2.id JOIN stadium AS t3 ON t3.id  =  t2.stadium_id GROUP BY t2.stadium_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the name, IHSAA Football Class, and Mascot of the schools that have more than 6000 of budgeted amount or were founded before 2003, in the order of percent of total invested budget and total budgeted budget.
sql_command: SELECT T1.School_name ,  T1.Mascot ,  T1.IHSAA_Football_Class FROM school AS T1 JOIN budget AS T2 ON T1.school_id  =  T2.school_id WHERE Budgeted  >  6000 OR YEAR  <  2003 ORDER BY T2.total_budget_percent_invested ,  T2.total_budget_percent_budgeted

text_query: Show the names and ages of editors and the theme of journals for which they serve on committees, in ascending alphabetical order of theme.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name ,  T2.age ,  T3.Theme FROM journal_committee AS T1 JOIN editor AS T2 ON T1.Editor_ID  =  T2.Editor_ID JOIN journal AS T3 ON T1.Journal_ID  =  T3.Journal_ID ORDER BY T3.Theme ASC

text_query: What are the names of the physician who prescribed the highest dose?
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM physician AS T1 JOIN prescribes AS T2 ON T1.employeeid = T2.physician ORDER BY T2.dose DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the name of employees with three lowest salaries.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM Employee ORDER BY salary ASC LIMIT 3

text_query: How many paragraphs for the document with name 'Summer Show'?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Paragraphs AS T1 JOIN Documents AS T2 ON T1.document_ID  =  T2.document_ID WHERE T2.document_name  =  'Summer Show'

text_query: What are the titles of papers published by "Jeremy Gibbons"?
sql_command: SELECT t3.title FROM authors AS t1 JOIN authorship AS t2 ON t1.authid  =  t2.authid JOIN papers AS t3 ON t2.paperid  =  t3.paperid WHERE  t1.fname  =  "Jeremy" AND t1.lname  =  "Gibbons"

text_query: Find the name of the swimmer who has at least 2 records.
sql_command: SELECT t1.name FROM swimmer AS t1 JOIN record AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.swimmer_id GROUP BY t2.swimmer_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: What are the names of perpetrators in country "China" or "Japan"?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name FROM people AS T1 JOIN perpetrator AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID WHERE T2.Country  =  "China" OR T2.Country  =  "Japan"

text_query: Which artist does the album "Balls to the Wall" belong to?
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name FROM ALBUM AS T1 JOIN ARTIST AS T2 ON T1.ArtistId  =  T2.ArtistId WHERE T1.Title  =  "Balls to the Wall"

text_query: What is the first name of students enrolled in class ACCT-211 and got grade C?
sql_command: SELECT T3.stu_fname FROM CLASS AS T1 JOIN enroll AS T2 ON T1.class_code  =  T2.class_code JOIN student AS T3 ON T2.stu_num  =  T3.stu_num WHERE T1.crs_code  =  'ACCT-211' AND T2.enroll_grade  =  'C'

text_query: How many schools do not participate in the basketball match?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM university WHERE school_id NOT IN (SELECT school_id FROM basketball_match)

text_query: Show the names of players and names of their coaches.
sql_command: SELECT T3.Player_name ,  T2.coach_name FROM player_coach AS T1 JOIN coach AS T2 ON T1.Coach_ID  =  T2.Coach_ID JOIN player AS T3 ON T1.Player_ID  =  T3.Player_ID

text_query: Show names of cities and names of counties they are in.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name ,  T2.Name FROM city AS T1 JOIN county_public_safety AS T2 ON T1.County_ID  =  T2.County_ID

text_query: Retrieve the country that has published the most papers.
sql_command: SELECT t1.country FROM inst AS t1 JOIN authorship AS t2 ON t1.instid  =  t2.instid JOIN papers AS t3 ON t2.paperid  =  t3.paperid GROUP BY t1.country ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many songs have a lead vocal?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT title) FROM vocals AS T1 JOIN songs AS T2 ON T1.songid  =  T2.songid WHERE TYPE  =  "lead"

text_query: What is the average base price of different bed type? List bed type and average base price.
sql_command: SELECT bedType ,  avg(basePrice) FROM Rooms GROUP BY bedType;

text_query: Show card type codes with at least 5 cards.
sql_command: SELECT card_type_code FROM Customers_cards GROUP BY card_type_code HAVING count(*)  >=  5

text_query: For grants with both documents described as 'Regular' and documents described as 'Initial Application', list its start date.
sql_command: SELECT T1.grant_start_date FROM Grants AS T1 JOIN Documents AS T2 ON T1.grant_id  =  T2.grant_id JOIN Document_Types AS T3 ON T2.document_type_code  =  T3.document_type_code WHERE T3.document_description  =  'Regular' INTERSECT SELECT T1.grant_start_date FROM Grants AS T1 JOIN Documents AS T2 ON T1.grant_id  =  T2.grant_id JOIN Document_Types AS T3 ON T2.document_type_code  =  T3.document_type_code WHERE T3.document_description  =  'Initial Application'

text_query: Find the name of rooms whose price is higher than the average price.
sql_command: SELECT roomName FROM Rooms WHERE basePrice  >  ( SELECT avg(basePrice) FROM Rooms );

text_query: find the package option of the tv channel that do not have any cartoon directed by Ben Jones.
sql_command: SELECT package_option FROM TV_Channel WHERE id NOT IN (SELECT channel FROM cartoon WHERE directed_by  =  'Ben Jones')

text_query: How many stadiums are not in country "Russia"?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM stadium WHERE country != 'Russia'

text_query: Show all role codes with at least 3 employees.
sql_command: SELECT role_code FROM Employees GROUP BY role_code HAVING count(*)  >=  3

text_query: What is the product description of the product booked with an amount of 102.76?
sql_command: SELECT T2.product_description FROM products_booked AS T1 JOIN products_for_hire AS T2 ON T1.product_id  =  T2.product_id WHERE T1.booked_amount  =  102.76

text_query: Which kind of part has the least number of faults? List the part name.
sql_command: SELECT T1.part_name FROM Parts AS T1 JOIN Part_Faults AS T2 ON T1.part_id  =  T2.part_id GROUP BY T1.part_name ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the names of sponsors of players whose residence is either "Brandon" or "Birtle".
sql_command: SELECT Sponsor_name FROM player WHERE Residence  =  "Brandon" OR Residence  =  "Birtle"

text_query: What is the level name of the cheapest catalog (in USD)?
sql_command: SELECT t2.catalog_level_name FROM catalog_contents AS t1 JOIN catalog_structure AS t2 ON t1.catalog_level_number  =  t2.catalog_level_number ORDER BY t1.price_in_dollars LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the tax source system code related to the benefits and overpayments? List the code and the benifit id, order by benifit id.
sql_command: SELECT T1.source_system_code ,  T2.council_tax_id FROM CMI_Cross_References AS T1 JOIN Benefits_Overpayments AS T2 ON T1.cmi_cross_ref_id  =  T2.cmi_cross_ref_id ORDER BY T2.council_tax_id

text_query: How many different countries are all the swimmers from?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT nationality) FROM swimmer

text_query: List the number of invoices from the US, grouped by state.
sql_command: SELECT billing_state ,  COUNT(*) FROM invoices WHERE billing_country  =  "USA" GROUP BY billing_state;

text_query: Find the addresses of the course authors who teach the course with name "operating system" or "data structure".
sql_command: SELECT T1.address_line_1 FROM Course_Authors_and_Tutors AS T1 JOIN Courses AS T2 ON T1.author_id  =  T2.author_id WHERE T2.course_name  =  "operating system" OR T2.course_name  =  "data structure"

text_query: What is the product category description and unit of measurement of category "Herbs"?
sql_command: SELECT product_category_description ,  unit_of_measure FROM ref_product_categories WHERE product_category_code  =  "Herbs"

text_query: Which vocal type has the band mate with first name "Solveig" played the most?
sql_command: SELECT TYPE FROM vocals AS T1 JOIN band AS T2 ON T1.bandmate  =  T2.id WHERE firstname  =  "Solveig" GROUP BY TYPE ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the description of the restaurant type Sandwich?
sql_command: SELECT ResTypeDescription FROM Restaurant_Type WHERE ResTypeName = "Sandwich";

text_query: What are the names of stations that are located in Palo Alto city but have never been the ending point of trips more than 100 times?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM station WHERE city  =  "Palo Alto" EXCEPT SELECT end_station_name FROM trip GROUP BY end_station_name HAVING count(*)  >  100

text_query: Please show the titles of films and the types of market estimations.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Title ,  T2.Type FROM film AS T1 JOIN film_market_estimation AS T2 ON T1.Film_ID  =  T2.Film_ID

text_query: Show the names and heights of buildings with at least two institutions founded after 1880.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  T1.height_feet FROM building AS T1 JOIN institution AS T2 ON T1.building_id  =  T2.building_id WHERE T2.founded  >  1880 GROUP BY T1.building_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: What is the number of the cars with horsepower more than 150?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM CARS_DATA WHERE horsepower  >  150;

text_query: Select the name of the products with a price less than or equal to $200.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM products WHERE price  <=  200

text_query: Show ids for all the male faculty.
sql_command: SELECT FacID FROM Faculty WHERE Sex  =  'M'

text_query: What are the country names, area and population which has both roller coasters with speed higher
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  T1.area ,  T1.population FROM country AS T1 JOIN roller_coaster AS T2 ON T1.Country_ID  =  T2.Country_ID WHERE T2.speed  >  60 INTERSECT SELECT T1.name ,  T1.area ,  T1.population FROM country AS T1 JOIN roller_coaster AS T2 ON T1.Country_ID  =  T2.Country_ID WHERE T2.speed  <  55

text_query: Which events id does not have any participant with detail 'Kenyatta Kuhn'?
sql_command: SELECT event_id FROM EVENTS EXCEPT SELECT T1.event_id FROM Participants_in_Events AS T1 JOIN Participants AS T2 ON T1.Participant_ID  =  T2.Participant_ID WHERE Participant_Details  =  'Kenyatta Kuhn'

text_query: Find the number of vocal types used in song "Le Pop"
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM vocals AS T1 JOIN songs AS T2 ON T1.songid  =  T2.songid WHERE title  =  "Le Pop"

text_query: Give me the average prices of wines that are produced by appelations in Sonoma County.
sql_command: SELECT AVG(T2.Price) FROM APPELLATIONS AS T1 JOIN WINE AS T2 ON T1.Appelation  =  T2.Appelation WHERE T1.County  =  "Sonoma"

text_query: What is the name of the shipping agent of the document with id 2?
sql_command: SELECT Ref_Shipping_Agents.shipping_agent_name FROM Ref_Shipping_Agents JOIN Documents ON Documents.shipping_agent_code = Ref_Shipping_Agents.shipping_agent_code WHERE Documents.document_id = 2;

text_query: What states have at least two representatives?
sql_command: SELECT State FROM representative GROUP BY State HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  2

text_query: How many Patent outcomes are generated from all the projects?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Project_outcomes WHERE outcome_code  =  'Patent'

text_query: Which first names are used for professionals or owners but are not used as dog names?
sql_command: SELECT first_name FROM Professionals UNION SELECT first_name FROM Owners EXCEPT SELECT name FROM Dogs

text_query: List the names of all distinct nurses ordered by alphabetical order?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT name FROM nurse ORDER BY name

text_query: List the names of people that are not perpetrators.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM people WHERE People_ID NOT IN (SELECT People_ID FROM perpetrator)

text_query: What are the names of the countries that are in the continent of Europe and have a population of 80000?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM country WHERE continent  =  "Europe" AND Population  =  "80000"

text_query: List the names of all winners who played in both 2013 and 2016.
sql_command: SELECT winner_name FROM matches WHERE YEAR  =  2013 INTERSECT SELECT winner_name FROM matches WHERE YEAR  =  2016

text_query: Find the name, headquarter and founder of the manufacturer that has the highest revenue.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  headquarter ,  founder FROM manufacturers ORDER BY revenue DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the id and name of the most expensive base price room.

text_query: What is the full name ( first name and last name ) for those employees who gets more salary than the employee whose id is 163?
sql_command: SELECT first_name ,  last_name FROM employees WHERE salary  >  (SELECT salary FROM employees WHERE employee_id = 163 )

text_query: What are the drivers' last names and id who had 11 pit stops and participated in more than 5 race results?
sql_command: SELECT T1.surname ,  T1.driverid FROM drivers AS T1 JOIN pitstops AS T2 ON T1.driverid  =  T2.driverid GROUP BY T1.driverid HAVING count(*)  =  11 INTERSECT SELECT T1.surname ,  T1.driverid FROM drivers AS T1 JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.driverid  =  T2.driverid GROUP BY T1.driverid HAVING count(*)  >  5

text_query: Show the names of people aged either 35 or 36.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM  people WHERE Age  =  35 OR Age  =  36

text_query: Display all the information about the department Marketing.
sql_command: SELECT * FROM  departments WHERE department_name  =  'Marketing'

text_query: What is the average price of the products for each category?
sql_command: SELECT avg(product_price) ,  product_category_code FROM products GROUP BY product_category_code

text_query: Find the number of students whose age is older than the average age for each gender.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  sex FROM student WHERE age  >  (SELECT avg(age) FROM student) GROUP BY sex

text_query: What are the names of the drama workshop groups with address in Feliciaberg city?
sql_command: SELECT T2.Store_Name FROM Addresses AS T1 JOIN Drama_Workshop_Groups AS T2 ON T1.Address_ID  =  T2.Address_ID WHERE T1.City_Town  =  "Feliciaberg"

text_query: What are all the policy types of the customer that has the most policies listed?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT t3.policy_type_code FROM customers AS t1 JOIN customers_policies AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id JOIN available_policies AS t3 ON t2.policy_id  =  t3.policy_id WHERE t1.customer_name  =  (SELECT t1.customer_name FROM customers AS t1 JOIN customers_policies AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id GROUP BY t1.customer_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1)

text_query: How many cards does customer Art Turcotte have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Customers_cards AS T1 JOIN Customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE T2.customer_first_name  =  "Art" AND T2.customer_last_name  =  "Turcotte"

text_query: What is the number of distinct teams that suffer elimination?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT (DISTINCT team) FROM elimination

text_query: Among the cars with more than lowest horsepower, which ones do not have more than 3 cylinders? List the car makeid and make name.
sql_command: SELECT T2.MakeId ,  T2.Make FROM CARS_DATA AS T1 JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.MakeId WHERE T1.Horsepower  >  (SELECT min(Horsepower) FROM CARS_DATA) AND T1.Cylinders  <=  3;

text_query: Find the names of stores whose number products is more than the average number of products.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM shop WHERE number_products  >  (SELECT avg(number_products) FROM shop)

text_query: Find all information about student addresses, and sort by monthly rental in descending order.
sql_command: SELECT * FROM Student_Addresses ORDER BY monthly_rental DESC

text_query: Show the stadium names without any concert.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM stadium WHERE stadium_id NOT IN (SELECT stadium_id FROM concert)

text_query: How many languages are in these films?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT language_id) FROM film

text_query: Find the names of stadiums that some Australian swimmers have been to.
sql_command: SELECT t4.name FROM swimmer AS t1 JOIN record AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.swimmer_id JOIN event AS t3 ON t2.event_id  =  t3.id JOIN stadium AS t4 ON t4.id  =  t3.stadium_id WHERE t1.nationality  =  'Australia'

text_query: List the names and emails of customers who payed by Visa card.
sql_command: SELECT customer_email ,  customer_name FROM customers WHERE payment_method  =  'Visa'

text_query: Find the names of all distinct wines that have appellations in North Coast area.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T2.Name FROM APPELLATIONs AS T1 JOIN WINE AS T2 ON T1.Appelation  =  T2.Appelation WHERE T1.Area  =  "North Coast"

text_query: List the names of countries whose language is not "German".
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM country WHERE Languages != "German"

text_query: Return all the information for all employees without any department number.
sql_command: SELECT * FROM employees WHERE department_id  =  "null"

text_query: What is the customer last name, id and phone number with most number of orders?
sql_command: SELECT T2.customer_last_name ,  T1.customer_id ,  T2.phone_number FROM Orders AS T1 JOIN Customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id GROUP BY T1.customer_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show all document ids and the number of paragraphs in each document. Order by document id.
sql_command: SELECT document_id ,  count(*) FROM Paragraphs GROUP BY document_id ORDER BY document_id

text_query: Find the max, average and min training hours of all players.
sql_command: SELECT avg(HS) ,  max(HS) ,  min(HS) FROM Player

text_query: Show the name and location of track with 1 race.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name ,  T2.location FROM race AS T1 JOIN track AS T2 ON T1.track_id  =  T2.track_id GROUP BY T1.track_id HAVING count(*)  =  1

text_query: What document types do have more than 10000 total access number.
sql_command: SELECT document_type_code FROM documents GROUP BY document_type_code HAVING sum(access_count)  >  10000

text_query: Find the total revenue for each manufacturer.
sql_command: SELECT sum(revenue) ,  name FROM manufacturers GROUP BY name

text_query: Show the distinct fate of missions that involve ships with nationality "United States"
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Fate FROM mission AS T1 JOIN ship AS T2 ON T1.Ship_ID  =  T2.Ship_ID WHERE T2.Nationality  =  "United States"

text_query: Which cmi cross reference id is not related to any parking taxes?
sql_command: SELECT cmi_cross_ref_id FROM cmi_cross_references EXCEPT SELECT cmi_cross_ref_id FROM parking_fines

text_query: Find the name of the project for which a scientist whose name contains ‘Smith’ is assigned to.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM assignedto AS T1 JOIN projects AS T2 ON T1.project  =  T2.code JOIN scientists AS T3 ON T1.scientist  =  T3.SSN WHERE T3.name LIKE '%Smith%'

text_query: Show the starting years shared by technicians from team "CLE" and "CWS".
sql_command: SELECT Starting_Year FROM technician WHERE Team  =  "CLE" INTERSECT SELECT Starting_Year FROM technician WHERE Team  =  "CWS"

text_query: display the first and last name, department, city, and state province for each employee.
sql_command: SELECT T1.first_name ,  T1.last_name ,  T2.department_name ,  T3.city ,  T3.state_province FROM employees AS T1 JOIN departments AS T2 ON T1.department_id  =  T2.department_id JOIN locations AS T3 ON T2.location_id  =  T3.location_id

text_query: Find all the distinct district names ordered by city area in descending.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT District_name FROM district ORDER BY city_area DESC

text_query: What are the gender and occupation of players?
sql_command: SELECT Gender ,  Occupation FROM player

text_query: What is the document status description of the document with id 1?
sql_command: SELECT Ref_Document_Status.document_status_description FROM Ref_Document_Status JOIN Documents ON Documents.document_status_code = Ref_Document_Status.document_status_code WHERE Documents.document_id = 1;

text_query: What are the maximum price and score of wines in each year?
sql_command: SELECT max(Price) ,  max(Score) ,  YEAR FROM WINE GROUP BY YEAR

text_query: Find the state, account type, and credit score of the customer whose number of loan is 0.
sql_command: SELECT state ,  acc_type ,  credit_score FROM customer WHERE no_of_loans  =  0

text_query: Find the name and checking balance of the account with the lowest savings balance.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  T2.balance FROM accounts AS T1 JOIN checking AS T2 ON T1.custid  =  T2.custid JOIN savings AS T3 ON T1.custid  =  T3.custid ORDER BY T3.balance LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the most frequent status of bookings?
sql_command: SELECT Status_Code FROM BOOKINGS GROUP BY Status_Code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List names of all pilot aged 30 or younger in descending alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM pilot WHERE Age  <=  30 ORDER BY Name DESC

text_query: Find the first name of students in the descending order of age.
sql_command: SELECT Fname FROM STUDENT ORDER BY Age DESC

text_query: what are all the addresses including line 1 and line 2?
sql_command: SELECT line_1 ,  line_2 FROM addresses

text_query: Among those engineers who have visited, which engineer makes the least number of visits? List the engineer id, first name and last name.
sql_command: SELECT T1.engineer_id ,  T1.first_name ,  T1.last_name FROM Maintenance_Engineers AS T1 JOIN Engineer_Visits AS T2 ON T1.engineer_id  =  T2.engineer_id GROUP BY T1.engineer_id ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: Return the dates of ceremony and the results of all music festivals
sql_command: SELECT Date_of_ceremony ,  RESULT FROM music_festival

text_query: What are the names of body builders?
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name FROM body_builder AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID

text_query: How many museums were opened after 2013 or before 2008?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM museum WHERE open_year  >  2013 OR open_year  <  2008

text_query: Show the investors shared by entrepreneurs that requested more than 140000 and entrepreneurs that requested less than 120000.
sql_command: SELECT Investor FROM entrepreneur WHERE Money_Requested  >  140000 INTERSECT SELECT Investor FROM entrepreneur WHERE Money_Requested  <  120000

text_query: What is the name of the wrestler with the fewest days held?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM wrestler ORDER BY Days_held ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: How long is the total lesson time taught by staff with first name as Janessa and last name as Sawayn?
sql_command: SELECT sum(lesson_time) FROM Lessons AS T1 JOIN Staff AS T2 ON T1.staff_id = T2.staff_id WHERE T2.first_name = "Janessa" AND T2.last_name = "Sawayn";

text_query: Show the ids of all the faculty members who participate in an activity and advise a student.
sql_command: SELECT FacID FROM Faculty_participates_in INTERSECT SELECT advisor FROM Student

text_query: What are the maximum and minimum number of transit passengers of all aiports.
sql_command: SELECT max(Transit_Passengers) ,  min(Transit_Passengers) FROM airport

text_query: Please give me a list of cities whose regional population is over 8000000 or under 5000000.
sql_command: SELECT city FROM city WHERE regional_population  >  10000000 UNION SELECT city FROM city WHERE regional_population  <  5000000

text_query: Show the host names for parties with number of hosts greater than 20.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name FROM party_host AS T1 JOIN HOST AS T2 ON T1.Host_ID  =  T2.Host_ID JOIN party AS T3 ON T1.Party_ID  =  T3.Party_ID WHERE T3.Number_of_hosts  >  20

text_query: How many employees are living in Canada?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM employees WHERE country = "Canada";

text_query: Find the total saving balance for each account name.
sql_command: SELECT sum(T2.balance) ,  T1.name FROM accounts AS T1 JOIN savings AS T2 ON T1.custid  =  T2.custid GROUP BY T1.name

text_query: What's the name of the course with most number of enrollments?
sql_command: SELECT  T1.course_name FROM Courses AS T1 JOIN Student_Enrolment_Courses AS T2 ON T1.course_id  =  T2.course_id GROUP BY T1.course_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Which committees have delegates from both democratic party and liberal party?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Committee FROM election AS T1 JOIN party AS T2 ON T1.Party  =  T2.Party_ID WHERE T2.Party  =  "Democratic" INTERSECT SELECT T1.Committee FROM election AS T1 JOIN party AS T2 ON T1.Party  =  T2.Party_ID WHERE T2.Party  =  "Liberal"

text_query: What is the id of the project with least number of documents?
sql_command: SELECT project_id FROM Documents GROUP BY project_id ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show me the departure date and arrival date for all flights from Los Angeles to Honolulu.
sql_command: SELECT departure_date ,  arrival_date FROM Flight WHERE origin  =  "Los Angeles" AND destination  =  "Honolulu"

text_query: What is the name of the product with the highest price?
sql_command: SELECT Product_Name FROM Products ORDER BY Product_Price DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the locations of schools that have more than 1 player.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Location FROM player AS T1 JOIN school AS T2 ON T1.School_ID  =  T2.School_ID GROUP BY T1.School_ID HAVING COUNT(*)  >  1

text_query: How many film are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM film

text_query: Show names of technicians in ascending order of quality rank of the machine they are assigned.
sql_command: SELECT T3.Name FROM repair_assignment AS T1 JOIN machine AS T2 ON T1.machine_id  =  T2.machine_id JOIN technician AS T3 ON T1.technician_ID  =  T3.technician_ID ORDER BY T2.quality_rank

text_query: Find the department name that is in Building "Mergenthaler".
sql_command: SELECT DName FROM DEPARTMENT WHERE Building  =  "Mergenthaler"

text_query: Show all church names except for those that had a wedding in year 2015.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM church EXCEPT SELECT T1.name FROM church AS T1 JOIN wedding AS T2 ON T1.church_id  =  T2.church_id WHERE T2.year  =  2015

text_query: List the dates of enrollment and completion of the student with family name "Zieme" and personal name "Bernie".
sql_command: SELECT T1.date_of_enrolment ,  T1.date_of_completion FROM Student_Course_Enrolment AS T1 JOIN Students AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.student_id WHERE T2.family_name  =  "Zieme" AND T2.personal_name  =  "Bernie"

text_query: Show headquarters with at least two companies in the banking industry.
sql_command: SELECT headquarters FROM company WHERE main_industry  =  'Banking' GROUP BY headquarters HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: List all characteristics of product named "sesame" with type code "Grade".
sql_command: SELECT t3.characteristic_name FROM products AS t1 JOIN product_characteristics AS t2 ON t1.product_id  =  t2.product_id JOIN CHARACTERISTICS AS t3 ON t2.characteristic_id  =  t3.characteristic_id WHERE t1.product_name  =  "sesame" AND t3.characteristic_type_code  =  "Grade"

text_query: What are the dates and locations of performances?
sql_command: SELECT Date ,  LOCATION FROM performance

text_query: List the names and the locations that the enzymes can make an effect.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  LOCATION FROM enzyme

text_query: Which major has the most students?
sql_command: SELECT Major FROM STUDENT GROUP BY major ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the official names of cities that have not held any competition.
sql_command: SELECT Official_Name FROM city WHERE City_ID NOT IN (SELECT Host_city_ID FROM farm_competition)

text_query: Show the number of documents with document type code CV or BK.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM All_documents WHERE document_type_code  =  "CV" OR document_type_code  =  "BK"

text_query: What are the names of the directors who made exactly one movie?
sql_command: SELECT director FROM Movie GROUP BY director HAVING count(*)  =  1

text_query: Find the product type whose average price is higher than the average price of all products.
sql_command: SELECT product_type_code FROM products GROUP BY product_type_code HAVING avg(product_price)  >  (SELECT avg(product_price) FROM products)

text_query: Find the ids of orders whose status is 'Success'.
sql_command: SELECT actual_order_id FROM actual_orders WHERE order_status_code  =  'Success'

text_query: What is the name of the course that has the most student enrollment?
sql_command: SELECT T1.course_name FROM Courses AS T1 JOIN Student_Course_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.course_id  =  T2.course_id GROUP BY T1.course_name ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the companies of entrepreneurs in descending order of money requested.
sql_command: SELECT Company FROM entrepreneur ORDER BY Money_Requested DESC

text_query: report the total number of degrees granted between 1998 and 2002.
sql_command: SELECT T1.campus ,  sum(T2.degrees) FROM campuses AS T1 JOIN degrees AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.campus WHERE T2.year  >=  1998 AND T2.year  <=  2002 GROUP BY T1.campus

text_query: What are the names of players who have the best dribbling?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.player_name FROM Player AS T1 JOIN Player_Attributes AS T2 ON T1.player_api_id = T2.player_api_id WHERE T2.dribbling  =  ( SELECT max(overall_rating) FROM Player_Attributes)

text_query: How many distinct kinds of injuries happened after season 2010?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT T1.injury) FROM injury_accident AS T1 JOIN game AS T2 ON T1.game_id  =  T2.id WHERE T2.season  >  2010

text_query: Find the name and account balance of the customers who have loans with a total amount of more than 5000.
sql_command: SELECT T1.cust_name ,  T1.acc_type FROM customer AS T1 JOIN loan AS T2 ON T1.cust_id  =  T2.cust_id GROUP BY T1.cust_name HAVING sum(T2.amount)  >  5000

text_query: Find the number of shops in each location.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  LOCATION FROM shop GROUP BY LOCATION

text_query: Show the names and main services for train stations that have the top three total number of passengers.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  main_services FROM station ORDER BY total_passengers DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: Show all paragraph ids and texts for the document with name 'Welcome to NY'.
sql_command: SELECT T1.paragraph_id ,   T1.paragraph_text FROM Paragraphs AS T1 JOIN Documents AS T2 ON T1.document_id  =  T2.document_id WHERE T2.Document_Name  =  'Welcome to NY'

text_query: What is the total amount of settlement made for all the settlements?
sql_command: SELECT sum(Amount_Settled) FROM Settlements

text_query: List the names of all courses ordered by their titles and credits.
sql_command: SELECT title FROM course ORDER BY title ,  credits

text_query: What are the names of poker players whose earnings is higher than 300000?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name FROM people AS T1 JOIN poker_player AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID WHERE T2.Earnings  >  300000

text_query: For each building, show the name of the building and the number of institutions in it.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  count(*) FROM building AS T1 JOIN institution AS T2 ON T1.building_id  =  T2.building_id GROUP BY T1.building_id

text_query: Find the name of route that has the highest number of deliveries.
sql_command: SELECT t1.route_name FROM Delivery_Routes AS t1 JOIN Delivery_Route_Locations AS t2 ON t1.route_id  =  t2.route_id GROUP BY t1.route_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the nationality of the journalist with the largest number of years working?
sql_command: SELECT Nationality FROM journalist ORDER BY Years_working DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show names, results and bulgarian commanders of the battles with no ships lost in the 'English Channel'.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  RESULT ,  bulgarian_commander FROM battle EXCEPT SELECT T1.name ,  T1.result ,  T1.bulgarian_commander FROM battle AS T1 JOIN ship AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.lost_in_battle WHERE T2.location  =  'English Channel'

text_query: Find the total budgets of the Marketing or Finance department.
sql_command: SELECT sum(budget) FROM department WHERE dept_name  =  'Marketing' OR dept_name  =  'Finance'

text_query: Show different tourist attractions' names, ids, and the corresponding number of visits.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name ,  T2.Tourist_Attraction_ID ,   COUNT(*) FROM Tourist_Attractions AS T1 JOIN VISITS AS T2 ON T1.Tourist_Attraction_ID  =  T2.Tourist_Attraction_ID GROUP BY T2.Tourist_Attraction_ID

text_query: List the school color of the school that has the largest enrollment.
sql_command: SELECT School_Colors FROM school ORDER BY Enrollment DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the last transcript release date?
sql_command: SELECT transcript_date FROM Transcripts ORDER BY transcript_date DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the average rating star for each movie that received at least 2 ratings.
sql_command: SELECT mID ,  avg(stars) FROM Rating GROUP BY mID HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: What is the average price for flights from Los Angeles to Honolulu.
sql_command: SELECT avg(price) FROM Flight WHERE origin  =  "Los Angeles" AND destination  =  "Honolulu"

text_query: What is the party of the youngest people?
sql_command: SELECT Party FROM people ORDER BY Age ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the distinct reigns of wrestlers whose location is not "Tokyo,Japan" ?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT Reign FROM wrestler WHERE LOCATION != "Tokyo , Japan"

text_query: What is the id of the longest song?
sql_command: SELECT f_id FROM files ORDER BY duration DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: show all train numbers and names ordered by their time from early to late.
sql_command: SELECT train_number ,  name FROM train ORDER BY TIME

text_query: Show the number of transaction types.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT transaction_type) FROM Financial_Transactions

text_query: Find the id of users who are followed by Mary and Susan.
sql_command: SELECT T2.f1 FROM user_profiles AS T1 JOIN follows AS T2 ON T1.uid  =  T2.f2 WHERE T1.name  =  "Mary" INTERSECT SELECT T2.f1 FROM user_profiles AS T1 JOIN follows AS T2 ON T1.uid  =  T2.f2 WHERE T1.name  =  "Susan"

text_query: Find the name of persons who are friends with Bob.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM Person AS T1 JOIN PersonFriend AS T2 ON T1.name  =  T2.name WHERE T2.friend  =  'Bob'

text_query: List document type codes and the number of documents in each code.
sql_command: SELECT document_type_code ,  count(*) FROM Documents GROUP BY document_type_code

text_query: Find the number of distinct amenities.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM dorm_amenity

text_query: Find the name of the company that produces both furnitures with less than 6 components and furnitures with more than 10 components.
sql_command: SELECT t3.name FROM furniture AS t1 JOIN furniture_manufacte AS t2 ON t1.Furniture_ID  =  t2.Furniture_ID JOIN manufacturer AS t3 ON t2.manufacturer_id  =  t3.manufacturer_id WHERE t1.num_of_component  <  6 INTERSECT SELECT t3.name FROM furniture AS t1 JOIN furniture_manufacte AS t2 ON t1.Furniture_ID  =  t2.Furniture_ID JOIN manufacturer AS t3 ON t2.manufacturer_id  =  t3.manufacturer_id WHERE t1.num_of_component  >  10

text_query: How many players have more than 1000 hours of training?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Player WHERE HS  >  1000

text_query: Return reviewer name, movie title, stars, and ratingDate. And sort the data first by reviewer name, then by movie title, and lastly by number of stars.
sql_command: SELECT T3.name ,  T2.title ,  T1.stars ,  T1.ratingDate FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID JOIN Reviewer AS T3 ON T1.rID  =  T3.rID ORDER BY T3.name ,  T2.title ,  T1.stars

text_query: How many department stores does the store chain South have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM department_stores AS T1 JOIN department_store_chain AS T2 ON T1.dept_store_chain_id  =  T2.dept_store_chain_id WHERE T2.dept_store_chain_name  =  "South"

text_query: List all the event names by year from the most recent to the oldest.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM event ORDER BY YEAR DESC

text_query: Find the names of all stores in Khanewal District.
sql_command: SELECT t1.store_name FROM store AS t1 JOIN store_district AS t2 ON t1.store_id  =  t2.store_id JOIN district AS t3 ON t2.district_id  =  t3.district_id WHERE t3.district_name  =  "Khanewal District"

text_query: How many degrees does the engineering department offer?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Departments AS T1 JOIN Degree_Programs AS T2 ON T1.department_id  =  T2.department_id WHERE T1.department_name  =  'engineer'

text_query: Find the titles of all movies directed by steven spielberg.
sql_command: SELECT title FROM Movie WHERE director = 'Steven Spielberg'

text_query: Find the name of the train whose route runs through greatest number of stations.
sql_command: SELECT t1.name FROM train AS t1 JOIN route AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.train_id GROUP BY t2.train_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: For each customer who has at least two orders, find the customer name and number of orders made.
sql_command: SELECT T2.customer_name ,  count(*) FROM orders AS T1 JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id GROUP BY T2.customer_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: What instrument did the musician with last name "Heilo" use in the song "Badlands"?
sql_command: SELECT T4.instrument FROM Performance AS T1 JOIN Band AS T2 ON T1.bandmate  =  T2.id JOIN Songs AS T3 ON T3.SongId  =  T1.SongId JOIN Instruments AS T4 ON T4.songid  =  T3.songid AND T4.bandmateid  =  T2.id WHERE T2.lastname  =  "Heilo" AND T3.title  =  "Badlands"

text_query: What are the dates of the assessment notes?
sql_command: SELECT date_of_notes FROM Assessment_Notes

text_query: Which district has both stores with less than 3000 products and stores with more than 10000 products?
sql_command: SELECT district FROM shop WHERE Number_products  <  3000 INTERSECT SELECT district FROM shop WHERE Number_products  >  10000

text_query: What parties have at least three representatives?
sql_command: SELECT Party FROM representative GROUP BY Party HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  3

text_query: What is the campus fee of "San Francisco State University" in year 2000?
sql_command: SELECT t1.campusfee FROM csu_fees AS t1 JOIN campuses AS t2 ON t1.campus  =  t2.id WHERE t2.campus  =  "San Francisco State University" AND t1.year  =  2000

text_query: Find the first name, country code and birth date of the winner who has the highest rank points in all matches.
sql_command: SELECT T1.first_name ,  T1.country_code ,  T1.birth_date FROM players AS T1 JOIN matches AS T2 ON T1.player_id  =  T2.winner_id ORDER BY T2.winner_rank_points DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name of the customers who have at most two orders.
sql_command: SELECT T2.customer_name FROM orders AS T1 JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id GROUP BY T2.customer_id HAVING count(*)  <=  2

text_query: List all singer names in concerts in year 2014.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM singer_in_concert AS T1 JOIN singer AS T2 ON T1.singer_id  =  T2.singer_id JOIN concert AS T3 ON T1.concert_id  =  T3.concert_id WHERE T3.year  =  2014

text_query: What is the type of video game Call of Destiny.
sql_command: SELECT gtype FROM Video_games WHERE gname  =  "Call of Destiny"

text_query: How many students attend course English?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM courses AS T1 JOIN student_course_attendance AS T2 ON T1.course_id = T2.course_id WHERE T1.course_name = "English"

text_query: How many phone hardware models are produced by the company named "Nokia Corporation"?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM phone WHERE Company_name = "Nokia Corporation";

text_query: List the industry shared by the most companies.
sql_command: SELECT Industry FROM Companies GROUP BY Industry ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many lessons were in cancelled state?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Lessons WHERE lesson_status_code = "Cancelled";

text_query: Find the last name of the individuals that have been contact individuals of an organization.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT t1.individual_last_name FROM individuals AS t1 JOIN organization_contact_individuals AS t2 ON t1.individual_id  =  t2.individual_id

text_query: Show the names of students who have at least 2 likes.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM Likes AS T1 JOIN Highschooler AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.id GROUP BY T1.student_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: Find the number of students for the cities where have more than one student.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  city_code FROM student GROUP BY city_code HAVING count(*)  >  1

text_query: What are the notes of the death events which has substring 'East'?
sql_command: SELECT note FROM death WHERE note LIKE '%East%'

text_query: What is the average and minimum age of all artists from United States.
sql_command: SELECT avg(age) ,  min(age) FROM artist WHERE country  =  'United States'

text_query: List all the scientists' names, their projects' names, and the hours worked by that scientist on each project, in alphabetical order of project name, and then scientist name.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name ,  T3.Name ,  T3.Hours FROM Scientists AS T1 JOIN AssignedTo AS T2 ON T1.SSN = T2.Scientist JOIN Projects AS T3 ON T2.Project = T3.Code ORDER BY T3.Name ,  T1.Name

text_query: What is the salary and name of the employee who has the most number of certificates on aircrafts with distance more than 5000?
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM Employee AS T1 JOIN Certificate AS T2 ON T1.eid  =  T2.eid JOIN Aircraft AS T3 ON T3.aid  =  T2.aid WHERE T3.distance  >  5000 GROUP BY T1.eid ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the name of cities in the county that has the largest number of police officers.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM city WHERE county_ID  =  (SELECT county_ID FROM county_public_safety ORDER BY Police_officers DESC LIMIT 1)

text_query: Which professionals live in a city containing the substring 'West'? List his or her role, street, city and state.
sql_command: SELECT role_code ,  street ,  city ,  state FROM professionals WHERE city LIKE '%West%'

text_query: Show the names of high schoolers who have at least 3 friends.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM Friend AS T1 JOIN Highschooler AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.id GROUP BY T1.student_id HAVING count(*)  >=  3

text_query: How many types of products have Rodrick Heaney bought in total?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT t3.product_id) FROM customers AS t1 JOIN customer_orders AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id JOIN order_items AS t3 ON t2.order_id  =  t3.order_id WHERE t1.customer_name  =  "Rodrick Heaney"

text_query: Find the names of rooms that have been reserved for more than 60 times.
sql_command: SELECT T2.roomName FROM Reservations AS T1 JOIN Rooms AS T2 ON T1.Room  =  T2.RoomId GROUP BY T1.Room HAVING count(*)  >  60

text_query: display all the information of the employees whose salary if within the range of smallest salary and 2500.
sql_command: SELECT * FROM employees WHERE salary BETWEEN (SELECT MIN(salary) FROM employees) AND 2500

text_query: List the names of all distinct races in reversed  lexicographic order?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT name FROM races ORDER BY name DESC

text_query: Show the name and prominence of the mountains whose picture is not taken by a lens of brand 'Sigma'.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  prominence FROM mountain EXCEPT SELECT T1.name ,  T1.prominence FROM mountain AS T1 JOIN photos AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.mountain_id JOIN camera_lens AS T3 ON T2.camera_lens_id  =  T3.id WHERE T3.brand  =  'Sigma'

text_query: How many customers does Steve Johnson support?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM employees AS T1 JOIN customers AS T2 ON T2.support_rep_id = T1.id WHERE T1.first_name = "Steve" AND T1.last_name = "Johnson";

text_query: List the names of conductors in ascending order of age.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM conductor ORDER BY Age ASC

text_query: How many unique languages are spoken in the world?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT LANGUAGE) FROM countrylanguage

text_query: Which Asian countries have a population that is larger than any country in Africa?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM country WHERE Continent  =  "Asia"  AND population  >  (SELECT max(population) FROM country WHERE Continent  =  "Africa")

text_query: Find the number of rooms with more than 50 capacity for each building.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  building FROM classroom WHERE capacity  >  50 GROUP BY building

text_query: How many times at most can a course enrollment result show in different transcripts? Also show the course enrollment id.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  student_course_id FROM Transcript_Contents GROUP BY student_course_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the average and maximum age for each type of pet.
sql_command: SELECT avg(pet_age) ,  max(pet_age) ,  pettype FROM pets GROUP BY pettype

text_query: Which university is in Los Angeles county and opened after 1950?
sql_command: SELECT campus FROM campuses WHERE county  =  "Los Angeles" AND YEAR  >  1950

text_query: How many papers are published by the institution "Tokohu University"?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT t1.title) FROM papers AS t1 JOIN authorship AS t2 ON t1.paperid  =  t2.paperid JOIN inst AS t3 ON t2.instid  =  t3.instid WHERE t3.name  =  "Tokohu University"

text_query: What is the average expected life expectancy for countries in the region of Central Africa?
sql_command: SELECT avg(LifeExpectancy) FROM country WHERE Region  =  "Central Africa"

text_query: What are the phone and email for customer Harold?
sql_command: SELECT Customer_Phone ,  Customer_Email_Address FROM CUSTOMERS WHERE Customer_Name  =  "Harold"

text_query: How many patients do each physician take care of? List their names and number of patients they take care of.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  count(*) FROM physician AS T1 JOIN patient AS T2 ON T1.employeeid  =  T2.PCP GROUP BY T1.employeeid

text_query: List all club names in descending alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM club ORDER BY name DESC

text_query: What is the maximum point for climbers whose country is United Kingdom?
sql_command: SELECT max(Points) FROM climber WHERE Country  =  "United Kingdom"

text_query: what are the average and maximum attendances of all events?
sql_command: SELECT avg(Event_Attendance) ,  max(Event_Attendance) FROM event

text_query: Show the authors of submissions and the acceptance results of their submissions.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Author ,  T1.Result FROM acceptance AS T1 JOIN submission AS T2 ON T1.Submission_ID  =  T2.Submission_ID

text_query: List the name of artworks whose type is not "Program Talent Show".
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM artwork WHERE TYPE != "Program Talent Show"

text_query: Find the codes of countries that have more than 50 players.
sql_command: SELECT country_code FROM players GROUP BY country_code HAVING count(*)  >  50

text_query: What is the address of employee Nancy Edwards?
sql_command: SELECT address FROM employees WHERE first_name = "Nancy" AND last_name = "Edwards";

text_query: How many different nationalities do conductors have?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT Nationality) FROM conductor

text_query: What is the interaction type of the enzyme named 'ALA synthase' and the medicine named 'Aripiprazole'?
sql_command: SELECT T1.interaction_type FROM medicine_enzyme_interaction AS T1 JOIN medicine AS T2 ON T1.medicine_id  =  T2.id JOIN enzyme AS T3 ON T1.enzyme_id  =  T3.id WHERE T3.name  =  'ALA synthase' AND T2.name  =  'Aripiprazole'

text_query: Show the number of customers for each gender.
sql_command: SELECT gender ,  count(*) FROM Customers GROUP BY gender

text_query: Find the name of accounts whose checking balance is higher than corresponding saving balance.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM accounts AS T1 JOIN checking AS T2 ON T1.custid  =  T2.custid JOIN savings AS T3 ON T1.custid  =  T3.custid WHERE T2.balance  >  T3.balance

text_query: Find the ids and names of stations from which at least 200 trips started.
sql_command: SELECT start_station_id ,  start_station_name FROM trip GROUP BY start_station_name HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  200

text_query: Find the distinct majors of students who have treasurer votes.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Major FROM STUDENT AS T1 JOIN VOTING_RECORD AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  T2.Treasurer_Vote

text_query: What are the country code and first name of the players who won in both tourney WTA Championships and Australian Open?
sql_command: SELECT T1.country_code ,  T1.first_name FROM players AS T1 JOIN matches AS T2 ON T1.player_id  =  T2.winner_id WHERE T2.tourney_name  =  'WTA Championships' INTERSECT SELECT T1.country_code ,  T1.first_name FROM players AS T1 JOIN matches AS T2 ON T1.player_id  =  T2.winner_id WHERE T2.tourney_name  =  'Australian Open'

text_query: How many addresses are there in country USA?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM addresses WHERE country  =  'USA'

text_query: Find the title and star rating of the movie that got the least rating star for each reviewer.
sql_command: SELECT T2.title ,  T1.rID ,  T1.stars ,  min(T1.stars) FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID GROUP BY T1.rID

text_query: What is the role name and role description for employee called Ebba?
sql_command: SELECT T2.role_name ,  T2.role_description FROM Employees AS T1 JOIN ROLES AS T2 ON T1.role_code  =  T2.role_code WHERE T1.employee_name  =  "Ebba"

text_query: What is the code of airport that has the highest number of flights?
sql_command: SELECT T1.AirportCode FROM AIRPORTS AS T1 JOIN FLIGHTS AS T2 ON T1.AirportCode  =  T2.DestAirport OR T1.AirportCode  =  T2.SourceAirport GROUP BY T1.AirportCode ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the average checking balance.
sql_command: SELECT avg(balance) FROM checking

text_query: Show the name and population of the country that has the highest roller coaster.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name ,  T1.population FROM country AS T1 JOIN roller_coaster AS T2 ON T1.Country_ID  =  T2.Country_ID ORDER BY T2.Height DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the average hours for the students whose tryout decision is no.
sql_command: SELECT avg(T1.HS) FROM player AS T1 JOIN tryout AS T2 ON T1.pID  =  T2.pID WHERE T2.decision  =  'no'

text_query: List all information about courses sorted by credits in the ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT * FROM COURSE ORDER BY Credits

text_query: How many persons are not body builders?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM people WHERE people_id NOT IN (SELECT People_ID FROM body_builder)

text_query: Find all the phone numbers.
sql_command: SELECT customer_phone FROM available_policies

text_query: What are the phone numbers of all customers and suppliers.
sql_command: SELECT customer_phone FROM customers UNION SELECT supplier_phone FROM suppliers

text_query: Find the name of tracks which are in Movies playlist but not in music playlist.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM tracks AS T1 JOIN playlist_tracks AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.track_id JOIN playlists AS T3 ON T2.playlist_id  =  T3.id WHERE T3.name  =  'Movies' EXCEPT SELECT T1.name FROM tracks AS T1 JOIN playlist_tracks AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.track_id JOIN playlists AS T3 ON T2.playlist_id  =  T3.id WHERE T3.name  =  'Music'

text_query: Find the driver id and number of races of all drivers who have at most participated in 30 races?
sql_command: SELECT T1.driverid ,  count(*) FROM drivers AS T1 JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.driverid = T2.driverid JOIN races AS T3 ON T2.raceid = T3.raceid GROUP BY T1.driverid HAVING count(*)  <=  30

text_query: Which countries do not have a stadium that was opened after 2006?
sql_command: SELECT country FROM stadium EXCEPT SELECT country FROM stadium WHERE opening_year  >  2006

text_query: Find the total number of employees.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM employee

text_query: What is the description of the color used by least products?
sql_command: SELECT t2.color_description FROM products AS t1 JOIN ref_colors AS t2 ON t1.color_code  =  t2.color_code GROUP BY t2.color_description ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name of services that have been used for more than 2 times in first notification of loss.
sql_command: SELECT t2.service_name FROM first_notification_of_loss AS t1 JOIN services AS t2 ON t1.service_id  =  t2.service_id GROUP BY t1.service_id HAVING count(*)  >  2

text_query: Find the names of items whose rank is higher than 3 and whose average rating is above 5.
sql_command: SELECT T1.title FROM item AS T1 JOIN review AS T2 ON T1.i_id  =  T2.i_id WHERE T2.rank  >  3 INTERSECT SELECT T1.title FROM item AS T1 JOIN review AS T2 ON T1.i_id  =  T2.i_id GROUP BY T2.i_id HAVING avg(T2.rating)  >  5

text_query: List the name of browsers in descending order by market share.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM browser ORDER BY market_share DESC

text_query: Find the year which offers the largest number of courses.
sql_command: SELECT YEAR FROM SECTION GROUP BY YEAR ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the code of airport that has fewest number of flights?
sql_command: SELECT T1.AirportCode FROM AIRPORTS AS T1 JOIN FLIGHTS AS T2 ON T1.AirportCode  =  T2.DestAirport OR T1.AirportCode  =  T2.SourceAirport GROUP BY T1.AirportCode ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

text_query: display the department name, city, and state province for each department.
sql_command: SELECT T1.department_name ,  T2.city ,  T2.state_province FROM departments AS T1 JOIN locations AS T2 ON T2.location_id  =  T1.location_id

text_query: Find the address line 1 and 2 of the customer with email "vbogisich@example.org".
sql_command: SELECT address_line_1 ,  address_line_2 FROM customers WHERE email_address  =  "vbogisich@example.org"

text_query: What is the document id with 1 to 2 paragraphs?
sql_command: SELECT document_id FROM Paragraphs GROUP BY document_id HAVING count(*) BETWEEN 1 AND 2

text_query: List the names of members who did not participate in any round.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM member WHERE Member_ID NOT IN (SELECT Member_ID FROM round)

text_query: What are all the distinct premise types?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT premises_type FROM premises

text_query: How many distinct colleges are associated with players from the team with name "Columbus Crew".
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT T1.College) FROM match_season AS T1 JOIN team AS T2 ON T1.Team  =  T2.Team_id WHERE T2.Name  =  "Columbus Crew"

text_query: List the personal names and family names of all the students in alphabetical order of family name.
sql_command: SELECT personal_name ,  family_name FROM Students ORDER BY family_name

text_query: Show the different nationalities and the number of journalists of each nationality.
sql_command: SELECT Nationality ,  COUNT(*) FROM journalist GROUP BY Nationality

text_query: List the total points of gymnasts in descending order.
sql_command: SELECT Total_Points FROM gymnast ORDER BY Total_Points DESC

text_query: What is the name and id of the department with the most number of degrees ?
sql_command: select t2.department_name ,  t1.department_id from degree_programs as t1 join departments as t2 on t1.department_id  =  t2.department_id group by t1.department_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

text_query: What is the project detail for the project with document "King Book"?
sql_command: SELECT T1.project_details FROM Projects AS T1 JOIN Documents AS T2 ON T1.project_id  =  T2.project_id WHERE T2.document_name  =  "King Book"

text_query: Which vocal type has the band mate with last name "Heilo" played the most?
sql_command: SELECT TYPE FROM vocals AS T1 JOIN band AS T2 ON T1.bandmate  =  T2.id WHERE lastname  =  "Heilo" GROUP BY TYPE ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the number of departments in each school.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT dept_name) ,  school_code FROM department GROUP BY school_code

text_query: Show student ids who are on scholarship and have major 600.
sql_command: SELECT StuID FROM Student WHERE major  =  600 INTERSECT SELECT StuID FROM Sportsinfo WHERE onscholarship  =  'Y'

text_query: Find the zip code in which the average mean visibility is lower than 10.
sql_command: SELECT zip_code FROM weather GROUP BY zip_code HAVING avg(mean_visibility_miles)  <  10

text_query: What are the distinct ages of the heads who are acting?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.age FROM management AS T2 JOIN head AS T1 ON T1.head_id  =  T2.head_id WHERE T2.temporary_acting  =  'Yes'

text_query: Show the names of trains and locations of railways they are in.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name ,  T1.Location FROM railway AS T1 JOIN train AS T2 ON T1.Railway_ID  =  T2.Railway_ID

text_query: List all cities of addresses in alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT city FROM Addresses ORDER BY city

text_query: Find the name of rooms whose base price is between 120 and 150.
sql_command: SELECT roomname FROM rooms WHERE baseprice BETWEEN 120 AND 150

text_query: What are all role codes?
sql_command: SELECT role_code FROM ROLES;

text_query: List the name and number of followers for each user, and sort the results by the number of followers in descending order.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  followers FROM user_profiles ORDER BY followers DESC

text_query: Which store owns most items?
sql_command: SELECT store_id FROM inventory GROUP BY store_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many different roles are there in the club "Bootup Baltimore"?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT t2.position) FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid WHERE t1.clubname  =  "Bootup Baltimore"

text_query: What are the names of conductors whose nationalities are not "USA"?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM conductor WHERE Nationality != 'USA'

text_query: Find the rank of the faculty that the fewest faculties belong to.
sql_command: SELECT Rank FROM FACULTY GROUP BY Rank ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the names and grades of each high schooler.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  grade FROM Highschooler

text_query: Who were the governors of the parties associated with delegates from district 1?
sql_command: SELECT T2.Governor FROM election AS T1 JOIN party AS T2 ON T1.Party  =  T2.Party_ID WHERE T1.District  =  1

text_query: Show all the distinct districts for elections.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT District FROM election

text_query: How many architects are female?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM architect WHERE gender  =  'female'

text_query: What is the name and salary for employee with id 242518965?
sql_command: SELECT name ,  salary FROM Employee WHERE eid  =  242518965

text_query: Show the locations that have more than one railways.
sql_command: SELECT LOCATION FROM railway GROUP BY LOCATION HAVING COUNT(*)  >  1

text_query: Find the number of classes in each school.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  T3.school_code FROM CLASS AS T1 JOIN course AS T2 ON T1.crs_code  =  T2.crs_code JOIN department AS T3 ON T2.dept_code  =  T3.dept_code GROUP BY T3.school_code

text_query: Among all the claims, which settlements have a claimed amount that is no more than the average? List the claim start date.
sql_command: SELECT Date_Claim_Made FROM Claims WHERE Amount_Settled  <=  ( SELECT avg(Amount_Settled) FROM Claims )

text_query: How many artists are from Bangladesh?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM artist WHERE country  =  "Bangladesh"

text_query: What is the average number of rooms of apartments with type code "Studio"?
sql_command: SELECT avg(room_count) FROM Apartments WHERE apt_type_code  =  "Studio"

text_query: What are the ids and names of the battles that led to more than 10 people killed in total.
sql_command: SELECT T1.id ,  T1.name FROM battle AS T1 JOIN ship AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.lost_in_battle JOIN death AS T3 ON T2.id  =  T3.caused_by_ship_id GROUP BY T1.id HAVING sum(T3.killed)  >  10

text_query: List the hardware model name and company name for all the phones that were launched in year 2002 or have RAM size greater than 32.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Hardware_Model_name ,  T2.Company_name FROM chip_model AS T1 JOIN phone AS T2 ON T1.Model_name  =  T2.chip_model WHERE T1.Launch_year = 2002 OR T1.RAM_MiB  >  32;

text_query: Find the name and hours of the students whose tryout decision is yes.
sql_command: SELECT T1.pName ,  T1.HS FROM player AS T1 JOIN tryout AS T2 ON T1.pID  =  T2.pID WHERE T2.decision  =  'yes'

text_query: Show all document names using templates with template type code BK.
sql_command: SELECT T2.document_name FROM Templates AS T1 JOIN Documents AS T2 ON T1.template_id  =  T2.template_id WHERE T1.template_type_code  =  "BK"

text_query: What are the dates for the documents with both 'GV' type and 'SF' type expenses?
sql_command: SELECT T1.document_date FROM Documents AS T1 JOIN Documents_with_Expenses AS T2 ON T1.document_id  =  T2.document_id WHERE T2.budget_type_code  =  'GV' INTERSECT SELECT T1.document_date FROM Documents AS T1 JOIN Documents_with_Expenses AS T2 ON T1.document_id  =  T2.document_id WHERE T2.budget_type_code  =  'SF'

text_query: List the names of wrestlers in descending order of days held.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM wrestler ORDER BY Days_held DESC

text_query: Show all game names played by Linda Smith
sql_command: SELECT Gname FROM Plays_games AS T1 JOIN Video_games AS T2 ON T1.gameid  =  T2.gameid JOIN Student AS T3 ON T3.Stuid  =  T1.Stuid WHERE T3.Lname  =  "Smith" AND T3.Fname  =  "Linda"

text_query: What is the first and last name of the professor in biology department?
sql_command: SELECT T3.EMP_FNAME ,  T3.EMP_LNAME FROM professor AS T1 JOIN department AS T2 ON T1.dept_code  =  T2.dept_code JOIN employee AS T3 ON T1.EMP_NUM  =  T3.EMP_NUM WHERE DEPT_NAME  =  "Biology"

text_query: find the number of players whose points are lower than 30 in each position.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  POSITION FROM player WHERE points  <  30 GROUP BY POSITION

text_query: Find the name and id of accounts whose checking balance is below the maximum checking balance.
sql_command: SELECT T1.custid ,  T1.name FROM accounts AS T1 JOIN checking AS T2 ON T1.custid  =  T2.custid WHERE T2.balance  <  (SELECT max(balance) FROM checking)

text_query: Return the number of routes with destination airport in Italy operated by the airline with name 'American Airlines'.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM routes AS T1 JOIN airports AS T2 ON T1.dst_apid  =  T2.apid JOIN airlines AS T3 ON T1.alid  =  T3.alid WHERE T2.country  =  'Italy' AND T3.name  =  'American Airlines'

text_query: Find the average and total capacity of dorms for the students with gender X.
sql_command: SELECT avg(student_capacity) ,  sum(student_capacity) FROM dorm WHERE gender  =  'X'

text_query: Find the types and details for all premises and order by the premise type.
sql_command: SELECT premises_type ,  premise_details FROM premises ORDER BY premises_type

text_query: What is the name of the product with the color description 'yellow'?
sql_command: SELECT T1.product_name FROM products AS T1 JOIN ref_colors AS T2 ON T1.color_code  =  T2.color_code WHERE T2.color_description  =  'yellow'

text_query: How many clubs are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM club

text_query: What are the country codes for countries that do not speak English?
sql_command: SELECT CountryCode FROM countrylanguage EXCEPT SELECT CountryCode FROM countrylanguage WHERE LANGUAGE  =  "English"

text_query: Wat is the tax source system code and master customer id of the taxes related to each parking fine id?
sql_command: SELECT T1.source_system_code ,  T1.master_customer_id ,  T2.council_tax_id FROM CMI_Cross_References AS T1 JOIN Parking_Fines AS T2 ON T1.cmi_cross_ref_id  =  T2.cmi_cross_ref_id

text_query: List the names of climbers in descending order of points.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM climber ORDER BY Points DESC

text_query: List the hardware model name for the phones that have screen mode type "Text" or RAM size greater than 32.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Hardware_Model_name FROM chip_model AS T1 JOIN phone AS T2 ON T1.Model_name  =  T2.chip_model JOIN screen_mode AS T3 ON T2.screen_mode = T3.Graphics_mode WHERE T3.Type = "Text" OR T1.RAM_MiB  >  32;

text_query: What are the first names and date of birth of professors teaching course ACCT-211?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.EMP_FNAME ,  T1.EMP_DOB FROM employee AS T1 JOIN CLASS AS T2 ON T1.EMP_NUM  =  T2.PROF_NUM WHERE CRS_CODE  =  "ACCT-211"

text_query: List each birth place along with the number of people from there.
sql_command: SELECT Birth_Place ,  COUNT(*) FROM people GROUP BY Birth_Place

text_query: How many movie directors are there?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT (DISTINCT director) FROM movie

text_query: Find the emails of the user named "Mary".
sql_command: SELECT email FROM user_profiles WHERE name  =  'Mary'

text_query: What is the title and credits of the course that is taught in the largest classroom (with the highest capacity)?
sql_command: SELECT T3.title ,  T3.credits FROM classroom AS T1 JOIN SECTION AS T2 ON T1.building  =  T2.building AND T1.room_number  =  T2.room_number JOIN course AS T3 ON T2.course_id  =  T3.course_id WHERE T1.capacity  =  (SELECT max(capacity) FROM classroom)

text_query: Show the id, the account name, and other account details for all accounts by the customer with first name 'Meaghan'.
sql_command: SELECT T1.account_id ,  T1.date_account_opened ,  T1.account_name ,  T1.other_account_details FROM Accounts AS T1 JOIN Customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE T2.customer_first_name  =  'Meaghan'

text_query: Show the names of members whose country is "United States" or "Canada".
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM member WHERE Country  =  "United States" OR Country  =  "Canada"

text_query: Which state can address "6862 Kaitlyn Knolls" possibly be in?
sql_command: SELECT state_province_county FROM addresses WHERE line_1_number_building LIKE "%6862 Kaitlyn Knolls%"

text_query: Show the names of companies in the banking or retailing industry?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM company WHERE Industry  =  "Banking" OR Industry  =  "Retailing"

text_query: What is the title of the prerequisite class of International Finance course?
