sql_command: SELECT title FROM course WHERE course_id IN (SELECT T1.prereq_id FROM prereq AS T1 JOIN course AS T2 ON T1.course_id  =  T2.course_id WHERE T2.title  =  'International Finance')

text_query: Which model saves the most gasoline? That is to say, have the maximum miles per gallon.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id ORDER BY T2.mpg DESC LIMIT 1;

text_query: What are the allergies and their types that the student with first name Lisa has? And order the result by name of allergies.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Allergy ,  T1.AllergyType FROM Allergy_type AS T1 JOIN Has_allergy AS T2 ON T1.Allergy  =  T2.Allergy JOIN Student AS T3 ON T3.StuID  =  T2.StuID WHERE T3.Fname  =  "Lisa" ORDER BY T1.Allergy

text_query: Please list the years of film market estimations when the market is in country "Japan" in descending order.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Year FROM film_market_estimation AS T1 JOIN market AS T2 ON T1.Market_ID  =  T2.Market_ID WHERE T2.Country  =  "Japan" ORDER BY T1.Year DESC

text_query: Find the names of the items that did not receive any review.
sql_command: SELECT title FROM item WHERE i_id NOT IN (SELECT i_id FROM review)

text_query: What are the issue dates of volumes associated with the artist aged 23 or younger?
sql_command: SELECT Issue_Date FROM artist AS T1 JOIN volume AS T2 ON T1.Artist_ID  =  T2.Artist_ID WHERE T1.age  <=  23

text_query: How much is the track Fast As a Shark?
sql_command: SELECT unit_price FROM tracks WHERE name = "Fast As a Shark";

text_query: What is the id and family name of the driver who has the longest laptime?
sql_command: SELECT T1.driverid ,  T1.surname FROM drivers AS T1 JOIN laptimes AS T2 ON T1.driverid = T2.driverid ORDER BY T2.milliseconds DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the maximum and minimum resolution of songs whose duration is 3 minutes?
sql_command: SELECT max(T2.resolution) ,  min(T2.resolution) FROM files AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.f_id  =  T2.f_id WHERE T1.duration LIKE "3:%"

text_query: get the details of employees who manage a department.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT * FROM employees AS T1 JOIN departments AS T2 ON T1.department_id  =  T2.department_id WHERE T1.employee_id  =  T2.manager_id

text_query: How many papers are published in total?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM papers

text_query: What is the role of the employee named Koby?
sql_command: SELECT T1.role_description FROM ROLES AS T1 JOIN Employees AS T2 ON T1.role_code = T2.role_code WHERE T2.employee_name = "Koby";

text_query: List the names of all songs that have 4 minute duration or are in English.
sql_command: SELECT T2.song_name FROM files AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.f_id  =  T2.f_id WHERE T1.duration LIKE "4:%" UNION SELECT song_name FROM song WHERE languages  =  "english"

text_query: What are the id of students who registered course 301?
sql_command: SELECT student_id FROM student_course_attendance WHERE course_id  =  301

text_query: What is the name of the movie produced after 2000 and directed by James Cameron?
sql_command: SELECT title FROM Movie WHERE director = 'James Cameron' AND YEAR  >  2000

text_query: show the titles, and authors or editors for all books made after the year 1989.
sql_command: SELECT book_title ,  author_or_editor FROM book_club WHERE YEAR  >  1989

text_query: List the name, date and result of each battle.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  date FROM battle

text_query: How many distinct currency codes are there for all drama workshop groups?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT Currency_Code) FROM Drama_Workshop_Groups

text_query: Find all the male members of club "Hopkins Student Enterprises". Show the first name and last name.
sql_command: SELECT t3.fname ,  t3.lname FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid JOIN student AS t3 ON t2.stuid  =  t3.stuid WHERE t1.clubname  =  "Hopkins Student Enterprises" AND t3.sex  =  "M"

text_query: Please show each industry and the corresponding number of companies in that industry.
sql_command: SELECT Industry ,  COUNT(*) FROM Companies GROUP BY Industry

text_query: Show the outcome code of mailshots along with the number of mailshots in each outcome code.
sql_command: SELECT outcome_code ,  count(*) FROM mailshot_customers GROUP BY outcome_code

text_query: Show the phone, room, and building for the faculty named Jerry Prince.
sql_command: SELECT phone ,  room ,  building FROM Faculty WHERE Fname  =  "Jerry" AND Lname  =  "Prince"

text_query: What is the average number of audience for festivals?
sql_command: SELECT avg(Num_of_Audience) FROM festival_detail

text_query: What are the average, maximum, and minimum number of floors for all buildings?
sql_command: SELECT avg(floors) ,  max(floors) ,  min(floors) FROM building

text_query: Please show the different statuses, ordered by the number of cities that have each.
sql_command: SELECT Status FROM city GROUP BY Status ORDER BY COUNT(*) ASC

text_query: List the names and scores of all wines.
sql_command: SELECT Name ,  Score FROM WINE

text_query: What is the name of the highest rated wine?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM WINE ORDER BY Score LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the number of members living in each address.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  address FROM member GROUP BY address

text_query: Show invoice dates and order id and details for all invoices.
sql_command: SELECT T1.invoice_date ,  T1.order_id ,  T2.order_details FROM Invoices AS T1 JOIN Orders AS T2 ON T1.order_id  =  T2.order_id

text_query: Find the captain rank that has no captain in Third-rate ship of the line class.
sql_command: SELECT rank FROM captain EXCEPT SELECT rank FROM captain WHERE CLASS  =  'Third-rate ship of the line'

text_query: How many flights does airline 'JetBlue Airways' have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM FLIGHTS AS T1 JOIN AIRLINES AS T2 ON T1.Airline  =  T2.uid WHERE T2.Airline = "JetBlue Airways"

text_query: What is average life expectancy in the countries where English is not the official language?
sql_command: SELECT avg(LifeExpectancy) FROM country WHERE Name NOT IN (SELECT T1.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "English" AND T2.IsOfficial  =  "T")

text_query: Find the name of customers who have both saving and checking account types.
sql_command: SELECT cust_name FROM customer WHERE acc_type  =  'saving' INTERSECT SELECT cust_name FROM customer WHERE acc_type  =  'checking'

text_query: Which shipping agent shipped the most documents? List the shipping agent name and the number of documents.
sql_command: SELECT Ref_Shipping_Agents.shipping_agent_name , count(Documents.document_id) FROM Ref_Shipping_Agents JOIN Documents ON Documents.shipping_agent_code = Ref_Shipping_Agents.shipping_agent_code GROUP BY Ref_Shipping_Agents.shipping_agent_code ORDER BY count(Documents.document_id) DESC LIMIT 1;

text_query: Show the transaction types and the total amount of transactions.
sql_command: SELECT transaction_type ,  sum(transaction_amount) FROM Financial_transactions GROUP BY transaction_type

text_query: Find the top 3 wineries with the greatest number of wines made of white color grapes.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Winery FROM GRAPES AS T1 JOIN WINE AS T2 ON T1.GRAPE  =  T2.GRAPE WHERE T1.Color  =  "White" GROUP BY T2.Winery ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: Find the distinct first names of all the students who have vice president votes and whose city code is not PIT.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Fname FROM STUDENT AS T1 JOIN VOTING_RECORD AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  T2.VICE_PRESIDENT_Vote EXCEPT SELECT DISTINCT Fname FROM STUDENT WHERE city_code  =  "PIT"

text_query: What are the names of festivals held in year 2007?
sql_command: SELECT Festival_Name FROM festival_detail WHERE YEAR  =  2007

text_query: Find the names of all the catalog entries.
sql_command: SELECT distinct(catalog_entry_name) FROM catalog_contents

text_query: Show the ids of all employees who have authorized destruction.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT Destruction_Authorised_by_Employee_ID FROM Documents_to_be_destroyed

text_query: What are the average, maximum and total revenues of all companies?
sql_command: SELECT avg(revenue) ,  max(revenue) ,  sum(revenue) FROM manufacturers

text_query: How many customers live in Prague city?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM customers WHERE city = "Prague";

text_query: What are the highest cost, lowest cost and average cost of procedures?
sql_command: SELECT MAX(cost) ,  MIN(cost) ,  AVG(cost) FROM procedures

text_query: How many owners temporarily do not have any dogs?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Owners WHERE owner_id NOT IN ( SELECT owner_id FROM Dogs )

text_query: Find the number of cities in each district whose population is greater than the average population of cities?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  District FROM city WHERE Population  >  (SELECT avg(Population) FROM city) GROUP BY District

text_query: Show all director names who have a movie in the year 1999 or 2000.
sql_command: SELECT director FROM movie WHERE YEAR  =  1999 OR YEAR  =  2000

text_query: List the cost of each treatment and the corresponding treatment type description.
sql_command: SELECT T1.cost_of_treatment ,  T2.treatment_type_description FROM Treatments AS T1 JOIN treatment_types AS T2 ON T1.treatment_type_code  =  T2.treatment_type_code

text_query: How many courses do the student whose id is 171 attend?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM courses AS T1 JOIN student_course_attendance AS T2 ON T1.course_id = T2.course_id WHERE T2.student_id = 171

text_query: What are the maximum and minimum number of silver medals for clubs.
sql_command: SELECT max(Silver) ,  min(Silver) FROM club_rank

text_query: How many participants belong to the type 'Organizer'?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM participants WHERE participant_type_code  =  'Organizer'

text_query: How many drivers are from Hartford city or younger than 40?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM driver WHERE home_city  =  'Hartford' OR age  <  40

text_query: With which kind of payment method were the least number of payments processed?
sql_command: SELECT Payment_Method_Code FROM Payments GROUP BY Payment_Method_Code ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name of instructors who are advising more than one student.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM instructor AS T1 JOIN advisor AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.i_id GROUP BY T2.i_id HAVING count(*)  >  1

text_query: How many distinct payment methods are used by parties?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT payment_method_code) FROM parties

text_query: What are the names of wines whose production year are before the year of all wines by Brander winery?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM WINE WHERE YEAR  <  (SELECT min(YEAR) FROM WINE WHERE Winery  =  "Brander")

text_query: Find the id and last name of the teacher that has the most detentions with detention type code "AFTER"?
sql_command: SELECT T1.teacher_id ,  T2.last_name FROM Detention AS T1 JOIN Teachers AS T2 ON T1.teacher_id  =  T2.teacher_id WHERE T1.detention_type_code  =  "AFTER" GROUP BY T1.teacher_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show all allergies with type food.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT allergy FROM Allergy_type WHERE allergytype  =  "food"

text_query: How many distinct complaint type codes are there in the database?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT complaint_type_code) FROM complaints

text_query: Find the the name of the customers who have a loan with amount more than 3000.
sql_command: SELECT T1.cust_name FROM customer AS T1 JOIN loan AS T2 ON T1.cust_id  =  T2.cust_id WHERE amount  >  3000

text_query: What are the heights of body builders with total score smaller than 315?
sql_command: SELECT T2.Height FROM body_builder AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID WHERE T1.Total  <  315

text_query: List all countries of markets in ascending alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT Country FROM market ORDER BY Country ASC

text_query: Show the locations shared by shops with open year later than 2012 and shops with open year before 2008.
sql_command: SELECT LOCATION FROM shop WHERE Open_Year  >  2012 INTERSECT SELECT LOCATION FROM shop WHERE Open_Year  <  2008

text_query: Find the name of scientists who are assigned to some project.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM assignedto AS T1 JOIN scientists AS T2 ON T1.scientist  =  T2.ssn

text_query: Show the ID of the high schooler named Kyle.
sql_command: SELECT ID FROM Highschooler WHERE name  =  "Kyle"

text_query: Show the countries that have both managers of age above 50 and managers of age below 46.
sql_command: SELECT Country FROM manager WHERE Age  >  50 INTERSECT SELECT Country FROM manager WHERE Age  <  46

text_query: Show the ids for all the students who participate in an activity and are under 20.
sql_command: SELECT StuID FROM Participates_in INTERSECT SELECT StuID FROM Student WHERE age  <  20

text_query: What are the names and locations of festivals?
sql_command: SELECT Festival_Name ,  LOCATION FROM festival_detail

text_query: Find the total number of hours have done for all students in each department.
sql_command: SELECT sum(stu_hrs) ,  dept_code FROM student GROUP BY dept_code

text_query: For each nomination, show the name of the artwork and name of the festival where it is nominated.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name ,  T3.Festival_Name FROM nomination AS T1 JOIN artwork AS T2 ON T1.Artwork_ID  =  T2.Artwork_ID JOIN festival_detail AS T3 ON T1.Festival_ID  =  T3.Festival_ID

text_query: Show the leader names and locations of colleges.
sql_command: SELECT Leader_Name ,  College_Location FROM college

text_query: Show first name and last name for all students.
sql_command: SELECT Fname ,  Lname FROM Student

text_query: Show the student IDs and numbers of friends corresponding to each.
sql_command: SELECT student_id ,  count(*) FROM Friend GROUP BY student_id

text_query: List the names of courses in alphabetical order?
sql_command: SELECT course_name FROM courses ORDER BY course_name

text_query: Find the market shares and names of furnitures which no any company is producing in our records.
sql_command: SELECT Market_Rate ,  name FROM furniture WHERE Furniture_ID NOT IN (SELECT Furniture_ID FROM furniture_manufacte)

text_query: How many countries are listed?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM COUNTRIES;

text_query: Find the total claimed amount of all the claims.
sql_command: SELECT sum(Amount_Claimed) FROM Claims

text_query: How many 'United Airlines' flights go to Airport 'ASY'?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM AIRLINES AS T1 JOIN FLIGHTS AS T2 ON T2.Airline  =  T1.uid WHERE T1.Airline  =  "United Airlines" AND T2.DestAirport  =  "ASY"

text_query: Find the name and age of the person who is a friend of both Dan and Alice.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  T1.age FROM Person AS T1 JOIN PersonFriend AS T2 ON T1.name  =  T2.name WHERE T2.friend  =  'Dan' INTERSECT SELECT T1.name ,   T1.age FROM Person AS T1 JOIN PersonFriend AS T2 ON T1.name  =  T2.name WHERE T2.friend  =  'Alice'

text_query: Find the total account balance of each customer from Utah or Texas.
sql_command: SELECT sum(acc_bal) FROM customer WHERE state  =  'Utah' OR state  =  'Texas'

text_query: Show the start dates and end dates of all the apartment bookings.
sql_command: SELECT booking_start_date ,  booking_end_date FROM Apartment_Bookings

text_query: List all ship names in the order of built year and class.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM ship ORDER BY built_year ,  CLASS

text_query: Find the average price of all product clothes.
sql_command: SELECT avg(product_price) FROM products WHERE product_type_code  =  'Clothes'

text_query: Find the last names of teachers teaching in classroom 109.
sql_command: SELECT lastname FROM teachers WHERE classroom  =  109

text_query: What are the student ids of students who don't have any allergies?
sql_command: SELECT StuID FROM Student EXCEPT SELECT StuID FROM Has_allergy

text_query: List the emails of the professionals who live in the state of Hawaii or the state of Wisconsin.
sql_command: SELECT email_address FROM Professionals WHERE state  =  'Hawaii' OR state  =  'Wisconsin'

text_query: What are the descriptions of the courses with name "database"?
sql_command: SELECT course_description FROM COURSES WHERE course_name  =  "database"

text_query: Show member names that are not in the Progress Party.
sql_command: SELECT T1.member_name FROM Member AS T1 JOIN party AS T2 ON T1.party_id  =  T2.party_id WHERE T2.Party_name != "Progress Party"

text_query: Find the common personal name of course authors and students.
sql_command: SELECT personal_name FROM Course_Authors_and_Tutors INTERSECT SELECT personal_name FROM Students

text_query: Show publishers with a book published in 1989 and a book in 1990.
sql_command: SELECT publisher FROM book_club WHERE YEAR  =  1989 INTERSECT SELECT publisher FROM book_club WHERE YEAR  =  1990

text_query: For directors who had more than one movie, return the titles and produced years of all movies directed by them.
sql_command: SELECT T1.title ,  T1.year FROM Movie AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.director  =  T2.director WHERE T1.title != T2.title

text_query: Which stadium name contains the substring "Bank"?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM stadium WHERE name LIKE "%Bank%"

text_query: How many Annual Meeting events happened in the United Kingdom region?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM region AS t1 JOIN party AS t2 ON t1.region_id  =  t2.region_id JOIN party_events AS t3 ON t2.party_id  =  t3.party_id WHERE t1.region_name  =  "United Kingdom" AND t3.Event_Name  =  "Annaual Meeting"

text_query: Show all publishers and the number of books for each publisher.
sql_command: SELECT publisher ,  count(*) FROM book_club GROUP BY publisher

text_query: How many people live in Gelderland district?
sql_command: SELECT sum(Population) FROM city WHERE District  =  "Gelderland"

text_query: What are the average and maximum number of tickets bought in all visits?
sql_command: SELECT avg(num_of_ticket) ,  max(num_of_ticket) FROM visit

text_query: Find the average elevation of all airports for each country.
sql_command: SELECT avg(elevation) ,  country FROM airports GROUP BY country

text_query: give me names of all compatible browsers and accelerators in the descending order of compatible year
sql_command: SELECT T2.name ,  T3.name FROM accelerator_compatible_browser AS T1 JOIN browser AS T2 ON T1.browser_id  =  T2.id JOIN web_client_accelerator AS T3 ON T1.accelerator_id  =  T3.id ORDER BY T1.compatible_since_year DESC

text_query: When was the order placed whose shipment tracking number is 3452? Give me the date.
sql_command: SELECT T1.date_order_placed FROM orders AS T1 JOIN shipments AS T2 ON T1.order_id = T2.order_id WHERE T2.shipment_tracking_number = 3452

text_query: List the company name and rank for all companies in the decreasing order of their sales.
sql_command: SELECT company ,  rank FROM company ORDER BY Sales_billion DESC

text_query: Find the name of customers whose credit score is below the average credit scores of all customers.
sql_command: SELECT cust_name FROM customer WHERE credit_score  <  (SELECT avg(credit_score) FROM customer)

text_query: Show the location name for document "Robin CV".
sql_command: SELECT T3.location_name FROM All_documents AS T1 JOIN Document_locations AS T2 ON T1.document_id  =  T2.document_id JOIN Ref_locations AS T3 ON T2.location_code  =  T3.location_code WHERE T1.document_name  =  "Robin CV"

text_query: Show the names of employees that work for companies with sales bigger than 200.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name FROM employment AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID JOIN company AS T3 ON T1.Company_ID  =  T3.Company_ID WHERE T3.Sales_in_Billion  >  200

text_query: List the language used least number of TV Channel. List language and number of TV Channel.
sql_command: SELECT LANGUAGE ,  count(*) FROM TV_Channel GROUP BY LANGUAGE ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1;

text_query: Show all template type codes and the number of documents using each type.
sql_command: SELECT T1.template_type_code ,  count(*) FROM Templates AS T1 JOIN Documents AS T2 ON T1.template_id  =  T2.template_id GROUP BY T1.template_type_code

text_query: What are all the customer phone numbers under the most popular policy type?
sql_command: SELECT customer_phone FROM available_policies WHERE policy_type_code  =  (SELECT policy_type_code FROM available_policies GROUP BY policy_type_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1)

text_query: How many female Professors do we have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Faculty WHERE Sex  =  'F' AND Rank  =  "Professor"

text_query: What are the first names of customers who have not rented any films after '2005-08-23 02:06:01'?
sql_command: SELECT first_name FROM customer WHERE customer_id NOT IN( SELECT customer_id FROM rental WHERE rental_date  >  '2005-08-23 02:06:01' )

text_query: What are the shortest duration and lowest rating of songs grouped by genre and ordered by genre?
sql_command: SELECT min(T1.duration) ,  min(T2.rating) ,  T2.genre_is FROM files AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.f_id  =  T2.f_id GROUP BY T2.genre_is ORDER BY T2.genre_is

text_query: Which parts have more than 2 faults? Show the part name and id.
sql_command: SELECT T1.part_name ,  T1.part_id FROM Parts AS T1 JOIN Part_Faults AS T2 ON T1.part_id  =  T2.part_id GROUP BY T1.part_id HAVING count(*)  >  2

text_query: Find the title and score of the movie with the lowest rating among all movies directed by each director.
sql_command: SELECT T2.title ,  T1.stars ,  T2.director ,  min(T1.stars) FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID GROUP BY T2.director

text_query: What are the id, name and membership level of visitors who have spent the largest amount of money in total in all museum tickets?
sql_command: SELECT t2.visitor_id ,  t1.name ,  t1.Level_of_membership FROM visitor AS t1 JOIN visit AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.visitor_id GROUP BY t2.visitor_id ORDER BY sum(t2.Total_spent) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the Package Option of TV Channel with serial name "Sky Radio"?
sql_command: SELECT Package_Option FROM TV_Channel WHERE series_name = "Sky Radio";

text_query: What is the most common hometown of gymnasts?
sql_command: SELECT T2.Hometown FROM gymnast AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.Gymnast_ID  =  T2.People_ID GROUP BY T2.Hometown ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the name of all different customers who have some loan sorted by their total loan amount.
sql_command: SELECT T1.cust_name FROM customer AS T1 JOIN loan AS T2 ON T1.cust_id  =  T2.cust_id GROUP BY T1.cust_name ORDER BY sum(T2.amount)

text_query: Show the names of conductors and the orchestras they have conducted.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name ,  T2.Orchestra FROM conductor AS T1 JOIN orchestra AS T2 ON T1.Conductor_ID  =  T2.Conductor_ID

text_query: Find the first name and gpa of the students whose gpa is lower than the average gpa of all students.
sql_command: SELECT stu_fname ,  stu_gpa FROM student WHERE stu_gpa  <  (SELECT avg(stu_gpa) FROM student)

text_query: How many king beds are there?
sql_command: SELECT sum(beds) FROM Rooms WHERE bedtype  =  'King';

text_query: What are the names and parties of representatives?
sql_command: SELECT Name ,  Party FROM representative

text_query: Show the minimum, maximum, average price for all products.
sql_command: SELECT min(product_price) ,  max(product_price) ,  avg(product_price) FROM products

text_query: How many different kinds of lens brands are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT brand) FROM camera_lens

text_query: List the names of the top 5 oldest people.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM People ORDER BY Age DESC LIMIT 5

text_query: What are the movie titles and average rating of the movies with the lowest average rating?
sql_command: SELECT T2.title ,  avg(T1.stars) FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID GROUP BY T1.mID ORDER BY avg(T1.stars) LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the vocal types used in song "Badlands"?
sql_command: SELECT TYPE FROM vocals AS T1 JOIN songs AS T2 ON T1.songid  =  T2.songid WHERE title  =  "Badlands"

text_query: Which campus has the most degrees conferred in all times?
sql_command: SELECT campus FROM degrees GROUP BY campus ORDER BY sum(degrees) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name and id of the top 3 expensive rooms.
sql_command: SELECT RoomId ,  roomName FROM Rooms ORDER BY basePrice DESC LIMIT 3;

text_query: List the names of pilots in ascending order of rank.
sql_command: SELECT Pilot_name FROM pilot ORDER BY Rank ASC

text_query: Show names for all employees who have certificate of Boeing 737-800.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM Employee AS T1 JOIN Certificate AS T2 ON T1.eid  =  T2.eid JOIN Aircraft AS T3 ON T3.aid  =  T2.aid WHERE T3.name  =  "Boeing 737-800"

text_query: Show all cities where students live.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT city_code FROM Student

text_query: List all countries and their number of airlines in the descending order of number of airlines.
sql_command: SELECT country ,  count(*) FROM airlines GROUP BY country ORDER BY count(*) DESC

text_query: Find the number of schools that have more than one donator whose donation amount is less than 8.5.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM (SELECT * FROM endowment WHERE amount  >  8.5 GROUP BY school_id HAVING count(*)  >  1)

text_query: Give me the dates when the max temperature was higher than 85.
sql_command: SELECT date FROM weather WHERE max_temperature_f  >  85

text_query: What are the id and name of the photos for mountains?
sql_command: SELECT T1.id ,  T1.name FROM mountain AS T1 JOIN photos AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.mountain_id WHERE T1.height  >  4000

text_query: Give me a list of id and status of orders which belong to the customer named "Jeramie".
sql_command: SELECT T2.order_id ,  T2.order_status FROM customers AS T1 JOIN orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id WHERE T1.customer_name = "Jeramie"

text_query: Find the names of all physicians and their primary affiliated departments' names.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  T3.name FROM physician AS T1 JOIN affiliated_with AS T2 ON T1.EmployeeID  =  T2.physician JOIN department AS T3 ON T2.department  =  T3.DepartmentID WHERE T2.PrimaryAffiliation  =  1

text_query: Who is the "CTO" of club "Hopkins Student Enterprises"? Show the first name and last name.
sql_command: SELECT t3.fname ,  t3.lname FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid JOIN student AS t3 ON t2.stuid  =  t3.stuid WHERE t1.clubname  =  "Hopkins Student Enterprises" AND t2.position  =  "CTO"

text_query: What is the average age of female (sex is F) students?
sql_command: SELECT avg(Age) FROM STUDENT WHERE Sex  =  "F"

text_query: How many appointments are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM appointment

text_query: Find the number of different cities which banks are located at.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT city) FROM bank

text_query: list the card number of all members whose hometown address includes word "Kentucky".
sql_command: SELECT card_number FROM member WHERE Hometown LIKE "%Kentucky%"

text_query: Show the names of phones and the districts of markets they are on, in ascending order of the ranking of the market.
sql_command: SELECT T3.Name ,  T2.District FROM phone_market AS T1 JOIN market AS T2 ON T1.Market_ID  =  T2.Market_ID JOIN phone AS T3 ON T1.Phone_ID  =  T3.Phone_ID ORDER BY T2.Ranking

text_query: What are the ids and durations of the trips with the top 3 durations?
sql_command: SELECT id ,  duration FROM trip ORDER BY duration DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: How many students did not have any course enrollment?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Students WHERE student_id NOT IN (SELECT student_id FROM Student_Course_Enrolment)

text_query: Which room has cheapest base price? List the room's name and the base price.
sql_command: SELECT roomName ,  basePrice FROM Rooms ORDER BY basePrice ASC LIMIT 1;

text_query: How many services are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM services

text_query: List the names of all routes in alphabetic order.
sql_command: SELECT route_name FROM Delivery_Routes ORDER BY route_name

text_query: Find the average grade of all students who have some friends.
sql_command: SELECT avg(grade) FROM Highschooler WHERE id IN (SELECT T1.student_id FROM Friend AS T1 JOIN Highschooler AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.id)

text_query: Show the names of phones with carrier either "Sprint" or "TMobile".
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM phone WHERE Carrier  =  "Sprint" OR Carrier  =  "TMobile"

text_query: Show the names of people who have been on the negative side of debates at least twice.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name FROM debate_people AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.Negative  =  T2.People_ID GROUP BY T2.Name HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  2

text_query: What are the name and id of the team with the most victories in 2008 postseason?
sql_command: SELECT T2.name ,  T1.team_id_winner FROM postseason AS T1 JOIN team AS T2 ON T1.team_id_winner  =  T2.team_id_br WHERE T1.year  =  2008 GROUP BY T1.team_id_winner ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1;

text_query: Show all product colors.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT product_color FROM Products

text_query: What are the famous title of the artists associated with volumes with more than 2 weeks on top?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Famous_Title FROM artist AS T1 JOIN volume AS T2 ON T1.Artist_ID  =  T2.Artist_ID WHERE T2.Weeks_on_Top  >  2

text_query: Find the name and salary of instructors whose salary is below the average salary of the instructors in the Physics department.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  salary FROM instructor WHERE salary  <  (SELECT avg(salary) FROM instructor WHERE dept_name  =  'Physics')

text_query: List the names of editors in ascending order of age.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM editor ORDER BY Age ASC

text_query: Which city has hosted the most events?
sql_command: SELECT T1.city FROM city AS T1 JOIN hosting_city AS T2 ON T1.city_id  =  T2.host_city GROUP BY T2.host_city ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the number of students who are older than 18 and do not have allergy to either food or animal.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Student WHERE age  >  18 AND StuID NOT IN ( SELECT StuID FROM Has_allergy AS T1 JOIN Allergy_Type AS T2 ON T1.Allergy  =  T2.Allergy WHERE T2.allergytype  =  "food" OR T2.allergytype  =  "animal")

text_query: Show the names and genders of players with a coach starting after 2011.
sql_command: SELECT T3.Player_name ,  T3.gender FROM player_coach AS T1 JOIN coach AS T2 ON T1.Coach_ID  =  T2.Coach_ID JOIN player AS T3 ON T1.Player_ID  =  T3.Player_ID WHERE T1.Starting_year  >  2011

text_query: List the name of staff who has been assigned multiple jobs.
sql_command: SELECT T1.staff_name FROM staff AS T1 JOIN staff_department_assignments AS T2 ON T1.staff_id  =  T2.staff_id GROUP BY T2.staff_id HAVING COUNT (*)  >  1

text_query: What are the details and ways to get to tourist attractions related to royal family?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Royal_Family_Details ,  T2.How_to_Get_There FROM ROYAL_FAMILY AS T1 JOIN TOURIST_ATTRACTIONS AS T2 ON T1.Royal_Family_ID  =  T2.Tourist_Attraction_ID

text_query: What is the starting year of the oldest technicians?
sql_command: SELECT Starting_Year FROM technician ORDER BY Age DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the locations that have at least two performances.
sql_command: SELECT LOCATION FROM performance GROUP BY LOCATION HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  2

text_query: Show all the distinct buildings that have faculty rooms.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT building FROM Faculty

text_query: What is the name of the visitor who visited both a museum opened before 2009 and a museum opened after 2011?
sql_command: SELECT t1.name FROM visitor AS t1 JOIN visit AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.visitor_id JOIN museum AS t3 ON t3.Museum_ID  =  t2.Museum_ID WHERE t3.open_year  <  2009 INTERSECT SELECT t1.name FROM visitor AS t1 JOIN visit AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.visitor_id JOIN museum AS t3 ON t3.Museum_ID  =  t2.Museum_ID WHERE t3.open_year  >  2011

text_query: Which year has most number of concerts?
sql_command: SELECT YEAR FROM concert GROUP BY YEAR ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Which campus was opened between 1935 and 1939?
sql_command: SELECT campus FROM campuses WHERE YEAR  >=  1935 AND YEAR  <=  1939

text_query: Find the name and address of the department that has the highest number of students.
sql_command: SELECT T2.dept_name ,  T2.dept_address FROM student AS T1 JOIN department AS T2 ON T1.dept_code  =  T2.dept_code GROUP BY T1.dept_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many male (sex is M) students have class senator votes in the fall election cycle?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM STUDENT AS T1 JOIN VOTING_RECORD AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  Class_Senator_Vote WHERE T1.Sex  =  "M" AND T2.Election_Cycle  =  "Fall"

text_query: Show all the activity names and the number of faculty involved in each activity.
sql_command: SELECT T1.activity_name ,  count(*) FROM Activity AS T1 JOIN Faculty_participates_in AS T2 ON T1.actID  =  T2.actID GROUP BY T1.actID

text_query: How many customers have an active value of 1?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM customer WHERE active = '1'

text_query: For each phone, show its names and total number of stocks.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name ,  sum(T1.Num_of_stock) FROM phone_market AS T1 JOIN phone AS T2 ON T1.Phone_ID  =  T2.Phone_ID GROUP BY T2.Name

text_query: What are the first names of all the students?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT fname FROM student

text_query: Which poll resource provided the most number of candidate information?
sql_command: SELECT poll_source FROM candidate GROUP BY poll_source ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Which classes have more than two captains?
sql_command: SELECT CLASS FROM captain GROUP BY CLASS HAVING count(*)  >  2

text_query: Find the id for the trips that lasted at least as long as the average duration of trips in zip code 94103.
sql_command: SELECT id FROM trip WHERE duration  >=  (SELECT avg(duration) FROM trip WHERE zip_code  =  94103)

text_query: Find the number of rooms for different block code?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  T1.blockcode FROM BLOCK AS T1 JOIN room AS T2 ON T1.blockfloor  =  T2.blockfloor AND T1.blockcode  =  T2.blockcode GROUP BY T1.blockcode

text_query: How many drivers participated in the race Australian Grand Prix held in 2009?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM results AS T1 JOIN races AS T2 ON T1.raceid = T2.raceid WHERE T2.name = "Australian Grand Prix" AND YEAR = 2009

text_query: What are the id of students who registered courses or attended courses?
sql_command: SELECT student_id FROM student_course_registrations UNION SELECT student_id FROM student_course_attendance

text_query: Which bike traveled the most often in zip code 94002?
sql_command: SELECT bike_id FROM trip WHERE zip_code  =  94002 GROUP BY bike_id ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is maximum, minimum and average amount of outstanding of customer?
sql_command: SELECT max(amount_outstanding) ,  min(amount_outstanding) ,  avg(amount_outstanding) FROM Customers;

text_query: Show the names of editors that are on the committee of journals with sales bigger than 3000.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name FROM journal_committee AS T1 JOIN editor AS T2 ON T1.Editor_ID  =  T2.Editor_ID JOIN journal AS T3 ON T1.Journal_ID  =  T3.Journal_ID WHERE T3.Sales  >  3000

text_query: What is first names of the top 5 staff who have handled the greatest number of complaints?
sql_command: SELECT t1.first_name FROM staff AS t1 JOIN complaints AS t2 ON t1.staff_id  =  t2.staff_id GROUP BY t2.staff_id ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 5

text_query: How many rooms whose capacity is less than 50 does the Lamberton building have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM classroom WHERE building  =  'Lamberton' AND capacity  <  50

text_query: Show names of teachers and the courses they are arranged to teach.
sql_command: SELECT T3.Name ,  T2.Course FROM course_arrange AS T1 JOIN course AS T2 ON T1.Course_ID  =  T2.Course_ID JOIN teacher AS T3 ON T1.Teacher_ID  =  T3.Teacher_ID

text_query: What is the maximum horsepower and the make of the car models with 3 cylinders?
sql_command: SELECT T2.horsepower ,  T1.Make FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id WHERE T2.cylinders  =  3 ORDER BY T2.horsepower DESC LIMIT 1;

text_query: What is the average rating of songs for each language?
sql_command: SELECT avg(rating) ,  languages FROM song GROUP BY languages

text_query: Show all locations which don't have a train station with at least 15 platforms.
sql_command: SELECT LOCATION FROM station EXCEPT SELECT LOCATION FROM station WHERE number_of_platforms  >=  15

text_query: What is the total number of purchases for members with level 6?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM purchase AS T1 JOIN member AS T2 ON T1.member_id  =  T2.member_id WHERE T2.level  =  6

text_query: List the position of players and the average number of points of players of each position.
sql_command: SELECT POSITION ,  avg(Points) FROM player GROUP BY POSITION

text_query: What are the dates of publications in descending order of price?
sql_command: SELECT Publication_Date FROM publication ORDER BY Price DESC

text_query: List the name and tonnage ordered by in descending alphaetical order for the names.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  tonnage FROM ship ORDER BY name DESC

text_query: How many different services are provided by all stations?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT services) FROM station

text_query: Find the first name of the band mate that has performed in most songs.
sql_command: SELECT t2.firstname FROM Performance AS t1 JOIN Band AS t2 ON t1.bandmate  =  t2.id JOIN Songs AS T3 ON T3.SongId  =  T1.SongId GROUP BY firstname ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the invoice number and invoice date for the invoice with most number of transactions?
sql_command: SELECT T2.invoice_number ,  T2.invoice_date FROM Financial_transactions AS T1 JOIN Invoices AS T2 ON T1.invoice_number  =  T2.invoice_number GROUP BY T1.invoice_number ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the publication dates of publications with 3 lowest prices.
sql_command: SELECT Publication_Date FROM publication ORDER BY Price ASC LIMIT 3

text_query: What are the investors that have invested in at least two entrepreneurs?
sql_command: SELECT Investor FROM entrepreneur GROUP BY Investor HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  2

text_query: Which city is the headquarter of the store named "Blackville" in?
sql_command: SELECT t3.headquartered_city FROM store AS t1 JOIN store_district AS t2 ON t1.store_id  =  t2.store_id JOIN district AS t3 ON t2.district_id  =  t3.district_id WHERE t1.store_name  =  "Blackville"

text_query: Find the series name and country of the tv channel that is playing some cartoons directed by Ben Jones and Michael Chang?
sql_command: SELECT T1.series_name ,  T1.country FROM TV_Channel AS T1 JOIN cartoon AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.Channel WHERE T2.directed_by  =  'Michael Chang' INTERSECT SELECT T1.series_name ,  T1.country FROM TV_Channel AS T1 JOIN cartoon AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.Channel WHERE T2.directed_by  =  'Ben Jones'

text_query: What are the memories and carriers of phones?
sql_command: SELECT Memory_in_G ,  Carrier FROM phone

text_query: What are the document ids for the budget type code 'SF'?
sql_command: SELECT document_id FROM Documents_with_expenses WHERE budget_type_code  =  'SF'

text_query: Find the number of players for each hand type.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  hand FROM players GROUP BY hand

text_query: What is the membership card held by both members living in Hartford and ones living in Waterbury address?
sql_command: SELECT membership_card FROM member WHERE address  =  'Hartford' INTERSECT SELECT membership_card FROM member WHERE address  =  'Waterbury'

text_query: For each state, find the total account balance of customers whose credit score is above 100.
sql_command: SELECT sum(acc_bal) ,  state FROM customer WHERE credit_score  >  100 GROUP BY state

text_query: List the names and decor of rooms that have a king bed. Sort the list by their price.
sql_command: SELECT roomName ,  decor FROM Rooms WHERE bedtype  =  'King' ORDER BY basePrice;

text_query: How many students got accepted after the tryout?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM tryout WHERE decision  =  'yes'

text_query: Group by ships by flag, and return number of ships that have each flag.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  flag FROM ship GROUP BY flag

text_query: Show the member names which are in both the party with id 3 and the party with id 1.
sql_command: SELECT member_name FROM member WHERE party_id  =  3 INTERSECT SELECT member_name FROM member WHERE party_id  =  1

text_query: What is the average number of hosts for parties?
sql_command: SELECT avg(Number_of_hosts) FROM party

text_query: List the name of albums that are released by aritist whose name has 'Led'
sql_command: SELECT T2.title FROM artists AS T1 JOIN albums AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.artist_id WHERE T1.name LIKE '%Led%'

text_query: Who is the oldest person whose job is student?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM Person WHERE job  =  'student' AND age  =  (SELECT max(age) FROM person WHERE job  =  'student' )

text_query: Find the average age of members of the club "Hopkins Student Enterprises".
sql_command: SELECT avg(t3.age) FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid JOIN student AS t3 ON t2.stuid  =  t3.stuid WHERE t1.clubname  =  "Hopkins Student Enterprises"

text_query: Find the id and surname of the driver who participated the most number of races?
sql_command: SELECT T1.driverid ,  T1.surname FROM drivers AS T1 JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.driverid = T2.driverid JOIN races AS T3 ON T2.raceid = T3.raceid GROUP BY T1.driverid ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the names of courses that have either 3 credits or 1 credit but 4 hours.
sql_command: SELECT CName FROM COURSE WHERE Credits  =  3 UNION SELECT CName FROM COURSE WHERE Credits  =  1 AND Hours  =  4

text_query: Which country is the airport that has the highest altitude located in?
sql_command: SELECT country FROM airports ORDER BY elevation DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the residences that have both a player of gender "M" and a player of gender "F".
sql_command: SELECT Residence FROM player WHERE gender  =  "M" INTERSECT SELECT Residence FROM player WHERE gender  =  "F"

text_query: What is the number of states that has some colleges whose enrollment is smaller than the average enrollment?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT state) FROM college WHERE enr  <  (SELECT avg(enr) FROM college)

text_query: Show all party names and their region names.
sql_command: SELECT T1.party_name ,  T2.region_name FROM party AS T1 JOIN region AS T2 ON T1.region_id  =  T2.region_id

text_query: What are the maximum and minimum values of area codes?
sql_command: SELECT max(area_code) ,  min(area_code) FROM area_code_state

text_query: Report the name of all campuses in Los Angeles county.
sql_command: SELECT campus FROM campuses WHERE county  =  "Los Angeles"

text_query: How many parties do we have?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT party_name) FROM party

text_query: Find the first and last name of students who are not in the largest major.
sql_command: SELECT fname ,  lname FROM student WHERE major != (SELECT major FROM student GROUP BY major ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1)

text_query: Find the first and last name of all the students of age 18 who have vice president votes.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Fname ,  T1.LName FROM STUDENT AS T1 JOIN VOTING_RECORD AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  T2.VICE_President_VOTE WHERE T1.age  =  18

text_query: Show locations and nicknames of schools.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Location ,  T2.Nickname FROM school AS T1 JOIN school_details AS T2 ON T1.School_ID  =  T2.School_ID

text_query: What are the distinct creation years of the departments managed by a secretary born in state 'Alabama'?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.creation FROM department AS T1 JOIN management AS T2 ON T1.department_id  =  T2.department_id JOIN head AS T3 ON T2.head_id  =  T3.head_id WHERE T3.born_state  =  'Alabama'

text_query: Show the country where people older than 30 and younger than 25 are from.
sql_command: SELECT country FROM people WHERE age  <  25 INTERSECT SELECT country FROM people WHERE age  >  30

text_query: Find the purchase time, age and address of each member, and show the results in the order of purchase time.
sql_command: SELECT Time_of_purchase ,  age ,  address FROM member ORDER BY Time_of_purchase

text_query: Find the total number of scientists.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM scientists

text_query: What are the ids and details of events that have more than one participants?
sql_command: SELECT T1.event_id ,  T1.event_details FROM EVENTS AS T1 JOIN Participants_in_Events AS T2 ON T1.Event_ID  =  T2.Event_ID GROUP BY T1.Event_ID HAVING count(*)  >  1

text_query: What is the name of the department that has the largest number of students enrolled?
sql_command: SELECT T4.dept_name FROM CLASS AS T1 JOIN enroll AS T2 ON T1.class_code  =  T2.class_code JOIN course AS T3 ON T1.crs_code  =  T3.crs_code JOIN department AS T4 ON T3.dept_code  =  T4.dept_code GROUP BY T3.dept_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the total number of matches.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM matches

text_query: List how many times the number of people in the room reached the maximum occupancy of the room. The number of people include adults and kids.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Reservations AS T1 JOIN Rooms AS T2 ON T1.Room  =  T2.RoomId WHERE T2.maxOccupancy  =  T1.Adults + T1.Kids;

text_query: How many songs have 4 minute duration?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM files WHERE duration LIKE "4:%"

text_query: Give me the name and year of opening of the manufacturers that have either less than 10 factories or more than 10 shops.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  open_year FROM manufacturer WHERE num_of_shops  >  10 OR Num_of_Factories  <  10

text_query: What is the document name and template id for document with description with the letter 'w' in it?
sql_command: SELECT document_name ,  template_id FROM Documents WHERE Document_Description LIKE "%w%"

text_query: What is the maximum fastest lap speed in race named 'Monaco Grand Prix' in 2008 ?
sql_command: SELECT max(T2.fastestlapspeed) FROM races AS T1 JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.raceid = T2.raceid WHERE T1.year = 2008 AND T1.name = "Monaco Grand Prix"

text_query: Find name of the services that has never been used.
sql_command: SELECT service_name FROM services EXCEPT SELECT t1.service_name FROM services AS t1 JOIN party_services AS t2 ON t1.service_id  =  t2.service_id

text_query: What is the names of the physicians who prescribe medication Thesisin?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.name FROM physician AS T1 JOIN prescribes AS T2 ON T1.employeeid = T2.physician JOIN medication AS T3 ON T3.code = T2.medication WHERE T3.name  =  "Thesisin"

text_query: Give me a list of cities whose temperature in Mar is lower than that in Dec and which have never been host cities.
sql_command: SELECT T1.city FROM city AS T1 JOIN temperature AS T2 ON T1.city_id  =  T2.city_id WHERE T2.Mar  <  T2.Dec EXCEPT SELECT T3.city FROM city AS T3 JOIN hosting_city AS T4 ON T3.city_id  =  T4.host_city

text_query: What is the product with the highest height? Give me the catalog entry name.
sql_command: SELECT catalog_entry_name FROM catalog_contents ORDER BY height DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many credits does course CIS-220 have, and what its description?
sql_command: SELECT crs_credit ,  crs_description FROM course WHERE crs_code  =  'CIS-220'

text_query: Find the average number of factories for the manufacturers that have more than 20 shops.
sql_command: SELECT avg(Num_of_Factories) FROM manufacturer WHERE num_of_shops  >  20

text_query: Find the subject ID, name of subject and the corresponding number of courses for each subject, and sort by the course count in ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT T1.subject_id ,  T2.subject_name ,  COUNT(*) FROM Courses AS T1 JOIN Subjects AS T2 ON T1.subject_id  =  T2.subject_id GROUP BY T1.subject_id ORDER BY COUNT(*) ASC

text_query: Find the number of dorms and total capacity for each gender.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  sum(student_capacity) ,  gender FROM dorm GROUP BY gender

text_query: What is the name of the oldest manager?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM manager ORDER BY Age DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show names of teachers and the courses they are arranged to teach in ascending alphabetical order of the teacher's name.
sql_command: SELECT T3.Name ,  T2.Course FROM course_arrange AS T1 JOIN course AS T2 ON T1.Course_ID  =  T2.Course_ID JOIN teacher AS T3 ON T1.Teacher_ID  =  T3.Teacher_ID ORDER BY T3.Name

text_query: Show all the distinct institution types.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT TYPE FROM institution

text_query: Show all advisors who have at least two students.
sql_command: SELECT advisor FROM Student GROUP BY advisor HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: What are the names and countries of origin for the artists who produced the top three highly rated songs.
sql_command: SELECT T1.artist_name ,  T1.country FROM artist AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.artist_name  =  T2.artist_name ORDER BY T2.rating DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: Show the id and salary of Mark Young.
sql_command: SELECT eid ,  salary FROM Employee WHERE name  =  'Mark Young'

text_query: What is the total number of unique official languages spoken in the countries that are founded before 1930?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT T2.Language) FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE  IndepYear  <  1930 AND T2.IsOfficial  =  "T"

text_query: How many entrepreneurs are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM entrepreneur

text_query: List the maximum, minimum and average number of used kb in screen mode.
sql_command: SELECT max(used_kb) , min(used_kb) , avg(used_kb) FROM screen_mode;

text_query: How many pilots are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM pilot

text_query: How many different types of beds are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT bedType) FROM Rooms;

text_query: Give me a list of cities whose temperature in March is lower than that in July or higher than that in Oct?
sql_command: SELECT T1.city FROM city AS T1 JOIN temperature AS T2 ON T1.city_id  =  T2.city_id WHERE T2.Mar  <  T2.Jul OR T2.Mar  >  T2.Oct

text_query: What is the minimum, maximum, and average seating for all tracks.
sql_command: SELECT min(seating) ,  max(seating) ,  avg(seating) FROM track

text_query: What is the number of faculty lines in campus "Long Beach State University" in 2002?
sql_command: SELECT faculty FROM faculty AS T1 JOIN campuses AS T2 ON T1.campus  =  T2.id WHERE T1.year  =  2002 AND T2.campus  =  "Long Beach State University"

text_query: Show the names of donors who donated to both school "Glenn" and "Triton."
sql_command: SELECT T1.donator_name FROM endowment AS T1 JOIN school AS T2 ON T1.school_id  =  T2.school_id WHERE T2.school_name  =  'Glenn' INTERSECT SELECT T1.donator_name FROM endowment AS T1 JOIN school AS T2 ON T1.school_id  =  T2.school_id WHERE T2.school_name  =  'Triton'

text_query: What is the type of allergy Cat?
sql_command: SELECT allergytype FROM Allergy_type WHERE allergy  =  "Cat"

text_query: Find the average age of the students who have allergies with food and animal types.
sql_command: SELECT avg(age) FROM Student WHERE StuID IN ( SELECT T1.StuID FROM Has_allergy AS T1 JOIN Allergy_Type AS T2 ON T1.Allergy  =  T2.Allergy WHERE T2.allergytype  =  "food" INTERSECT SELECT T1.StuID FROM Has_allergy AS T1 JOIN Allergy_Type AS T2 ON T1.Allergy  =  T2.Allergy WHERE T2.allergytype  =  "animal")

text_query: Find the cities which have exactly two airports.
sql_command: SELECT city FROM airports GROUP BY city HAVING count(*)  =  2

text_query: Which districts have at least two addresses?
sql_command: SELECT district FROM address GROUP BY district HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: Show all train names and times in stations in London in descending order by train time.
sql_command: SELECT T3.name ,  T3.time FROM train_station AS T1 JOIN station AS T2 ON T1.station_id  =  T2.station_id JOIN train AS T3 ON T3.train_id  =  T1.train_id WHERE T2.location  =  'London' ORDER BY T3.time DESC

text_query: How many countries has more than 2 car makers ?
sql_command: select count(*) from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid  =  t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*)  >  2

text_query: Show all statement id and the number of accounts for each statement.
sql_command: SELECT STATEMENT_ID ,  count(*) FROM Accounts GROUP BY STATEMENT_ID

text_query: How many airlines are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM airlines

text_query: Show the top 3 apartment type codes sorted by the average number of rooms in descending order.
sql_command: SELECT apt_type_code FROM Apartments GROUP BY apt_type_code ORDER BY avg(room_count) DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: List the asset id, details, make and model for every asset.
sql_command: SELECT asset_id ,  asset_details ,  asset_make ,  asset_model FROM Assets

text_query: List the studios of each film and the number of films produced by that studio.
sql_command: SELECT Studio ,  COUNT(*) FROM film GROUP BY Studio

text_query: Show the names of all the employees with role "HR".
sql_command: SELECT employee_name FROM Employees WHERE role_code  =  "HR"

text_query: Find the first name of students living in city PHL whose age is between 20 and 25.

text_query: What is the type of the document named "David CV"?

sql_command: SELECT T2.Party FROM election AS T1 JOIN party AS T2 ON T1.Party  =  T2.Party_ID WHERE T1.Committee  =  "Appropriations" INTERSECT SELECT T2.Party FROM election AS T1 JOIN party AS T2 ON T1.Party  =  T2.Party_ID WHERE T1.Committee  =  "Economic Matters"

text_query: Find the names of accounts whose checking balance is above the average checking balance, but savings balance is below the average savings balance.

text_query: What are the ids and names of all countries that either have more than 3 car makers or produce fiat model ?
sql_command: select t1.countryid ,  t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid  =  t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*)  >  3 union select t1.countryid ,  t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid  =  t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id  =  t3.maker where t3.model  =  'fiat';
