text_query: How many wines are produced at Robert Biale winery?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM WINE WHERE Winery  =  "Robert Biale"

text_query: Find the name and flag of ships that are not steered by any captain with Midshipman rank.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  flag FROM ship WHERE ship_id NOT IN (SELECT ship_id FROM captain WHERE rank  =  'Midshipman')

text_query: What are the clean and jerk score of the body builder with the highest total score?
sql_command: SELECT Clean_Jerk FROM body_builder ORDER BY Total DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the last name and office of the professor from the history department?
sql_command: SELECT T1.emp_lname ,  T2.prof_office FROM employee AS T1 JOIN professor AS T2 ON T1.emp_num  =  T2.emp_num JOIN department AS T3 ON T2.dept_code  =  T3.dept_code WHERE T3.dept_name  =  'History'

text_query: Who has a friend that is from new york city?
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM Person AS T1 JOIN PersonFriend AS T2 ON T1.name  =  T2.friend WHERE T1.city  =  'new york city'

text_query: Find the average age and number of male students (with sex M) from each city.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  avg(age) ,  city_code FROM student WHERE sex  =  'M' GROUP BY city_code

text_query: List the final tables made and the best finishes of poker players.
sql_command: SELECT Final_Table_Made ,  Best_Finish FROM poker_player

text_query: Show all calendar dates and day Numbers.
sql_command: SELECT calendar_date ,  day_Number FROM Ref_calendar

text_query: Which assets did not incur any fault log? List the asset model.
sql_command: SELECT asset_model FROM Assets WHERE asset_id NOT IN (SELECT asset_id FROM Fault_Log)

text_query: What is the average earnings of poker players?
sql_command: SELECT avg(Earnings) FROM poker_player

text_query: What is the average enrollment of schools?
sql_command: SELECT avg(Enrollment) FROM school

text_query: What are the contestant numbers and names of the contestants who had at least two votes?
sql_command: SELECT T1.contestant_number , T1.contestant_name FROM contestants AS T1 JOIN votes AS T2 ON T1.contestant_number  =  T2.contestant_number GROUP BY T1.contestant_number HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: Find courses that ran in Fall 2009 and in Spring 2010.
sql_command: SELECT course_id FROM SECTION WHERE semester  =  'Fall' AND YEAR  =  2009 INTERSECT SELECT course_id FROM SECTION WHERE semester  =  'Spring' AND YEAR  =  2010

text_query: How many schools are in the basketball match?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT school_id) FROM basketball_match

text_query: Count the number of trips that did not end in San Francisco city.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM trip AS T1 JOIN station AS T2 ON T1.end_station_id  =  T2.id WHERE T2.city !=  "San Francisco"

text_query: How many car models are produced in the usa?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM MODEL_LIST AS T1 JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T2 ON T1.Maker  =  T2.Id JOIN COUNTRIES AS T3 ON T2.Country  =  T3.CountryId WHERE T3.CountryName  =  'usa';

text_query: Find the first names of professors who are teaching more than one class.
sql_command: SELECT T2.emp_fname FROM CLASS AS T1 JOIN employee AS T2 ON T1.prof_num  =  T2.emp_num GROUP BY T1.prof_num HAVING count(*)  >  1

text_query: Find the names of patients who are not using the medication of Procrastin-X.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM patient EXCEPT SELECT T1.name FROM patient AS T1 JOIN Prescribes AS T2 ON T2.Patient  =  T1.SSN JOIN Medication AS T3 ON T2.Medication  =  T3.Code WHERE T3.name  =  'Procrastin-X'

text_query: find the id, name and age for visitors who visited some museums more than once.
sql_command: SELECT t1.id ,  t1.name ,  t1.age FROM visitor AS t1 JOIN visit AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.visitor_id GROUP BY t1.id HAVING count(*)  >  1

text_query: List the grape, appelation and name of wines whose score is higher than 93 ordered by Name.
sql_command: SELECT Grape ,  Appelation ,  Name FROM WINE WHERE Score  >  93 ORDER BY Name

text_query: Find the production code and channel of the most recently aired cartoon .
sql_command: select production_code ,  channel from cartoon order by original_air_date desc limit 1

text_query: Find the name and checking balance of the account with the lowest saving balance.
sql_command: SELECT T2.balance ,  T1.name FROM accounts AS T1 JOIN checking AS T2 ON T1.custid  =  T2.custid JOIN savings AS T3 ON T1.custid  =  T3.custid ORDER BY T3.balance LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the first name of the professor who is teaching two courses with code CIS-220 and QM-261.
sql_command: SELECT T1.emp_fname FROM employee AS T1 JOIN CLASS AS T2 ON T1.emp_num  =  T2.prof_num WHERE crs_code  =  'CIS-220' INTERSECT SELECT T1.emp_fname FROM employee AS T1 JOIN CLASS AS T2 ON T1.emp_num  =  T2.prof_num WHERE crs_code  =  'QM-261'

text_query: Which destination has least number of flights?
sql_command: SELECT destination FROM Flight GROUP BY destination ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

text_query: How many video game types exist?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT gtype) FROM Video_games

text_query: Show the protein name and the institution name.
sql_command: SELECT T2.protein_name ,  T1.institution FROM institution AS T1 JOIN protein AS T2 ON T1.institution_id  =  T2.institution_id

text_query: Find the name of bank branch that provided the greatest total amount of loans to customers with credit score is less than 100.
sql_command: SELECT T2.bname FROM loan AS T1 JOIN bank AS T2 ON T1.branch_id  =  T2.branch_id JOIN customer AS T3 ON T1.cust_id  =  T3.cust_id WHERE T3.credit_score  <  100 GROUP BY T2.bname ORDER BY sum(T1.amount) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show all student IDs with more than total 10 hours per week on all sports played.
sql_command: SELECT StuID FROM Sportsinfo GROUP BY StuID HAVING sum(hoursperweek)  >  10

text_query: Find the name and email of the user whose name contains the word ‘Swift’.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  email FROM user_profiles WHERE name LIKE '%Swift%'

text_query: Find the state of the college which player Charles is attending.
sql_command: SELECT T1.state FROM college AS T1 JOIN tryout AS T2 ON T1.cName  =  T2.cName JOIN player AS T3 ON T2.pID  =  T3.pID WHERE T3.pName  =  'Charles'

text_query: What are the highest and lowest prices of products, grouped by and alphabetically ordered by product type?
sql_command: SELECT max(product_price) ,  min(product_price) ,  product_type_code FROM products GROUP BY product_type_code ORDER BY product_type_code

text_query: Find the name of the products that are not using the most frequently-used max page size.
sql_command: SELECT product FROM product WHERE product != (SELECT max_page_size FROM product GROUP BY max_page_size ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1)

text_query: What is the average price for products?
sql_command: SELECT avg(Product_Price) FROM Products

text_query: Show project ids and the number of documents in each project.
sql_command: SELECT project_id ,  count(*) FROM Documents GROUP BY project_id

text_query: Find the name of dorms only for female (F gender).
sql_command: SELECT dorm_name FROM dorm WHERE gender  =  'F'

text_query: Find the total amount of loans provided by bank branches in the state of New York.
sql_command: SELECT sum(T2.amount) FROM bank AS T1 JOIN loan AS T2 ON T1.branch_id  =  T2.branch_id WHERE T1.state  =  'New York'

text_query: Find the female friends of Alice.
sql_command: SELECT T2.friend FROM Person AS T1 JOIN PersonFriend AS T2 ON T1.name  =  T2.friend WHERE T2.name  =  'Alice' AND T1.gender  =  'female'

text_query: What are all locations of train stations?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT LOCATION FROM station

text_query: What is the most used instrument?
sql_command: SELECT instrument FROM instruments GROUP BY instrument ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the three most expensive procedures.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM procedures ORDER BY cost LIMIT 3

text_query: Show the document name and the document date for all documents on project with details 'Graph Database project'.
sql_command: SELECT document_name ,  document_date FROM Documents AS T1 JOIN projects AS T2 ON T1.project_id  =  T2.project_id WHERE T2.project_details  =  'Graph Database project'

text_query: Find the major and age of students who do not have a cat pet.
sql_command: SELECT major ,  age FROM student WHERE stuid NOT IN (SELECT T1.stuid FROM student AS T1 JOIN has_pet AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid JOIN pets AS T3 ON T3.petid  =  T2.petid WHERE T3.pettype  =  'cat')

text_query: Find the name and rank points of the winner who won the most times.
sql_command: SELECT winner_name ,  winner_rank_points FROM matches GROUP BY winner_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the name of ships in ascending order of tonnage.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM ship ORDER BY Tonnage ASC

text_query: list all female (sex is F) candidate names in the alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT t1.name FROM people AS t1 JOIN candidate AS t2 ON t1.people_id  =  t2.people_id WHERE t1.sex  =  'F' ORDER BY t1.name

text_query: Show the distinct position of players from college UCLA or Duke.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT POSITION FROM match_season WHERE College  =  "UCLA" OR College  =  "Duke"

text_query: What are the ids of all students for courses and what are the names of those courses?
sql_command: SELECT T1.student_id ,  T2.course_name FROM student_course_registrations AS T1 JOIN courses AS T2 ON T1.course_id = T2.course_id

text_query: List names of all teams in the basketball competition, ordered by all home scores in descending order.
sql_command: SELECT team_name FROM basketball_match ORDER BY All_Home DESC

text_query: What are names for top three branches with most number of membership?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM branch ORDER BY membership_amount DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: List the project details of the projects with the research outcome described with the substring 'Published'.
sql_command: SELECT T1.project_details FROM Projects AS T1 JOIN Project_outcomes AS T2 ON T1.project_id  =  T2.project_id JOIN Research_outcomes AS T3 ON T2.outcome_code  =  T3.outcome_code WHERE T3.outcome_description LIKE '%Published%'

text_query: Show ids for all employees who don't have a certificate.
sql_command: SELECT eid FROM Employee EXCEPT SELECT eid FROM Certificate

text_query: What is the average fastest lap speed in race named 'Monaco Grand Prix' in 2008 ?
sql_command: SELECT avg(T2.fastestlapspeed) FROM races AS T1 JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.raceid = T2.raceid WHERE T1.year = 2008 AND T1.name = "Monaco Grand Prix"

text_query: Who is the first student to register? List the first name, middle name and last name.
sql_command: SELECT first_name ,  middle_name ,  last_name FROM Students ORDER BY date_first_registered ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the role code with the largest number of employees?
sql_command: SELECT role_code FROM Employees GROUP BY role_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name of the dorm with the largest capacity.
sql_command: SELECT dorm_name FROM dorm ORDER BY student_capacity DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the average height and weight for all males (sex is M).
sql_command: SELECT avg(height) ,  avg(weight) FROM people WHERE sex  =  'M'

text_query: Which allergy type has least number of allergies?
sql_command: SELECT allergytype FROM Allergy_type GROUP BY allergytype ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the minimum, average, maximum order quantity of all invoices.
sql_command: SELECT min(Order_Quantity) ,  avg(Order_Quantity) ,  max(Order_Quantity) FROM INVOICES

text_query: Find the name of the most expensive product.
sql_command: SELECT product_name FROM products ORDER BY product_price DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the first names of all the authors who have written a paper with title containing the word "Functional".
sql_command: SELECT t1.fname FROM authors AS t1 JOIN authorship AS t2 ON t1.authid  =  t2.authid JOIN papers AS t3 ON t2.paperid  =  t3.paperid WHERE t3.title LIKE "%Functional%"

text_query: Show the transaction type descriptions and dates if the share count is smaller than 10.
sql_command: SELECT T1.transaction_type_description ,  T2.date_of_transaction FROM Ref_Transaction_Types AS T1 JOIN TRANSACTIONS AS T2 ON T1.transaction_type_code  =  T2.transaction_type_code WHERE T2.share_count  <  10

text_query: Find the name of students who have taken the prerequisite course of the course with title International Finance.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM student AS T1 JOIN takes AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.id WHERE T2.course_id IN (SELECT T4.prereq_id FROM course AS T3 JOIN prereq AS T4 ON T3.course_id  =  T4.course_id WHERE T3.title  =  'International Finance')

text_query: What are all the distinct last names of all the engineers?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT last_name FROM Maintenance_Engineers

text_query: Return the name and id of the furniture with the highest market rate.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  furniture_id FROM furniture ORDER BY market_rate DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the name of all playlist.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM playlists;

text_query: What is the storm name and max speed which affected the greatest number of regions?
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  T1.max_speed FROM storm AS T1 JOIN affected_region AS T2 ON T1.storm_id  =  T2.storm_id GROUP BY T1.storm_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the description of the club named "Tennis Club"?
sql_command: SELECT clubdesc FROM club WHERE clubname  =  "Tennis Club"

text_query: List the section_name in reversed lexicographical order.
sql_command: SELECT section_name FROM Sections ORDER BY section_name DESC

text_query: Find the address of all customers that live in Germany and have invoice.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Address FROM CUSTOMER AS T1 JOIN INVOICE AS T2 ON T1.CustomerId  =  T2.CustomerId WHERE T1.country  =  "Germany"

text_query: Which game type has most number of games?
sql_command: SELECT gtype FROM Video_games GROUP BY gtype ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: find the number of distinct country codes of all players.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT country_code) FROM players

text_query: Show the distinct countries of managers.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT Country FROM manager

text_query: Find the name of amenities Smith Hall dorm have. ordered the results by amenity names.
sql_command: SELECT T3.amenity_name FROM dorm AS T1 JOIN has_amenity AS T2 ON T1.dormid  =  T2.dormid JOIN dorm_amenity AS T3 ON T2.amenid  =  T3.amenid WHERE T1.dorm_name  =  'Smith Hall' ORDER BY T3.amenity_name

text_query: Where does the customer with the first name Linda live? And what is her email?
sql_command: SELECT T2.address ,  T1.email FROM customer AS T1 JOIN address AS T2 ON T2.address_id  =  T1.address_id WHERE T1.first_name  =  'LINDA'

text_query: Find the model of the car whose weight is below the average weight.
sql_command: SELECT T1.model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id WHERE T2.Weight  <  (SELECT avg(Weight) FROM CARS_DATA)

text_query: What is the total surface area of the continents Asia and Europe?
sql_command: SELECT sum(SurfaceArea) FROM country WHERE Continent  =  "Asia" OR Continent  =  "Europe"

text_query: List the names, color descriptions and product descriptions of products with category "Herbs".
sql_command: SELECT T1.product_name ,  T2.color_description ,  T1.product_description FROM products AS T1 JOIN Ref_colors AS T2 ON T1.color_code  =  T2.color_code WHERE product_category_code  =  "Herbs"

text_query: Find the last name of the staff member who processed the complaint of the cheapest product.
sql_command: SELECT t1.last_name FROM staff AS t1 JOIN complaints AS t2 ON t1.staff_id  =  t2.staff_id JOIN products AS t3 ON t2.product_id  =  t3.product_id ORDER BY t3.product_price LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the number of different products that are produced by companies at different headquarter cities.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT T1.name) ,  T2.Headquarter FROM products AS T1 JOIN manufacturers AS T2 ON T1.Manufacturer  =  T2.code GROUP BY T2.Headquarter

text_query: What is the receipt date of the document with id 3?
sql_command: SELECT receipt_date FROM Documents WHERE document_id = 3;

text_query: What are the average amount purchased and value purchased for the supplier who supplies the most products.
sql_command: SELECT avg(total_amount_purchased) ,  avg(total_value_purchased) FROM Product_Suppliers WHERE supplier_id  =  (SELECT supplier_id FROM Product_Suppliers GROUP BY supplier_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1)

text_query: Which models are lighter than 3500 but not built by the 'Ford Motor Company'?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.model FROM MODEL_LIST AS T1 JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T2 ON T1.Model  =  T2.Model JOIN CARS_DATA AS T3 ON T2.MakeId  =  T3.Id JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T4 ON T1.Maker  =  T4.Id WHERE T3.weight  <  3500 AND T4.FullName != 'Ford Motor Company';

text_query: List all budget type codes and descriptions.
sql_command: SELECT budget_type_code ,  budget_type_description FROM Ref_budget_codes

text_query: List the name of tracks belongs to genre Rock and whose media type is MPEG audio file.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM genres AS T1 JOIN tracks AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.genre_id JOIN media_types AS T3 ON T3.id = T2.media_type_id WHERE T1.name = "Rock" AND T3.name = "MPEG audio file";

text_query: Show different locations of railways along with the corresponding number of railways at each location.
sql_command: SELECT LOCATION ,  COUNT(*) FROM railway GROUP BY LOCATION

text_query: What is the name of the museum that had no visitor yet?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM museum WHERE Museum_ID NOT IN (SELECT museum_id FROM visit)

text_query: What is the document id and name with greatest number of paragraphs?
sql_command: SELECT T1.document_id ,  T2.document_name FROM Paragraphs AS T1 JOIN Documents AS T2 ON T1.document_id  =  T2.document_id GROUP BY T1.document_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the degrees conferred in "San Francisco State University" in 2001.
sql_command: SELECT degrees FROM campuses AS T1 JOIN degrees AS T2 ON t1.id  =  t2.campus WHERE t1.campus  =  "San Francisco State University" AND t2.year  =  2001

text_query: How many distinct birth places are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT Birth_Place) FROM people

text_query: Return the gender and name of artist who produced the song with the lowest resolution.
sql_command: SELECT T1.gender ,  T1.artist_name FROM artist AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.artist_name  =  T2.artist_name ORDER BY T2.resolution LIMIT 1

text_query: List the countries that have more than one mountain.
sql_command: SELECT Country FROM mountain GROUP BY Country HAVING COUNT(*)  >  1

text_query: How many artworks are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM artwork

text_query: Show name, country, age for all singers ordered by age from the oldest to the youngest.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  country ,  age FROM singer ORDER BY age DESC

text_query: What are the staff ids and genders of all staffs whose job title is Department Manager?
sql_command: SELECT T1.staff_id ,  T1.staff_gender FROM staff AS T1 JOIN staff_department_assignments AS T2 ON T1.staff_id  =  T2.staff_id WHERE T2.job_title_code  =  "Department Manager"

text_query: Find all the stage positions of the musicians with first name "Solveig"
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.stageposition FROM Performance AS T1 JOIN Band AS T2 ON T1.bandmate  =  T2.id WHERE Firstname  =  "Solveig"

text_query: What are the names of directors who directed movies with 5 star rating? Also return the title of these movies.
sql_command: SELECT T1.director ,  T1.title FROM Movie AS T1 JOIN Rating AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID WHERE T2.stars  =  5

text_query: Show the names of companies and the number of employees they have
sql_command: SELECT T3.Name ,  COUNT(*) FROM employment AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID JOIN company AS T3 ON T1.Company_ID  =  T3.Company_ID GROUP BY T3.Name

text_query: What is the average latitude and longitude of the starting points of all trips?
sql_command: SELECT avg(T1.lat) ,  avg(T1.long) FROM station AS T1 JOIN trip AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.start_station_id

text_query: Return the cell phone number and email address for all students.
sql_command: SELECT cell_mobile_number ,  email_address FROM STUDENTS

text_query: Find the names of reviewers who had given higher than 3 star ratings.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Reviewer AS T2 ON T1.rID  =  T2.rID WHERE T1.stars  >  3

text_query: What are the names of parties with at least 2 events?
sql_command: SELECT T2.party_name FROM party_events AS T1 JOIN party AS T2 ON T1.party_id  =  T2.party_id GROUP BY T1.party_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: How many different results are there for the battles?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT RESULT) FROM battle

text_query: Show cinema name, film title, date, and price for each record in schedule.
sql_command: SELECT T3.name ,  T2.title ,  T1.date ,  T1.price FROM schedule AS T1 JOIN film AS T2 ON T1.film_id  =  T2.film_id JOIN cinema AS T3 ON T1.cinema_id  =  T3.cinema_id

text_query: What is the unit of measurement of product named "cumin"?
sql_command: SELECT t2.unit_of_measure FROM products AS t1 JOIN ref_product_categories AS t2 ON t1.product_category_code  =  t2.product_category_code WHERE t1.product_name  =  "cumin"

text_query: List the first names of people in alphabetical order?
sql_command: SELECT first_name FROM people ORDER BY first_name

text_query: Show the number of projects.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Projects

text_query: Which owner has paid for the most treatments on his or her dogs? List the owner id and last name.
sql_command: SELECT T1.owner_id ,  T1.last_name FROM Owners AS T1 JOIN Dogs AS T2 ON T1.owner_id  =  T2.owner_id JOIN Treatments AS T3 ON T2.dog_id  =  T3.dog_id GROUP BY T1.owner_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the most popular full name of the actors?
sql_command: SELECT first_name ,  last_name FROM actor GROUP BY first_name ,  last_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: list all the names of programs, ordering by launch time.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM program ORDER BY launch

text_query: List the problem id and log id which are assigned to the staff named Rylan Homenick.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T2.problem_id ,  T2.problem_log_id FROM staff AS T1 JOIN problem_log AS T2 ON T1.staff_id = T2.assigned_to_staff_id WHERE T1.staff_first_name = "Rylan" AND T1.staff_last_name = "Homenick"

text_query: List all the username and passwords of users with the most popular role.
sql_command: SELECT user_name ,  password FROM users GROUP BY role_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many companies were created by Andy?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM manufacturers WHERE founder  =  'Andy'

text_query: Show the apartment type codes and apartment numbers in the buildings managed by "Kyle".
sql_command: SELECT T2.apt_type_code ,  T2.apt_number FROM Apartment_Buildings AS T1 JOIN Apartments AS T2 ON T1.building_id  =  T2.building_id WHERE T1.building_manager  =  "Kyle"

text_query: Show all school names in alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT school_name FROM school ORDER BY school_name

text_query: What are the descriptions of the service types with product price above 100?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Service_Type_Description FROM Ref_Service_Types AS T1 JOIN Services AS T2 ON T1.Service_Type_Code  =  T2.Service_Type_Code WHERE T2.Product_Price  >  100

text_query: List the names of entrepreneurs and their companies in descending order of money requested?
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name ,  T1.Company FROM entrepreneur AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID ORDER BY T1.Money_Requested

text_query: What is the number of distinct cities the stations are located at?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT city) FROM station

text_query: Find the number of professors with a Ph.D. degree in each department.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  dept_code FROM professor WHERE prof_high_degree  =  'Ph.D.' GROUP BY dept_code

text_query: List the names of companies in descending order of market value.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM Companies ORDER BY Market_Value_billion DESC

text_query: How many items in inventory does store 1 have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM inventory WHERE store_id  =  1

text_query: List all player names who have an overall rating higher than the average.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.player_name FROM Player AS T1 JOIN Player_Attributes AS T2 ON T1.player_api_id = T2.player_api_id WHERE T2.overall_rating  >  ( SELECT avg(overall_rating) FROM Player_Attributes )

text_query: Find the name of the teacher who teaches the largest number of students.
sql_command: SELECT T2.firstname ,  T2.lastname FROM list AS T1 JOIN teachers AS T2 ON T1.classroom  =  T2.classroom GROUP BY T2.firstname ,  T2.lastname ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the names of players that do not have coaches.
sql_command: SELECT Player_name FROM player WHERE Player_ID NOT IN (SELECT Player_ID FROM player_coach)

text_query: List the names of phones that are not on any market.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM phone WHERE Phone_id NOT IN (SELECT Phone_ID FROM phone_market)

text_query: Show the institution type with an institution founded after 1990 and an institution with at least 1000 enrollment.
sql_command: SELECT TYPE FROM institution WHERE founded  >  1990 AND enrollment  >=  1000

text_query: What is the joined year of the pilot of the highest rank?
sql_command: SELECT Join_Year FROM pilot ORDER BY Rank ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the number of international and domestic passengers of the airport named London "Heathrow"?
sql_command: SELECT International_Passengers ,  Domestic_Passengers FROM airport WHERE Airport_Name  =  "London Heathrow"

text_query: Find the number of stores in each city.
sql_command: SELECT t3.headquartered_city ,  count(*) FROM store AS t1 JOIN store_district AS t2 ON t1.store_id  =  t2.store_id JOIN district AS t3 ON t2.district_id  =  t3.district_id GROUP BY t3.headquartered_city

text_query: Show different occupations along with the number of players in each occupation.
sql_command: SELECT Occupation ,  COUNT(*) FROM player GROUP BY Occupation

text_query: Show the first year and last year of parties with theme "Spring" or "Teqnology".
sql_command: SELECT First_year ,  Last_year FROM party WHERE Party_Theme  =  "Spring" OR Party_Theme  =  "Teqnology"

text_query: List the vote ids, phone numbers and states of all votes.
sql_command: SELECT vote_id ,  phone_number ,  state FROM votes

text_query: Find the maximum and minimum monthly rental for all student addresses.
sql_command: SELECT max(monthly_rental) ,  min(monthly_rental) FROM Student_Addresses

text_query: Find the full names of faculties who are members of department with department number 520.

text_query: What is the attribute data type of the attribute with name "Green"?

text_query: List all people names in the order of their date of birth from old to young.

text_query: Show the denomination shared by schools founded before 1890 and schools founded after 1900

sql_command: SELECT decor FROM Rooms WHERE roomName  =  "Recluse and defiance";

text_query: Show the stadium name and the number of concerts in each stadium.

text_query: find the name of employee who was awarded the most times in the evaluation.

text_query: Show party names and the number of events for each party.
sql_command: SELECT T2.party_name ,  count(*) FROM party_events AS T1 JOIN party AS T2 ON T1.party_id  =  T2.party_id GROUP BY T1.party_id

sql_command: SELECT T1.killed ,  T1.injured FROM death AS T1 JOIN ship AS t2 ON T1.caused_by_ship_id  =  T2.id WHERE T2.tonnage  =  't'

text_query: Which professionals have done at least two types of treatments? List the professional id and cell phone.

text_query: List the hosts of performances in ascending order of attendance.
sql_command: SELECT HOST FROM performance ORDER BY Attendance ASC

text_query: What is the phone number and postal code of the address 1031 Daugavpils Parkway?
sql_command: SELECT phone ,  postal_code FROM address WHERE address  =  '1031 Daugavpils Parkway'

text_query: Find the component amounts and names of all furnitures that have more than 10 components.
sql_command: SELECT Num_of_Component ,  name FROM furniture WHERE Num_of_Component  >  10

text_query: How many countries are there in total?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM country

text_query: What is the average number of cities of markets with low film market estimate bigger than 10000?
sql_command: SELECT avg(T2.Number_cities) FROM film_market_estimation AS T1 JOIN market AS T2 ON T1.Market_ID  =  T2.Market_ID WHERE T1.Low_Estimate  >  10000

text_query: Find the top 3 artists who have the largest number of songs works whose language is Bangla.
sql_command: SELECT T1.artist_name FROM artist AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.artist_name  =  T2.artist_name WHERE T2.languages  =  "bangla" GROUP BY T2.artist_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: Show the ids of the students who don't participate in any activity.
sql_command: SELECT StuID FROM Student EXCEPT SELECT StuID FROM Participates_in

text_query: Find the name of projects that require between 100 and 300 hours of work.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM projects WHERE hours BETWEEN 100 AND 300

text_query: Find the number of distinct type of pets.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT pettype) FROM pets

text_query: What is the race class with most number of races.
sql_command: SELECT CLASS FROM race GROUP BY CLASS ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the most common country across members.
sql_command: SELECT Country FROM member GROUP BY Country ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many main stream browsers whose market share is at least 5 exist?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM browser WHERE market_share  >=  5

text_query: Find the code of city where most of students are living in.
sql_command: SELECT city_code FROM student GROUP BY city_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show all distinct template type codes for all templates.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT template_type_code FROM Templates

text_query: Find the number of universities that have over a 20000 enrollment size for each affiliation type.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  affiliation FROM university WHERE enrollment  >  20000 GROUP BY affiliation

text_query: What are the names and year of construction for the mills of 'Grondzeiler' type?
sql_command: SELECT name ,  built_year FROM mill WHERE TYPE  =  'Grondzeiler'

text_query: Show the product type and name for the products with price higher than 1000 or lower than 500.
sql_command: SELECT product_type_code ,  product_name FROM products WHERE product_price  >  1000 OR product_price  <  500

text_query: Which address holds the most number of students currently? List the address id and all lines.
sql_command: SELECT T1.address_id ,  T1.line_1 ,  T1.line_2 FROM Addresses AS T1 JOIN Students AS T2 ON T1.address_id  =  T2.current_address_id GROUP BY T1.address_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the famous titles of the artist "Triumfall"?
sql_command: SELECT Famous_Title FROM artist WHERE Artist  =  "Triumfall"

text_query: Who is the earliest graduate of the school? List the first name, middle name and last name.
sql_command: SELECT first_name ,  middle_name ,  last_name FROM Students ORDER BY date_left ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many car models were produced by the maker with full name American Motor Company?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker WHERE T1.FullName  =  'American Motor Company';

text_query: Show the company name and the main industry for all companies whose headquarters are not from USA.
sql_command: SELECT company ,  main_industry FROM company WHERE headquarters != 'USA'

text_query: Find the papers which have "Olin Shivers" as an author.
sql_command: SELECT t3.title FROM authors AS t1 JOIN authorship AS t2 ON t1.authid  =  t2.authid JOIN papers AS t3 ON t2.paperid  =  t3.paperid WHERE t1.fname  =  "Olin" AND t1.lname  =  "Shivers"

text_query: Find the average access counts of documents with functional area "Acknowledgement".
sql_command: SELECT avg(t1.access_count) FROM documents AS t1 JOIN document_functional_areas AS t2 ON t1.document_code  =  t2.document_code JOIN functional_areas AS t3 ON t2.functional_area_code  =  t3.functional_area_code WHERE t3.functional_area_description  =  "Acknowledgement"

text_query: Show all video game types.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT gtype FROM Video_games

text_query: Find the name all districts with city area greater than 10 or population larger than 100000
sql_command: SELECT district_name FROM district WHERE city_area  >  10 OR City_Population  >  100000

text_query: Find all the papers published by "Aaron Turon".
sql_command: SELECT t3.title FROM authors AS t1 JOIN authorship AS t2 ON t1.authid  =  t2.authid JOIN papers AS t3 ON t2.paperid  =  t3.paperid WHERE  t1.fname  =  "Aaron" AND t1.lname  =  "Turon"

text_query: List all information about college sorted by enrollment number in the ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT * FROM College ORDER BY enr

text_query: What are the average profits of companies?
sql_command: SELECT avg(Profits_billion) FROM Companies

text_query: List all countries of markets in descending order of number of cities.
sql_command: SELECT Country FROM market ORDER BY Number_cities DESC

text_query: What is the average number of attendance at home games for each year?
sql_command: SELECT YEAR ,  avg(attendance) FROM home_game GROUP BY YEAR;

text_query: Show the most common headquarter for companies.
sql_command: SELECT Headquarters FROM company GROUP BY Headquarters ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are airport names at City 'Aberdeen'?
sql_command: SELECT AirportName FROM AIRPORTS WHERE City = "Aberdeen"

text_query: find all dependent names who have a spouse relation with some employee.
sql_command: SELECT Dependent_name FROM dependent WHERE relationship  =  'Spouse'

text_query: Show all investor details.
sql_command: SELECT Investor_details FROM INVESTORS

text_query: What are the codes of countries where Spanish is spoken by the largest percentage of people?
sql_command: SELECT CountryCode ,  max(Percentage) FROM countrylanguage WHERE LANGUAGE  =  "Spanish" GROUP BY CountryCode

text_query: Find the last name of the student who has a cat that is age 3.
sql_command: SELECT T1.lname FROM student AS T1 JOIN has_pet AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid JOIN pets AS T3 ON T3.petid  =  T2.petid WHERE T3.pet_age  =  3 AND T3.pettype  =  'cat'

text_query: What are the id of songs whose format is mp3.
sql_command: SELECT f_id FROM files WHERE formats  =  "mp3"

text_query: Find the number and time of the train that goes from Chennai to Guruvayur.
sql_command: SELECT train_number ,  TIME FROM train WHERE origin  =  'Chennai' AND destination  =  'Guruvayur'

text_query: Show names for all regions except for Denmark.
sql_command: SELECT region_name FROM region WHERE region_name != 'Denmark'

text_query: How many technicians are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM technician

text_query: Show the years, book titles, and publishers for all books, in descending order by year.
sql_command: SELECT YEAR ,  book_title ,  publisher FROM book_club ORDER BY YEAR DESC

text_query: In which year did the least people enter hall of fame?
sql_command: SELECT yearid FROM hall_of_fame GROUP BY yearid ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1;

text_query: What are the types of film market estimations in year 1995?
sql_command: SELECT TYPE FROM film_market_estimation WHERE YEAR  =  1995

text_query: Which vocal type has the band mate with first name "Marianne" played the most?
sql_command: SELECT TYPE FROM vocals AS T1 JOIN band AS T2 ON T1.bandmate  =  T2.id WHERE firstname  =  "Marianne" GROUP BY TYPE ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Which kind of policy type was chosen by the most customers?
sql_command: SELECT Policy_Type_Code FROM Customer_Policies GROUP BY Policy_Type_Code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many cars have more than 4 cylinders?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM CARS_DATA WHERE Cylinders  >  4;

text_query: Show all the locations where some cinemas were opened in both year 2010 and year 2011.
sql_command: SELECT LOCATION FROM cinema WHERE openning_year  =  2010 INTERSECT SELECT LOCATION FROM cinema WHERE openning_year  =  2011

text_query: Find all details for each swimmer.
sql_command: SELECT * FROM swimmer

text_query: Find the number of items that did not receive any review.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM item WHERE i_id NOT IN (SELECT i_id FROM review)

text_query: Which department has the lowest budget?
sql_command: SELECT dept_name FROM department ORDER BY budget LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the first and last name of the author(s) who wrote the paper "Nameless, Painless".
sql_command: SELECT t1.fname ,  t1.lname FROM authors AS t1 JOIN authorship AS t2 ON t1.authid  =  t2.authid JOIN papers AS t3 ON t2.paperid  =  t3.paperid WHERE t3.title  =  "Nameless ,  Painless"

text_query: which course has most number of registered students?
sql_command: SELECT T1.course_name FROM courses AS T1 JOIN student_course_registrations AS T2 ON T1.course_id = T2.course_Id GROUP BY T1.course_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many albums are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM ALBUM

text_query: Show the order ids and the number of invoices for each order.
sql_command: SELECT order_id ,  count(*) FROM Invoices GROUP BY order_id

text_query: Show the number of transactions for different investors.
sql_command: SELECT investor_id ,  COUNT(*) FROM TRANSACTIONS GROUP BY investor_id

text_query: List the main industry with highest total market value and its number of companies.
sql_command: SELECT main_industry ,  count(*) FROM company GROUP BY main_industry ORDER BY sum(market_value) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the document ids of documents with the status done and type Paper, which not shipped by the shipping agent named USPS.
sql_command: SELECT document_id FROM Documents WHERE document_status_code  =  "done" AND document_type_code = "Paper" EXCEPT SELECT document_id FROM Documents JOIN Ref_Shipping_Agents ON Documents.shipping_agent_code = Ref_Shipping_Agents.shipping_agent_code WHERE Ref_Shipping_Agents.shipping_agent_name = "USPS";

text_query: Find the number of students in one classroom.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  classroom FROM list GROUP BY classroom

text_query: what is id of students who registered some courses but the least number of courses in these students?
sql_command: SELECT student_id FROM student_course_registrations GROUP BY student_id ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the names of goods that receive a rating of 10.
sql_command: SELECT T1.title FROM item AS T1 JOIN review AS T2 ON T1.i_id  =  T2.i_id WHERE T2.rating  =  10

text_query: Find the name and id of the good with the highest average rank.
sql_command: SELECT T1.title ,  T1.i_id FROM item AS T1 JOIN review AS T2 ON T1.i_id  =  T2.i_id GROUP BY T2.i_id ORDER BY avg(T2.rank) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the lot details of lots associated with transactions whose share count is bigger than 100 and whose type code is "PUR"?
sql_command: SELECT T1.lot_details FROM LOTS AS T1 JOIN TRANSACTIONS_LOTS AS T2 ON  T1.lot_id  =  T2.transaction_id JOIN TRANSACTIONS AS T3 ON T2.transaction_id  =  T3.transaction_id WHERE T3.share_count  >  100 AND T3.transaction_type_code  =  "PUR"

text_query: For each Orange county campus, report the number of degrees granted after 2000.
sql_command: SELECT T1.campus ,  sum(T2.degrees) FROM campuses AS T1 JOIN degrees AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.campus WHERE T1.county  =  "Orange" AND T2.year  >=  2000 GROUP BY T1.campus

text_query: what are the details of the cmi masters that have the cross reference code 'Tax'?
sql_command: SELECT T1.cmi_details FROM Customer_Master_Index AS T1 JOIN CMI_Cross_References AS T2 ON T1.master_customer_id  =  T2.master_customer_id WHERE T2.source_system_code  =  'Tax'

text_query: List the id of students who never attends courses?
sql_command: SELECT student_id FROM students WHERE student_id NOT IN (SELECT student_id FROM student_course_attendance)

text_query: Find the movies with the highest average rating. Return the movie titles and average rating.
sql_command: SELECT T2.title ,  avg(T1.stars) FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID GROUP BY T1.mID ORDER BY avg(T1.stars) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name and capacity of the stadium where the event named "World Junior" happened.
sql_command: SELECT t1.name ,  t1.capacity FROM stadium AS t1 JOIN event AS t2 ON t1.id  =  t2.stadium_id WHERE t2.name  =  'World Junior'

text_query: Find the names of users who have more than one tweet.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM user_profiles AS T1 JOIN tweets AS T2 ON T1.uid  =  T2.uid GROUP BY T2.uid HAVING count(*)  >  1

text_query: Show names of technicians and series of machines they are assigned to repair.
sql_command: SELECT T3.Name ,  T2.Machine_series FROM repair_assignment AS T1 JOIN machine AS T2 ON T1.machine_id  =  T2.machine_id JOIN technician AS T3 ON T1.technician_ID  =  T3.technician_ID

text_query: Show the first name, last name, and phone number for all female faculty members.
sql_command: SELECT Fname ,  Lname ,  phone FROM Faculty WHERE Sex  =  'F'

text_query: What are the id and names of the countries which have more than 3 car makers or produce the 'fiat' model?
sql_command: SELECT T1.countryId ,  T1.CountryName FROM Countries AS T1 JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T2 ON T1.CountryId  =  T2.Country GROUP BY T1.countryId HAVING count(*)  >  3 UNION SELECT T1.countryId ,  T1.CountryName FROM Countries AS T1 JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T2 ON T1.CountryId  =  T2.Country JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T3 ON T2.Id  =  T3.Maker WHERE T3.Model  =  'fiat';

text_query: What is the air date of TV series with Episode "A Love of a Lifetime"?
sql_command: SELECT Air_Date FROM TV_series WHERE Episode = "A Love of a Lifetime";

text_query: Which city has the least number of customers whose type code is "Good Credit Rating"?
sql_command: SELECT town_city FROM customers WHERE customer_type_code  =  "Good Credit Rating" GROUP BY town_city ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the premise type and address type code for all customer addresses.
sql_command: SELECT T2.premises_type ,  T1.address_type_code FROM customer_addresses AS T1 JOIN premises AS T2 ON T1.premise_id  =  T2.premise_id

text_query: Find the number of complaints with Product Failure type for each complaint status.
sql_command: SELECT complaint_status_code ,  count(*) FROM complaints WHERE complaint_type_code  =  "Product Failure" GROUP BY complaint_status_code

text_query: Show the people that have been comptroller the most times and the corresponding number of times.
sql_command: SELECT Comptroller ,  COUNT(*) FROM party GROUP BY Comptroller ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: list the first and last names, and the addresses of all employees in the ascending order of their birth date.
sql_command: SELECT fname ,  lname ,  address FROM employee ORDER BY Bdate

text_query: Show the company of the tallest entrepreneur.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Company FROM entrepreneur AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID ORDER BY T2.Height DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the total credits of all classes offered by each department.
sql_command: SELECT sum(T1.crs_credit) ,  T1.dept_code FROM course AS T1 JOIN CLASS AS T2 ON T1.crs_code  =  T2.crs_code GROUP BY T1.dept_code

text_query: List the phone hardware model and company name for the phones whose screen usage in kb is between 10 and 15.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T2.Hardware_Model_name , T2.Company_name FROM screen_mode AS T1 JOIN phone AS T2 ON T1.Graphics_mode = T2.screen_mode WHERE T1.used_kb BETWEEN 10 AND 15;

text_query: Show ids for all documents with budget types described as 'Government'.
sql_command: SELECT T1.document_id FROM Documents_with_expenses AS T1 JOIN Ref_Budget_Codes AS T2 ON T1.Budget_Type_code  =  T2.Budget_Type_code WHERE T2.budget_type_Description  =  "Government"

text_query: when is the hire date for those employees whose first name does not containing the letter M?
sql_command: SELECT hire_date FROM employees WHERE first_name NOT LIKE '%M%'

text_query: Show customer ids who don't have an account.
sql_command: SELECT customer_id FROM Customers EXCEPT SELECT customer_id FROM Accounts

text_query: How many courses that do not have prerequisite?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM course WHERE course_id NOT IN (SELECT course_id FROM prereq)

text_query: How many followers does each user have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM follows

text_query: List the creation year, name and budget of each department.
sql_command: SELECT creation ,  name ,  budget_in_billions FROM department

text_query: Show ids of students who don't play video game.
sql_command: SELECT StuID FROM Student EXCEPT SELECT StuID FROM Plays_games

text_query: Give me a list of the names of all songs ordered by their resolution.
sql_command: SELECT song_name FROM song ORDER BY resolution

text_query: Find the names and average salaries of all departments whose average salary is greater than 42000.
sql_command: SELECT dept_name ,  AVG (salary) FROM instructor GROUP BY dept_name HAVING AVG (salary)  >  42000

text_query: Return ids of all the products that are supplied by supplier id 2 and are more expensive than the average price of all products.
sql_command: SELECT T1.product_id FROM product_suppliers AS T1 JOIN products AS T2 ON T1.product_id  =  T2.product_id WHERE T1.supplier_id  =  2 AND T2.product_price  >  (SELECT avg(product_price) FROM products)

text_query: How many members does the club "Tennis Club" has?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid JOIN student AS t3 ON t2.stuid  =  t3.stuid WHERE t1.clubname  =  "Tennis Club"

text_query: What are the names and id of courses having at most 2 sections?
sql_command: SELECT T1.course_name ,  T1.course_id FROM Courses AS T1 JOIN Sections AS T2 ON T1.course_id  =  T2.course_id GROUP BY T1.course_id HAVING count(*)  <=  2

text_query: List name and damage for all storms in a descending order of max speed.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  damage_millions_USD FROM storm ORDER BY max_speed DESC

text_query: Find the number of customers in the banks at New York City.
sql_command: SELECT sum(no_of_customers) FROM bank WHERE city  =  'New York City'

text_query: Find the number of different departments in each school whose number of different departments is less than 5.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT dept_name) ,  school_code FROM department GROUP BY school_code HAVING count(DISTINCT dept_name)  <  5

text_query: Find the number of checking accounts for each account name.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  T1.name FROM accounts AS T1 JOIN checking AS T2 ON T1.custid  =  T2.custid GROUP BY T1.name

text_query: Find the name of the room with the maximum occupancy.
sql_command: SELECT roomName FROM Rooms ORDER BY maxOccupancy DESC LIMIT 1;

text_query: Find the name and address of the customers who have both New and Pending orders.
sql_command: SELECT T1.customer_name ,  T1.customer_address FROM customers AS T1 JOIN customer_orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE T2.order_status_code  =  "New" INTERSECT SELECT T1.customer_name ,  T1.customer_address FROM customers AS T1 JOIN customer_orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE T2.order_status_code  =  "Pending"

text_query: What is the oldest log id and its corresponding problem id?
sql_command: SELECT problem_log_id ,  problem_id FROM problem_log ORDER BY log_entry_date LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the id of the student who most recently registered course 301?
sql_command: SELECT student_id FROM student_course_attendance WHERE course_id = 301 ORDER BY date_of_attendance DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name, account type, and account balance of the customer who has the highest credit score.
sql_command: SELECT cust_name ,  acc_type ,  acc_bal FROM customer ORDER BY credit_score DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the description and credit for the course QM-261?
sql_command: SELECT crs_credit ,  crs_description FROM course WHERE crs_code  =  'QM-261'

text_query: Show the number of high schoolers for each grade.
sql_command: SELECT grade ,  count(*) FROM Highschooler GROUP BY grade

text_query: Find the names of all person sorted in the descending order using age.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM Person ORDER BY age DESC

text_query: How many different status codes of things are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT Status_of_Thing_Code) FROM Timed_Status_of_Things

text_query: Show the id and details of the investor that has the largest number of transactions.
sql_command: SELECT T2.investor_id ,  T1.Investor_details FROM INVESTORS AS T1 JOIN TRANSACTIONS AS T2 ON T1.investor_id  =  T2.investor_id GROUP BY T2.investor_id ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many video games exist?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Video_games

sql_command: SELECT title FROM course WHERE course_id IN (SELECT T1.prereq_id FROM prereq AS T1 JOIN course AS T2 ON T1.course_id  =  T2.course_id WHERE T2.title  =  'Mobile Computing')

text_query: List the number of different series names and contents in the TV Channel table.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT series_name) ,  count(DISTINCT content) FROM TV_Channel;

text_query: What is the name of the perpetrator with the biggest weight.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name FROM people AS T1 JOIN perpetrator AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID ORDER BY T1.Weight DESC LIMIT 1

sql_command: SELECT claim_status_description FROM claims_processing_stages WHERE claim_status_name  =  "Open"

text_query: What is the city_code of the city that the most students live in?
sql_command: SELECT city_code FROM STUDENT GROUP BY city_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the region name with at least two storms.
sql_command: SELECT T1.region_name FROM region AS T1 JOIN affected_region AS T2 ON T1.region_id = T2.region_id GROUP BY T1.region_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: Show the average and maximum damage for all storms with max speed higher than 1000.
sql_command: SELECT avg(damage_millions_USD) ,  max(damage_millions_USD) FROM storm WHERE max_speed  >  1000

text_query: Find the room number of the rooms which can sit 50 to 100 students and their buildings.

text_query: List all the image name and URLs in the order of their names.
sql_command: SELECT image_name ,  image_url FROM images ORDER BY image_name

text_query: What are the names of wrestlers days held less than 100?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM wrestler WHERE Days_held  <  100

sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  T1.type FROM operate_company AS T1 JOIN flight AS t2 ON T1.id  =  T2.company_id

sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM races AS T1 JOIN circuits AS T2 ON T1.circuitid = T2.circuitid WHERE T2.country = "Spain" AND T1.year > 2017

text_query: What is the lowest and highest rating star?
sql_command: SELECT max(stars) ,  min(stars) FROM Rating

text_query: Find the total credits of courses provided by different department.
sql_command: SELECT sum(credits) ,  dept_name FROM course GROUP BY dept_name

text_query: Show the average price range of hotels that have 5 star ratings and allow pets.
sql_command: SELECT avg(price_range) FROM HOTELS WHERE star_rating_code  =  "5" AND pets_allowed_yn  =  1

text_query: What are the maximum and minimum age of students with major 600?
sql_command: SELECT max(Age) ,  min(Age) FROM STUDENT WHERE Major  =  600

text_query: List the names of all genres in alphabetical oder, together with its ratings.
sql_command: SELECT g_name ,  rating FROM genre ORDER BY g_name

text_query: Give me the temperature of Shanghai in January.

text_query: List the name of teachers whose hometown is not `` Little Lever Urban District '' .
sql_command: select name from teacher where hometown != "little lever urban district"

text_query: Find the number of companies whose industry is "Banking" or "Conglomerate",
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Companies WHERE Industry  =  "Banking" OR Industry  =  "Conglomerate"

text_query: What are the codes of the countries that do not speak English and whose government forms are not Republic?

sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM FLIGHTS WHERE DestAirport  =  "ATO"

text_query: Find the number of different states which banks are located at.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT state) FROM bank

text_query: List all the contact channel codes that were used less than 5 times.
sql_command: SELECT channel_code FROM customer_contact_channels GROUP BY channel_code HAVING count(customer_id)  <  5

text_query: How many sports do we have?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT sportname) FROM Sportsinfo

text_query: Show all card type codes.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT card_type_code FROM Customers_Cards

text_query: What is the average number of attendees for performances?
sql_command: SELECT avg(Attendance) FROM performance

text_query: Find the first name and last name of the instructor of course that has course name
sql_command: SELECT T2.Fname ,  T2.Lname FROM COURSE AS T1 JOIN FACULTY AS T2 ON T1.Instructor  =  T2.FacID WHERE T1.CName  =  "COMPUTER LITERACY"

text_query: In which year are there festivals both inside the 'United States' and outside the 'United States'?
sql_command: SELECT YEAR FROM festival_detail WHERE LOCATION  =  'United States' INTERSECT SELECT YEAR FROM festival_detail WHERE LOCATION != 'United States'

text_query: Find the number of students who is older than 20 in each dorm.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  T3.dorm_name FROM student AS T1 JOIN lives_in AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid JOIN dorm AS T3 ON T3.dormid  =  T2.dormid WHERE T1.age  >  20 GROUP BY T3.dorm_name

text_query: What are the date, mean temperature and mean humidity for the top 3 days with the largest max gust speeds?
sql_command: SELECT date ,  mean_temperature_f ,  mean_humidity FROM weather ORDER BY max_gust_speed_mph DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: What are the drivers' first, last names and id who had more than 8 pit stops or participated in more than 5 race results?
sql_command: SELECT T1.forename ,  T1.surname ,  T1.driverid FROM drivers AS T1 JOIN pitstops AS T2 ON T1.driverid  =  T2.driverid GROUP BY T1.driverid HAVING count(*)  >  8 UNION SELECT T1.forename ,  T1.surname ,  T1.driverid FROM drivers AS T1 JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.driverid  =  T2.driverid GROUP BY T1.driverid HAVING count(*)  >  5

text_query: Show the name and theme for all concerts and the number of singers in each concert.
sql_command: SELECT T2.concert_name ,  T2.theme ,  count(*) FROM singer_in_concert AS T1 JOIN concert AS T2 ON T1.concert_id  =  T2.concert_id GROUP BY T2.concert_id

text_query: What is the distinct service types that are provided by the organization which has detail 'Denesik and Sons Party'?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.service_type_code FROM services AS T1 JOIN organizations AS T2 ON T1.organization_id  =  T2.organization_id WHERE T2.organization_details  =  'Denesik and Sons Party'

text_query: How many different colleges do attend the tryout test?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT cName) FROM tryout

text_query: Find the name and level of catalog structure with level between 5 and 10.
sql_command: SELECT catalog_level_name ,  catalog_level_number FROM Catalog_Structure WHERE catalog_level_number BETWEEN 5 AND 10

text_query: Find the emails and phone numbers of all the customers, ordered by email address and phone number.
sql_command: SELECT email_address ,  phone_number FROM customers ORDER BY email_address ,  phone_number

text_query: Show all book categories and the number of books in each category.
sql_command: SELECT category ,  count(*) FROM book_club GROUP BY category

text_query: return the smallest salary for every departments.
sql_command: SELECT MIN(salary) ,  department_id FROM employees GROUP BY department_id

text_query: Show the statuses of roller coasters longer than 3300 or higher than 100.
sql_command: SELECT Status FROM roller_coaster WHERE LENGTH  >  3300 OR Height  >  100

text_query: Show names of musicals which have at least three actors.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name FROM actor AS T1 JOIN musical AS T2 ON T1.Musical_ID  =  T2.Musical_ID GROUP BY T1.Musical_ID HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  3

text_query: Please show the themes of competitions with host cities having populations larger than 1000.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Theme FROM city AS T1 JOIN farm_competition AS T2 ON T1.City_ID  =  T2.Host_city_ID WHERE T1.Population  >  1000

text_query: Show last names for all student who are on scholarship.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Lname FROM Sportsinfo AS T1 JOIN Student AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  T2.StuID WHERE T1.onscholarship  =  'Y'

text_query: Which city has most number of departing flights?
sql_command: SELECT T1.City FROM AIRPORTS AS T1 JOIN FLIGHTS AS T2 ON T1.AirportCode  =  T2.SourceAirport GROUP BY T1.City ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Return the first names and last names of all guests
sql_command: SELECT guest_first_name ,  guest_last_name FROM Guests

text_query: Find the name of different colleges involved in the tryout in alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT cName FROM tryout ORDER BY cName

text_query: What are the names of people in ascending order of height?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM People ORDER BY Height ASC

text_query: What is the cell phone number of the student whose address has the lowest monthly rental?
sql_command: SELECT T2.cell_mobile_number FROM Student_Addresses AS T1 JOIN Students AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.student_id ORDER BY T1.monthly_rental ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the title of all cartoon directed by "Ben Jones" or "Brandon Vietti".
sql_command: SELECT Title FROM Cartoon WHERE Directed_by = "Ben Jones" OR Directed_by = "Brandon Vietti";

text_query: What is the first name and last name of the student who have most number of sports?
sql_command: SELECT T2.Fname ,  T2.Lname FROM Sportsinfo AS T1 JOIN Student AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  T2.StuID GROUP BY T1.StuID ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the name for regions and the number of storms for each region.
sql_command: SELECT T1.region_name ,  count(*) FROM region AS T1 JOIN affected_region AS T2 ON T1.region_id = T2.region_id GROUP BY T1.region_id

text_query: Show the name, time, and service for all trains.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  TIME ,  service FROM train

text_query: Show the start dates and end dates of all the apartment bookings made by guests with gender code "Female".
sql_command: SELECT T1.booking_start_date ,  T1.booking_start_date FROM Apartment_Bookings AS T1 JOIN Guests AS T2 ON T1.guest_id  =  T2.guest_id WHERE T2.gender_code  =  "Female"

text_query: Find the average prices of all products from each manufacture, and list each company's name.
sql_command: SELECT avg(T1.price) ,  T2.name FROM products AS T1 JOIN manufacturers AS T2 ON T1.Manufacturer  =  T2.code GROUP BY T2.name

text_query: Who is performing in the back stage position for the song "Badlands"? Show the first name and the last name.
sql_command: SELECT T2.firstname ,  T2.lastname FROM Performance AS T1 JOIN Band AS T2 ON T1.bandmate  =  T2.id JOIN Songs AS T3 ON T3.SongId  =  T1.SongId WHERE T3.Title  =  "Badlands" AND T1.StagePosition  =  "back"

text_query: Who belong to the institution "University of Oxford"? Show the first names and last names.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT t1.fname ,  t1.lname FROM authors AS t1 JOIN authorship AS t2 ON t1.authid  =  t2.authid JOIN inst AS t3 ON t2.instid  =  t3.instid WHERE t3.name  =  "University of Oxford"

text_query: Show all cities where at least one customer lives in but no performer lives in.
sql_command: SELECT T1.City_Town FROM Addresses AS T1 JOIN Customers AS T2 ON T1.Address_ID  =  T2.Address_ID EXCEPT SELECT T1.City_Town FROM Addresses AS T1 JOIN Performers AS T2 ON T1.Address_ID  =  T2.Address_ID

text_query: List the names of all music genres.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM GENRE

text_query: Find the number of students who participate in the tryout for each college ordered by descending count.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  cName FROM tryout GROUP BY cName ORDER BY count(*) DESC

text_query: display all the details from Employees table for those employees who was hired before 2002-06-21.
sql_command: SELECT * FROM employees WHERE hire_date  <  '2002-06-21'

text_query: Please show the songs that have result "nominated" at music festivals.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Song FROM music_festival AS T1 JOIN volume AS T2 ON T1.Volume  =  T2.Volume_ID WHERE T1.Result  =  "Nominated"

text_query: Find the physician who was trained in the most expensive procedure?
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM physician AS T1 JOIN trained_in AS T2 ON T1.employeeid  =  T2.physician JOIN procedures AS T3 ON T3.code  =  T2.treatment ORDER BY T3.cost DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Return all players sorted by college in ascending alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT player FROM match_season ORDER BY College ASC

text_query: Find the names of the users whose number of followers is greater than that of the user named "Tyler Swift".
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM user_profiles AS T1 JOIN follows AS T2 ON T1.uid  =  T2.f1 GROUP BY T2.f1 HAVING count(*)  >  (SELECT count(*) FROM user_profiles AS T1 JOIN follows AS T2 ON T1.uid  =  T2.f1 WHERE T1.name  =  'Tyler Swift')

text_query: In which season and which stadium did any player have an injury of 'Foot injury' or 'Knee problem'?
sql_command: SELECT T1.season ,  T2.name FROM game AS T1 JOIN stadium AS T2 ON T1.stadium_id  =  T2.id JOIN injury_accident AS T3 ON T1.id  =  T3.game_id WHERE T3.injury  =  'Foot injury' OR T3.injury  =  'Knee problem'

text_query: How many drivers are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM driver

text_query: display the employee number, name( first name and last name ) and job title for all employees whose salary is more than any salary of those employees whose job title is PU_MAN.
sql_command: SELECT employee_id ,  first_name ,  last_name ,  job_id FROM employees WHERE salary  >  ( SELECT max(salary) FROM employees WHERE job_id  =  'PU_MAN' )

text_query: Show the result of the submission with the highest score.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Result FROM acceptance AS T1 JOIN submission AS T2 ON T1.Submission_ID  =  T2.Submission_ID ORDER BY T2.Scores DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the delegates and the names of county they belong to.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Delegate ,  T1.County_name FROM county AS T1 JOIN election AS T2 ON T1.County_id  =  T2.District

text_query: Find the pixels of the screen modes that are used by both phones with full accreditation types and phones with Provisional accreditation types.
sql_command: SELECT t1.pixels FROM screen_mode AS t1 JOIN phone AS t2 ON t1.Graphics_mode  =  t2.screen_mode WHERE t2.Accreditation_type  =  'Provisional' INTERSECT SELECT t1.pixels FROM screen_mode AS t1 JOIN phone AS t2 ON t1.Graphics_mode  =  t2.screen_mode WHERE t2.Accreditation_type  =  'Full'

text_query: In which year did the most recent crime happen?

text_query: Select the name and price of the cheapest product.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  price FROM Products ORDER BY price ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many authors are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM authors

text_query: Show all city with a branch opened in 2001 and a branch with more than 100 membership.
sql_command: SELECT city FROM branch WHERE open_year  =  2001 AND membership_amount  >  100

text_query: Show the ids for projects with at least 2 documents.
sql_command: SELECT project_id FROM Documents GROUP BY project_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: How many instrument does the musician with last name "Heilo" use?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT instrument) FROM instruments AS T1 JOIN Band AS T2 ON T1.bandmateid  =  T2.id WHERE T2.lastname  =  "Heilo"

text_query: What is the most common mill type, and how many are there?
sql_command: SELECT TYPE ,  count(*) FROM mill GROUP BY TYPE ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many distinct companies are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT Company) FROM entrepreneur

text_query: List the file size and format for all songs that have resolution lower than 800.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.file_size ,  T1.formats FROM files AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.f_id  =  T2.f_id WHERE T2.resolution  <  800

text_query: How many camera lenses have a focal length longer than 15 mm?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM camera_lens WHERE focal_length_mm  >  15

text_query: Show the name, location, and number of platforms for all stations.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  LOCATION ,  number_of_platforms FROM station

text_query: Show the name of drivers in descending order of age.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM driver ORDER BY age DESC

text_query: Show id and location of railways that are associated with more than one train.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Railway_ID ,  T1.Location FROM railway AS T1 JOIN train AS T2 ON T1.Railway_ID  =  T2.Railway_ID GROUP BY T2.Railway_ID HAVING COUNT(*)  >  1

text_query: Show the names of the three most recent festivals.
sql_command: SELECT Festival_Name FROM festival_detail ORDER BY YEAR DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: Which country has at most 3 stadiums listed?
sql_command: SELECT country FROM stadium GROUP BY country HAVING count(*)  <=  3

text_query: What is the maximum miles per gallon of the car with 8 cylinders or produced before 1980 ?
sql_command: select max(mpg) from cars_data where cylinders  =  8 or year  <  1980

text_query: Which address has both members younger than 30 and members older than 40?
sql_command: SELECT address FROM member WHERE age  <  30 INTERSECT SELECT address FROM member WHERE age  >  40

sql_command: SELECT date_of_transaction ,  share_count FROM TRANSACTIONS

text_query: display job ID for those jobs that were done by two or more for more than 300 days.
sql_command: SELECT job_id FROM job_history WHERE end_date - start_date  > 300 GROUP BY job_id HAVING COUNT(*) >= 2

text_query: Who is the youngest male?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM Person WHERE gender  =  'male' AND age  =  (SELECT min(age) FROM person WHERE gender  =  'male' )

text_query: What is the id of the event with the most participants?
sql_command: SELECT Event_ID FROM Participants_in_Events GROUP BY Event_ID ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the name of all customers sorted by their account balance in ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT cust_name FROM customer ORDER BY acc_bal

sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM EVENTS WHERE event_id NOT IN (SELECT event_id FROM Participants_in_Events)

text_query: Which origin has most number of flights?
sql_command: SELECT origin FROM Flight GROUP BY origin ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the list of documents that are both in the most three popular type and have the most three popular structure.
sql_command: SELECT document_name FROM documents GROUP BY document_type_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 3 INTERSECT SELECT document_name FROM documents GROUP BY document_structure_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: What is the product, chromosome and porphyria related to the enzymes which take effect at the location 'Cytosol'?
sql_command: SELECT product ,  chromosome ,  porphyria FROM enzyme WHERE LOCATION  =  'Cytosol'

text_query: Who is the person that has no friend?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM person EXCEPT SELECT name FROM PersonFriend

text_query: Find the names of all swimmers, sorted by their 100 meter scores in ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM swimmer ORDER BY meter_100

text_query: List the description of all aircrafts.
sql_command: SELECT Description FROM aircraft

text_query: Show the name, average attendance, total attendance for stadiums where no accidents happened.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  average_attendance ,  total_attendance FROM stadium EXCEPT SELECT T2.name ,  T2.average_attendance ,  T2.total_attendance FROM game AS T1 JOIN stadium AS T2 ON T1.stadium_id  =  T2.id JOIN injury_accident AS T3 ON T1.id  =  T3.game_id

text_query: What are all the course names of the courses which ever have students enrolled in?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.course_name FROM Courses AS T1 JOIN Student_Enrolment_Courses AS T2 ON T1.course_id  =  T2.course_id

text_query: What is the name and country of origin of the artist who released a song that has "love" in its title?
sql_command: SELECT T1.artist_name ,  T1.country FROM artist AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.artist_name  =  T2.artist_name WHERE T2.song_name LIKE "%love%"

text_query: Show the names of customers who have at least 2 mailshots with outcome code 'Order'.
sql_command: SELECT T2.customer_name FROM mailshot_customers AS T1 JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE outcome_code  =  'Order' GROUP BY T1.customer_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: Find the names of products that were bought by at least two distinct customers.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T3.product_name FROM customer_orders AS T1 JOIN order_items AS T2 ON T1.order_id  =  T2.order_id JOIN products AS T3 ON T2.product_id  =  T3.product_id GROUP BY T3.product_id HAVING COUNT (DISTINCT T1.customer_id)  >=  2

text_query: Show the players from college UCLA.
sql_command: SELECT Player FROM match_season WHERE College  =  "UCLA"

text_query: Which services type had both successful and failure event details?
sql_command: SELECT T1.service_type_code FROM services AS T1 JOIN EVENTS AS T2 ON T1.service_id  =  T2.service_id WHERE T2.event_details  =  'Success' INTERSECT SELECT T1.service_type_code FROM services AS T1 JOIN EVENTS AS T2 ON T1.service_id  =  T2.service_id WHERE T2.event_details  =  'Fail'

text_query: What are the names of perpetrators?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name FROM people AS T1 JOIN perpetrator AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID

text_query: What is the semester which most student registered in? Show both the name and the id.
sql_command: SELECT T1.semester_name ,  T1.semester_id FROM Semesters AS T1 JOIN Student_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.semester_id  =  T2.semester_id GROUP BY T1.semester_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the average age of all students living in the each city.
sql_command: SELECT avg(age) ,  city_code FROM student GROUP BY city_code

text_query: How many appelations are in Napa Country?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM APPELLATIONS WHERE County  =  "Napa"

text_query: Find the number of vocal types used in song "Demon Kitty Rag"?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM vocals AS T1 JOIN songs AS T2 ON T1.songid  =  T2.songid WHERE title  =  "Demon Kitty Rag"

text_query: Show name of all students who have some friends and also are liked by someone else.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM Friend AS T1 JOIN Highschooler AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.id INTERSECT SELECT T2.name FROM Likes AS T1 JOIN Highschooler AS T2 ON T1.liked_id  =  T2.id

text_query: Show the account name, id and the number of transactions for each account.
sql_command: SELECT T2.account_name ,  T1.account_id ,  count(*) FROM Financial_transactions AS T1 JOIN Accounts AS T2 ON T1.account_id  =  T2.account_id GROUP BY T1.account_id

text_query: Show names of teachers that teach at least two courses.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name FROM course_arrange AS T1 JOIN teacher AS T2 ON T1.Teacher_ID  =  T2.Teacher_ID GROUP BY T2.Name HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  2

text_query: Which documents have more than 1 draft copies? List document id and number of draft copies.
sql_command: SELECT document_id , count(*) FROM Draft_Copies GROUP BY document_id HAVING count(*)  >  1;

text_query: Find the first name and age of students who have a dog but do not have a cat as a pet.
sql_command: SELECT T1.fname ,  T1.age FROM student AS T1 JOIN has_pet AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid JOIN pets AS T3 ON T3.petid  =  T2.petid WHERE T3.pettype  =  'dog' AND T1.stuid NOT IN (SELECT T1.stuid FROM student AS T1 JOIN has_pet AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid JOIN pets AS T3 ON T3.petid  =  T2.petid WHERE T3.pettype  =  'cat')

text_query: How many high schoolers are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Highschooler

text_query: List the physicians' employee ids together with their primary affiliation departments' ids.
sql_command: SELECT physician ,  department FROM affiliated_with WHERE primaryaffiliation  =  1

text_query: Show countries where a singer above age 40 and a singer below 30 are from.
sql_command: SELECT country FROM singer WHERE age  >  40 INTERSECT SELECT country FROM singer WHERE age  <  30

text_query: What are the distinct template type descriptions for the templates ever used by any document?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.template_type_description FROM Ref_template_types AS T1 JOIN Templates AS T2 ON T1.template_type_code  = T2.template_type_code JOIN Documents AS T3 ON T2.Template_ID  =  T3.template_ID

text_query: Give me the names of customers who have placed orders between 2009-01-01 and 2010-01-01.
sql_command: SELECT T1.customer_name FROM customers AS T1 JOIN orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id WHERE T2.date_order_placed >= "2009-01-01" AND T2.date_order_placed <= "2010-01-01"

text_query: What is the average, minimum, and maximum age of all singers from France?
sql_command: SELECT avg(age) ,  min(age) ,  max(age) FROM singer WHERE country  =  'France'

text_query: Show the addresses of the buildings that have apartments with more than 2 bathrooms.
sql_command: SELECT T1.building_address FROM Apartment_Buildings AS T1 JOIN Apartments AS T2 ON T1.building_id  =  T2.building_id WHERE T2.bathroom_count  >  2

text_query: How many different degree names are offered?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT degree_summary_name) FROM Degree_Programs

text_query: Find the first and last name of the staff members who reported problems from the product "rem" but not "aut"?
sql_command: SELECT T3.staff_first_name ,  T3.staff_last_name FROM problems AS T1 JOIN product AS T2 JOIN staff AS T3 ON T1.product_id = T2.product_id AND T1.reported_by_staff_id = T3.staff_id WHERE T2.product_name = "rem" EXCEPT SELECT T3.staff_first_name ,  T3.staff_last_name FROM problems AS T1 JOIN product AS T2 JOIN staff AS T3 ON T1.product_id = T2.product_id AND T1.reported_by_staff_id = T3.staff_id WHERE T2.product_name = "aut"

text_query: List the names of all players who have a crossing score higher than 90 and prefer their right foot.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.player_name FROM Player AS T1 JOIN Player_Attributes AS T2 ON T1.player_api_id = T2.player_api_id WHERE T2.crossing  >  90 AND T2.preferred_foot  =  "right"

text_query: How many professors do have a Ph.D. degree?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM professor WHERE prof_high_degree  =  'Ph.D.'

text_query: How many airports are there per city in the United States? Order the cities by decreasing number of airports.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  city FROM airports WHERE country  =  'United States' GROUP BY city ORDER BY count(*) DESC

text_query: Find the name, enrollment of the colleges whose size is bigger than 10000 and location is in state LA.
sql_command: SELECT cName ,  enr FROM College WHERE enr  >  10000 AND state = "LA"

text_query: How many budget types do we have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Ref_budget_codes

text_query: What are the maximum and minimum settlement amount on record?
sql_command: SELECT max(settlement_amount) ,  min(settlement_amount) FROM settlements

text_query: What is the 3 most common cloud cover rates in the region of zip code 94107?
sql_command: SELECT cloud_cover FROM weather WHERE zip_code  =  94107 GROUP BY cloud_cover ORDER BY COUNT (*) DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: List the email, cell phone and home phone of all the professionals.
sql_command: SELECT email_address ,  cell_number ,  home_phone FROM professionals

text_query: Find the names of all races held in 2017.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM races WHERE YEAR = 2017

text_query: Give me all the information about hiring.
sql_command: SELECT * FROM hiring

text_query: What is the order id and order details for the order more than two invoices.
sql_command: SELECT T2.order_id ,  T2.order_details FROM Invoices AS T1 JOIN Orders AS T2 ON T1.order_id  =  T2.order_id GROUP BY T2.order_id HAVING count(*)  >  2

text_query: What are the names of all the countries that became independent after 1950?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM country WHERE IndepYear  >  1950

text_query: How many different cities do have some airport in the country of Greenland?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT city) FROM airports WHERE country  =  'Greenland'

text_query: find the name of the program that was launched most recently.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM program ORDER BY launch DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many rooms does the Lamberton building have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM classroom WHERE building  =  'Lamberton'

sql_command: SELECT T2.department_name ,  COUNT(*) FROM employees AS T1 JOIN departments AS T2 ON T1.department_id  =  T2.department_id GROUP BY T2.department_name

text_query: What are the positions with both players having more than 20 points and less than 10 points.

sql_command: SELECT COUNT (DISTINCT church_id) FROM wedding WHERE YEAR  =  2016

sql_command: SELECT T2.name ,  T2.salary FROM advisor AS T1 JOIN instructor AS T2 ON T1.i_id  =  T2.id JOIN student AS T3 ON T1.s_id  =  T3.id WHERE T3.dept_name  =  'Math'

text_query: Show the invoice number and the number of transactions for each invoice.
sql_command: SELECT invoice_number ,  count(*) FROM Financial_transactions GROUP BY invoice_number

text_query: Show the role description and the id of the project staff involved in most number of project outcomes?
sql_command: SELECT T1.role_description ,  T2.staff_id FROM Staff_Roles AS T1 JOIN Project_Staff AS T2 ON T1.role_code  =  T2.role_code JOIN Project_outcomes AS T3 ON T2.project_id  =  T3.project_id GROUP BY T2.staff_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the average number of followers for the users who had some tweets.
sql_command: SELECT avg(followers) FROM user_profiles WHERE UID IN (SELECT UID FROM tweets)

text_query: Find the names of users whose emails contain ‘superstar’ or ‘edu’.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM user_profiles WHERE email LIKE '%superstar%' OR email LIKE '%edu%'

text_query: Show the case burden of counties in descending order of population.
sql_command: SELECT Case_burden FROM county_public_safety ORDER BY Population DESC

text_query: Which month has the most happy hours?
sql_command: SELECT MONTH FROM happy_hour GROUP BY MONTH ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many type of jobs do they have?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT job) FROM Person

text_query: What are the names and opening hours of the tourist attractions that can be accessed by bus or walk?
sql_command: SELECT Name ,  Opening_Hours FROM TOURIST_ATTRACTIONS WHERE How_to_Get_There  =  "bus" OR How_to_Get_There  =  "walk"

text_query: What is the birth date of the poker player with the lowest earnings?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Birth_Date FROM people AS T1 JOIN poker_player AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID ORDER BY T2.Earnings ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find all the distinct id and nationality of drivers who have had laptime more than 100000 milliseconds?
