sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.driverid ,  T1.nationality FROM drivers AS T1 JOIN laptimes AS T2 ON T1.driverid = T2.driverid WHERE T2.milliseconds >  100000

text_query: Find the number of airports whose name contain the word 'International'.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM airports WHERE name LIKE '%International%'

text_query: What is the total budget amount for school "Glenn" in all years?
sql_command: SELECT sum(T1.budgeted) FROM budget AS T1 JOIN school AS T2 ON T1.school_id  =  T2.school_id WHERE T2.school_name  =  'Glenn'

text_query: What is total bonus given in all evaluations?
sql_command: SELECT sum(bonus) FROM evaluation

text_query: Find the names of departments that are located in Houston.
sql_command: SELECT t1.dname FROM department AS t1 JOIN dept_locations AS t2 ON t1.dnumber  =  t2.dnumber WHERE t2.dlocation  =  'Houston'

text_query: What is the average and maximum capacities for all stadiums ?
sql_command: select avg(capacity) ,  max(capacity) from stadium

text_query: Show the location with most number of train stations.
sql_command: SELECT LOCATION FROM station GROUP BY LOCATION ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the payment method of the customer that has purchased the least quantity of items?
sql_command: SELECT t1.payment_method FROM customers AS t1 JOIN customer_orders AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id JOIN order_items AS t3 ON t2.order_id  =  t3.order_id GROUP BY t1.customer_name ORDER BY sum(t3.order_quantity) LIMIT 1

text_query: Show all template ids and number of documents using each template.
sql_command: SELECT template_id ,  count(*) FROM Documents GROUP BY template_id

text_query: For each election cycle, report the number of voting records.
sql_command: SELECT Election_Cycle ,  count(*) FROM VOTING_RECORD GROUP BY Election_Cycle

text_query: find the full name of employees who report to Nancy Edwards?
sql_command: SELECT T2.first_name , T2.last_name FROM employees AS T1 JOIN employees AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.reports_to WHERE T1.first_name = "Nancy" AND T1.last_name = "Edwards";

text_query: Find the name of customers who do not have an saving account.
sql_command: SELECT cust_name FROM customer EXCEPT SELECT cust_name FROM customer WHERE acc_type  =  'saving'

text_query: List the clubs having "Davis Steven" as a member.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT t1.clubname FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid JOIN student AS t3 ON t2.stuid  =  t3.stuid WHERE t3.fname  =  "Davis" AND t3.lname  =  "Steven"

text_query: which country did participated in the most number of Tournament competitions?
sql_command: SELECT country FROM competition WHERE competition_type  =  'Tournament' GROUP BY country ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: which countries did participated in both Friendly and Tournament type competitions.
sql_command: SELECT country FROM competition WHERE competition_type  =  'Friendly' INTERSECT SELECT country FROM competition WHERE competition_type  =  'Tournament'

text_query: What is the name and id of the staff who recorded the fault log but has not contacted any visiting engineers?
sql_command: SELECT T1.staff_name ,  T1.staff_id FROM Staff AS T1 JOIN Fault_Log AS T2 ON T1.staff_id  =  T2.recorded_by_staff_id EXCEPT SELECT T3.staff_name ,  T3.staff_id FROM Staff AS T3 JOIN Engineer_Visits AS T4 ON T3.staff_id  =  T4.contact_staff_id

text_query: What is the zip code of the address in the city Port Chelsea?
sql_command: SELECT zip_postcode FROM Addresses WHERE city  =  'Port Chelsea'

text_query: List total amount of  invoice from Chicago, IL.
sql_command: SELECT sum(total) FROM invoices WHERE billing_city  =  "Chicago" AND billing_state  =  "IL";

text_query: Find the name of students who didn't take any course from Biology department.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM student WHERE id NOT IN (SELECT T1.id FROM takes AS T1 JOIN course AS T2 ON T1.course_id  =  T2.course_id WHERE T2.dept_name  =  'Biology')

text_query: How many different levels do members have?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT LEVEL) FROM member

text_query: Show gas station id, location, and manager_name for all gas stations ordered by open year.
sql_command: SELECT station_id ,  LOCATION ,  manager_name FROM gas_station ORDER BY open_year

text_query: Find the name and rank of the 3 youngest winners across all matches.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT winner_name ,  winner_rank FROM matches ORDER BY winner_age LIMIT 3

text_query: Show the average amount of transactions for different lots.
sql_command: SELECT T2.lot_id ,  avg(amount_of_transaction) FROM TRANSACTIONS AS T1 JOIN Transactions_Lots AS T2 ON T1.transaction_id  =  T2.transaction_id GROUP BY T2.lot_id

text_query: what is the full name and id of the college with the largest number of baseball players?
sql_command: SELECT T1.name_full ,  T1.college_id FROM college AS T1 JOIN player_college AS T2 ON T1.college_id  =  T2.college_id GROUP BY T1.college_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1;

text_query: What are the names of the channels owned by CCTV or HBS?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM channel WHERE OWNER  =  'CCTV' OR OWNER  =  'HBS'

text_query: Find the name of airports whose altitude is between -50 and 50.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM airports WHERE elevation BETWEEN -50 AND 50

text_query: For all directors who directed more than one movie, return the titles of all movies directed by them, along with the director name. Sort by director name, then movie title.
sql_command: SELECT T1.title ,  T1.director FROM Movie AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.director  =  T2.director WHERE T1.title != T2.title ORDER BY T1.director ,  T1.title

text_query: How many different courses offered by Physics department?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT course_id) FROM course WHERE dept_name  =  'Physics'

text_query: Find the name of the students and their department names sorted by their total credits in ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  dept_name FROM student ORDER BY tot_cred

text_query: Find distinct cities of addresses of people?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.city FROM addresses AS T1 JOIN people_addresses AS T2 ON T1.address_id = T2.address_id

text_query: What is the last name of the musician that have produced the most number of songs?
sql_command: SELECT T2.lastname FROM Performance AS T1 JOIN Band AS T2 ON T1.bandmate  =  T2.id JOIN Songs AS T3 ON T3.SongId  =  T1.SongId GROUP BY lastname ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the count and code of the job has most employees.
sql_command: SELECT emp_jobcode ,  count(*) FROM employee GROUP BY emp_jobcode ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the first and last name of all players who are left / L hand in the order of birth date.
sql_command: SELECT first_name ,  last_name FROM players WHERE hand  =  'L' ORDER BY birth_date

text_query: Find the name of organizations whose names contain "Party".
sql_command: SELECT organization_name FROM organizations WHERE organization_name LIKE "%Party%"

text_query: How many institutions are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM inst

text_query: What were all the salary values of players in 2010 and 2001?
sql_command: SELECT salary FROM salary WHERE YEAR  =  2010 UNION SELECT salary FROM salary WHERE YEAR  =  2001

text_query: Show all the locations where no cinema has capacity over 800.
sql_command: SELECT LOCATION FROM cinema EXCEPT SELECT LOCATION FROM cinema WHERE capacity  >  800

text_query: Find the name of the source user with the highest average trust score.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM useracct AS T1 JOIN trust AS T2 ON T1.u_id  =  T2.source_u_id GROUP BY T2.source_u_id ORDER BY avg(trust) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the ids, names and genders of the architects who built two bridges or one mill?
sql_command: SELECT T1.id ,  T1.name ,  T1.gender FROM architect AS T1 JOIN bridge AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.architect_id GROUP BY T1.id HAVING count(*)  =  2 UNION SELECT T1.id ,  T1.name ,  T1.gender FROM architect AS T1 JOIN mill AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.architect_id GROUP BY T1.id HAVING count(*)  =  1

text_query: How many vehicle in total?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Vehicles;

text_query: Find the ids of the problems that are reported by the staff whose last name is Bosco.
sql_command: SELECT T1.problem_id FROM problems AS T1 JOIN staff AS T2 ON T1.reported_by_staff_id = T2.staff_id WHERE T2.staff_last_name = "Bosco"

text_query: Find the total capacity of all dorms.
sql_command: SELECT sum(student_capacity) FROM dorm

text_query: What is the country that has the most perpetrators?
sql_command: SELECT Country ,  COUNT(*) FROM perpetrator GROUP BY Country ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the prices of the products named "Dining" or "Trading Policy".
sql_command: SELECT Product_Price FROM Products WHERE Product_Name  =  "Dining" OR Product_Name  =  "Trading Policy"

text_query: Find the buildings which have rooms with capacity more than 50.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT building FROM classroom WHERE capacity  >  50

text_query: Which semesters do not have any student enrolled? List the semester name.
sql_command: SELECT semester_name FROM Semesters WHERE semester_id NOT IN( SELECT semester_id FROM Student_Enrolment )

text_query: What is the sum of total pounds of purchase in year 2018 for all branches in London?
sql_command: SELECT sum(total_pounds) FROM purchase AS T1 JOIN branch AS T2 ON T1.branch_id  =  T2.branch_id WHERE T2.city  =  'London' AND T1.year  =  2018

text_query: Show different builders of railways, along with the corresponding number of railways using each builder.
sql_command: SELECT Builder ,  COUNT(*) FROM railway GROUP BY Builder

text_query: Show all student IDs who have at least two allergies.
sql_command: SELECT StuID FROM Has_allergy GROUP BY StuID HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: Which professionals live in the state of Indiana or have done treatment on more than 2 treatments? List his or her id, last name and cell phone.
sql_command: SELECT professional_id ,  last_name ,  cell_number FROM Professionals WHERE state  =  'Indiana' UNION SELECT T1.professional_id ,  T1.last_name ,  T1.cell_number FROM Professionals AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 ON T1.professional_id  =  T2.professional_id GROUP BY T1.professional_id HAVING count(*)  >  2

text_query: Show all track names that have had no races.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM track WHERE track_id NOT IN (SELECT track_id FROM race)

text_query: What is the name of the ship with the largest tonnage?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM ship ORDER BY Tonnage DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the last names of faculties who are members of computer science department.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Lname FROM DEPARTMENT AS T1 JOIN FACULTY AS T2 ON T1.DNO  =  T3.DNO JOIN MEMBER_OF AS T3 ON T2.FacID  =  T3.FacID WHERE T1.DName  =  "Computer Science"

text_query: display those employees who contain a letter z to their first name and also display their last name, city.
sql_command: SELECT T1.first_name ,  T1.last_name ,  T3.city FROM employees AS T1 JOIN departments AS T2 ON T1.department_id  =  T2.department_id JOIN locations AS T3 ON T2.location_id  =  T3.location_id WHERE T1.first_name LIKE '%z%'

text_query: List the dates of games by the home team name in descending order.
sql_command: SELECT Date FROM game ORDER BY home_team DESC

text_query: How many exhibition are there in year 2005 or after?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM exhibition WHERE YEAR  >=  2005

text_query: Which last names are both used by customers and by staff?
sql_command: SELECT last_name FROM Customers INTERSECT SELECT last_name FROM Staff

text_query: How many settlements were made on the claim with the most recent claim settlement date? List the number and the claim id.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  T1.claim_id FROM Claims AS T1 JOIN Settlements AS T2 ON T1.claim_id  =  T2.claim_id GROUP BY T1.claim_id ORDER BY T1.Date_Claim_Settled DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name of the target user with the lowest trust score.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM useracct AS T1 JOIN trust AS T2 ON T1.u_id  =  T2.target_u_id ORDER BY trust LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the builder of railways associated with the trains named "Andaman Exp".
sql_command: SELECT T1.Builder FROM railway AS T1 JOIN train AS T2 ON T1.Railway_ID  =  T2.Railway_ID WHERE T2.Name  =  "Andaman Exp"

text_query: Which staff handled least number of payments? List the full name and the id.
sql_command: SELECT T1.first_name ,  T1.last_name ,  T1.staff_id FROM staff AS T1 JOIN payment AS T2 ON T1.staff_id  =  T2.staff_id GROUP BY T1.staff_id ORDER BY count(*) ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the star rating descriptions of the hotels with price above 10000?
sql_command: SELECT T2.star_rating_description FROM HOTELS AS T1 JOIN Ref_Hotel_Star_Ratings AS T2 ON T1.star_rating_code  =  T2.star_rating_code WHERE T1.price_range  >  10000

text_query: What is the title, phone and hire date of Nancy Edwards?
sql_command: SELECT title ,  phone ,  hire_date FROM employees WHERE first_name = "Nancy" AND last_name = "Edwards";

text_query: How many users are logged in?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM users WHERE user_login  =  1

text_query: List the number of people injured by perpetrators in ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT Injured FROM perpetrator ORDER BY Injured ASC

text_query: Which paper's title contains the word "Database"?
sql_command: SELECT title FROM papers WHERE title LIKE "%Database%"

text_query: Please show the most common reigns of wrestlers.
sql_command: SELECT Reign FROM wrestler GROUP BY Reign ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name of the makers that produced some cars in the year of 1970?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Maker FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T3 ON T2.model  =  T3.model JOIN CARS_DATA AS T4 ON T3.MakeId  =  T4.id WHERE T4.year  =  '1970';

text_query: Who is the composer of track Fast As a Shark?
sql_command: SELECT composer FROM tracks WHERE name = "Fast As a Shark";

text_query: Show names of musicals and the number of actors who have appeared in the musicals.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name ,  COUNT(*) FROM actor AS T1 JOIN musical AS T2 ON T1.Musical_ID  =  T2.Musical_ID GROUP BY T1.Musical_ID

text_query: Find the number of routes that have destination John F Kennedy International Airport.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM airports AS T1 JOIN routes AS T2 ON T1.apid  =  T2.dst_apid WHERE T1.name  =  'John F Kennedy International Airport'

text_query: How many budgets are above 3000 in year 2001 or before?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM budget WHERE budgeted  >  3000 AND YEAR  <=  2001

text_query: Find the total number of instructors who teach a course in the Spring 2010 semester.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT (DISTINCT ID) FROM teaches WHERE semester  =  'Spring' AND YEAR  =  2010

text_query: Find the number of reviews.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM review

text_query: How many cartoons were written by "Joseph Kuhr"?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Cartoon WHERE Written_by = "Joseph Kuhr";

text_query: What is the name of the movie that is rated by most of times?
sql_command: SELECT T2.title ,  T1.mID FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID GROUP BY T1.mID ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: find the number of different programs that are broadcast during night time.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT program_id) FROM broadcast WHERE time_of_day  =  'Night'

text_query: Find the number of scientists who are not assigned to any project.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM scientists WHERE ssn NOT IN (SELECT scientist FROM AssignedTo)

text_query: How many elections are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM election

text_query: Show the names of players coached by the rank 1 coach.
sql_command: SELECT T3.Player_name FROM player_coach AS T1 JOIN coach AS T2 ON T1.Coach_ID  =  T2.Coach_ID JOIN player AS T3 ON T1.Player_ID  =  T3.Player_ID WHERE T2.Rank  =  1

text_query: Find the busiest source airport that runs most number of routes in China.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM airports AS T1 JOIN routes AS T2 ON T1.apid  =  T2.src_apid WHERE T1.country  =  'China' GROUP BY T1.name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many students have cat allergies?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Has_allergy WHERE Allergy  =  "Cat"

text_query: Find the id of the order whose shipment tracking number is "3452".
sql_command: SELECT order_id FROM shipments WHERE shipment_tracking_number = "3452"

text_query: Show the date and id of the transcript with at least 2 course results.
sql_command: SELECT T2.transcript_date ,  T1.transcript_id FROM Transcript_Contents AS T1 JOIN Transcripts AS T2 ON T1.transcript_id  =  T2.transcript_id GROUP BY T1.transcript_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: Which part has the least chargeable amount? List the part id and amount.
sql_command: SELECT part_id ,  chargeable_amount FROM Parts ORDER BY chargeable_amount ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: Return the different names of cities that are in Asia and for which Chinese is the official language.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T3.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode JOIN city AS T3 ON T1.Code  =  T3.CountryCode WHERE T2.IsOfficial  =  'T' AND T2.Language  =  'Chinese' AND T1.Continent  =  "Asia"

text_query: Show all locations and the number of gas stations in each location ordered by the count.
sql_command: SELECT LOCATION ,  count(*) FROM gas_station GROUP BY LOCATION ORDER BY count(*)

text_query: List all club names in ascending order of start year.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM club ORDER BY Start_year ASC

text_query: List the official name and status of the city with the largest population.
sql_command: SELECT Official_Name ,  Status FROM city ORDER BY Population DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Which cities are in European countries where English is not the official language?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T2.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN city AS T2 ON T2.CountryCode  =  T1.Code WHERE T1.Continent  =  'Europe' AND T1.Name NOT IN (SELECT T3.Name FROM country AS T3 JOIN countrylanguage AS T4 ON T3.Code  =  T4.CountryCode WHERE T4.IsOfficial  =  'T' AND T4.Language  =  'English')

text_query: Which location names contain the word "film"?
sql_command: SELECT Location_Name FROM LOCATIONS WHERE Location_Name LIKE "%film%"

text_query: What is the name of the customer that made the order with the largest quantity?
sql_command: SELECT t1.customer_name FROM customers AS t1 JOIN customer_orders AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id JOIN order_items AS t3 ON t2.order_id  =  t3.order_id WHERE t3.order_quantity  =  ( SELECT max(order_quantity) FROM order_items)

text_query: Show all the faculty ranks and the number of students advised by each rank.
sql_command: SELECT T1.rank ,  count(*) FROM Faculty AS T1 JOIN Student AS T2 ON T1.FacID  =  T2.advisor GROUP BY T1.rank

text_query: Find the names of customers who have no policies associated.
sql_command: SELECT customer_details FROM customers EXCEPT SELECT t2.customer_details FROM policies AS t1 JOIN customers AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id

text_query: List the Episode of all TV series sorted by rating.
sql_command: SELECT Episode FROM TV_series ORDER BY rating

text_query: Show all church names that have hosted least two weddings.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM church AS T1 JOIN wedding AS T2 ON T1.church_id  =  T2.church_id GROUP BY T1.church_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: How many courses have more than 2 credits?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM COURSE WHERE Credits  >  2

text_query: What is the average ticket sales gross in dollars of films?
sql_command: SELECT avg(Gross_in_dollar) FROM film

text_query: Which template type code has most number of templates?
sql_command: SELECT template_type_code FROM Templates GROUP BY template_type_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the birth year and citizenship of singers?
sql_command: SELECT Birth_Year ,  Citizenship FROM singer

text_query: What are the names of the tourist attractions Vincent and Marcelle visit?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name FROM Tourist_Attractions AS T1 JOIN VISITORS AS T2 JOIN VISITS AS T3 ON T1.Tourist_Attraction_ID  =  T3.Tourist_Attraction_ID AND T2.Tourist_ID  =  T3.Tourist_ID WHERE T2.Tourist_Details  =  "Vincent" INTERSECT SELECT T1.Name FROM Tourist_Attractions AS T1 JOIN VISITORS AS T2 JOIN VISITS AS T3 ON T1.Tourist_Attraction_ID  =  T3.Tourist_Attraction_ID AND T2.Tourist_ID  =  T3.Tourist_ID WHERE T2.Tourist_Details  =  "Marcelle"

text_query: How many customers have an account?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT customer_id) FROM Accounts

text_query: Show all the buildings along with the number of faculty members the buildings have.
sql_command: SELECT building ,  count(*) FROM Faculty GROUP BY building

text_query: What the smallest version number and its template type code?
sql_command: SELECT min(Version_Number) ,  template_type_code FROM Templates

text_query: How many documents have expenses?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Documents_with_expenses

text_query: What is the name of the nurse has the most appointments?
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM nurse AS T1 JOIN appointment AS T2 ON T1.employeeid  =  T2.prepnurse GROUP BY T1.employeeid ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the names of customers who ordered both products Latte and Americano.
sql_command: SELECT t1.customer_name FROM customers AS t1 JOIN customer_orders AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id JOIN order_items AS t3 ON t2.order_id  =  t3.order_id JOIN products AS t4 ON t3.product_id  =  t4.product_id WHERE t4.product_details  =  'Latte' INTERSECT SELECT t1.customer_name FROM customers AS t1 JOIN customer_orders AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id JOIN order_items AS t3 ON t2.order_id  =  t3.order_id JOIN products AS t4 ON t3.product_id  =  t4.product_id WHERE t4.product_details  =  'Americano'

text_query: Show the name and age for all male people who don't have a wedding.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  age FROM people WHERE is_male  =  'T' AND people_id NOT IN (SELECT male_id FROM wedding)

text_query: List the number of all matches who played in years of 2013 or 2016.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM matches WHERE YEAR  =  2013 OR YEAR  =  2016

text_query: Find the last names of all the teachers that teach GELL TAMI.
sql_command: SELECT T2.lastname FROM list AS T1 JOIN teachers AS T2 ON T1.classroom  =  T2.classroom WHERE T1.firstname  =  "GELL" AND T1.lastname  =  "TAMI"

text_query: Find the dates on which more than one revisions were made.
sql_command: SELECT date_of_latest_revision FROM Catalogs GROUP BY date_of_latest_revision HAVING count(*)  >  1

text_query: What are the names of managers in ascending order of level?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM manager ORDER BY LEVEL ASC

text_query: What are the names of races held after 12:00:00 or before 09:00:00?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM races WHERE TIME > "12:00:00" OR TIME < "09:00:00"

text_query: Find the founder of the company whose name begins with the letter 'S'.
sql_command: SELECT founder FROM manufacturers WHERE name LIKE 'S%'

text_query: What are the first and last names of the instructors who teach the top 3 number of courses?
sql_command: SELECT T2.Fname ,  T2.Lname FROM COURSE AS T1 JOIN FACULTY AS T2 ON T1.Instructor  =  T2.FacID GROUP BY T1.Instructor ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: Find the name of the department that offers the largest number of credits of all classes.
sql_command: SELECT T3.dept_name FROM course AS T1 JOIN CLASS AS T2 ON T1.crs_code  =  T2.crs_code JOIN department AS T3 ON T1.dept_code  =  T3.dept_code GROUP BY T1.dept_code ORDER BY sum(T1.crs_credit) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the pair of male and female names in all weddings after year 2014
sql_command: SELECT T2.name ,  T3.name FROM wedding AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.male_id  =  T2.people_id JOIN people AS T3 ON T1.female_id  =  T3.people_id WHERE T1.year  >  2014

text_query: Show the number of document types.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Ref_document_types

text_query: What is the average ROM size of phones produced by the company named "Nokia Corporation"?
sql_command: SELECT avg(T1.ROM_MiB) FROM chip_model AS T1 JOIN phone AS T2 ON T1.Model_name  =  T2.chip_model WHERE T2.Company_name = "Nokia Corporation";

text_query: Which assets have 2 parts and have less than 2 fault logs? List the asset id and detail.
sql_command: SELECT T1.asset_id ,  T1.asset_details FROM Assets AS T1 JOIN Asset_Parts AS T2 ON T1.asset_id  =  T2.asset_id GROUP BY T1.asset_id HAVING count(*)  =  2 INTERSECT SELECT T1.asset_id ,  T1.asset_details FROM Assets AS T1 JOIN Fault_Log AS T2 ON T1.asset_id  =  T2.asset_id GROUP BY T1.asset_id HAVING count(*)  <  2

text_query: How many continents are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM CONTINENTS;

text_query: Find the states where have some college students in tryout.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT state FROM college AS T1 JOIN tryout AS T2 ON T1.cName  =  T2.cName

text_query: Find number of products which Sony does not make.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT name) FROM products WHERE name NOT IN (SELECT T1.name FROM products AS T1 JOIN manufacturers AS T2 ON T1.Manufacturer  =  T2.code WHERE T2.name  =  'Sony')

text_query: Which countries in europe have at least 3 car manufacturers?
sql_command: SELECT T1.CountryName FROM COUNTRIES AS T1 JOIN CONTINENTS AS T2 ON T1.Continent  =  T2.ContId JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T3 ON T1.CountryId  =  T3.Country WHERE T2.Continent  =  'europe' GROUP BY T1.CountryName HAVING count(*)  >=  3;

text_query: Find the number of members of club "Pen and Paper Gaming".
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid JOIN student AS t3 ON t2.stuid  =  t3.stuid WHERE t1.clubname  =  "Pen and Paper Gaming"

text_query: List the names of journalists in ascending order of years working.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM journalist ORDER BY Years_working ASC

text_query: Show the document id with paragraph text 'Brazil' and 'Ireland'.
sql_command: SELECT document_id FROM Paragraphs WHERE paragraph_text  =  'Brazil' INTERSECT SELECT document_id FROM Paragraphs WHERE paragraph_text  =  'Ireland'

text_query: Find the players whose names contain letter 'a'.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT pName FROM Player WHERE pName LIKE '%a%'

text_query: Find the name of customers who have loans of both Mortgages and Auto.
sql_command: SELECT T1.cust_name FROM customer AS T1 JOIN loan AS T2 ON T1.cust_id  =  T2.cust_id WHERE loan_type  =  'Mortgages' INTERSECT SELECT T1.cust_name FROM customer AS T1 JOIN loan AS T2 ON T1.cust_id  =  T2.cust_id WHERE loan_type  =  'Auto'

text_query: How many undergraduates are there in "San Jose State University" in year 2004?
sql_command: SELECT sum(t1.undergraduate) FROM discipline_enrollments AS t1 JOIN campuses AS t2 ON t1.campus  =  t2.id WHERE t1.year  =  2004 AND t2.campus  =  "San Jose State University"

text_query: Find the list of page size which have more than 3 product listed
sql_command: SELECT max_page_size FROM product GROUP BY max_page_size HAVING count(*)  >  3

text_query: Show all distinct location names.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT Location_Name FROM LOCATIONS

text_query: What are the price ranges of hotels?
sql_command: SELECT price_range FROM HOTELS

text_query: What are the majors of male (sex is M) students?
sql_command: SELECT Major FROM STUDENT WHERE Sex  =  "M"

text_query: Find the name of the airports located in Cuba or Argentina.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM airports WHERE country  =  'Cuba' OR country  =  'Argentina'

text_query: What are the names of people in ascending alphabetical order?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM People ORDER BY Name ASC

text_query: How many different classes are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT class_code) FROM CLASS

text_query: Which unique cities are in Asian countries where Chinese is the official language ?
sql_command: select distinct t3.name from country as t1 join countrylanguage as t2 on t1.code  =  t2.countrycode join city as t3 on t1.code  =  t3.countrycode where t2.isofficial  =  't' and t2.language  =  'chinese' and t1.continent  =  "asia"

text_query: Give me a list of descriptions of the problems that are reported by the staff whose first name is Christop.
sql_command: SELECT T1.problem_description FROM problems AS T1 JOIN staff AS T2 ON T1.reported_by_staff_id = T2.staff_id WHERE T2.staff_first_name = "Christop"

text_query: Show the names of students who have a grade higher than 5 and have at least 2 friends.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM Friend AS T1 JOIN Highschooler AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.id WHERE T2.grade  >  5 GROUP BY T1.student_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: Show writers who have published a book with price more than 4000000.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Writer FROM book AS T1 JOIN publication AS T2 ON T1.Book_ID  =  T2.Book_ID WHERE T2.Price  >  4000000

text_query: What are the maximum and minimum week on top of all volumes?
sql_command: SELECT max(Weeks_on_Top) ,  min(Weeks_on_Top) FROM volume

text_query: What are the states or counties of the address of the stores with marketing region code "CA"?
sql_command: SELECT T1.State_County FROM Addresses AS T1 JOIN Stores AS T2 ON T1.Address_ID  =  T2.Address_ID WHERE T2.Marketing_Region_Code  =  "CA"

text_query: List the builders of railways in ascending alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT Builder FROM railway ORDER BY Builder ASC

text_query: List the names of technicians in ascending order of age.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM technician ORDER BY Age ASC

text_query: How many problems does the product with the most problems have? List the number of the problems and product name.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  T1.product_name FROM product AS T1 JOIN problems AS T2 ON T1.product_id = T2.product_id GROUP BY T1.product_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name of tracks which are in both Movies and music playlists.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM tracks AS T1 JOIN playlist_tracks AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.track_id JOIN playlists AS T3 ON T2.playlist_id  =  T3.id WHERE T3.name  =  'Movies' INTERSECT SELECT T1.name FROM tracks AS T1 JOIN playlist_tracks AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.track_id JOIN playlists AS T3 ON T2.playlist_id  =  T3.id WHERE T3.name  =  'Music'

text_query: find the code of the country where has the greatest number of players.
sql_command: SELECT country_code FROM players GROUP BY country_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the name, phone number and email address of the customer who made the largest number of orders?
sql_command: SELECT T1.customer_name ,  T1.customer_phone ,  T1.customer_email FROM customers AS T1 JOIN customer_orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id GROUP BY T2.customer_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the id of instructors who didn't teach any courses?
sql_command: SELECT id FROM instructor EXCEPT SELECT id FROM teaches

text_query: Show the people that have been governor the most times.
sql_command: SELECT Governor FROM party GROUP BY Governor ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Select the name and price of all products with a price larger than or equal to $180, and sort first by price (in descending order), and then by name  (in ascending order).
sql_command: SELECT name ,  price FROM products WHERE price  >=  180 ORDER BY price DESC ,  name ASC

text_query: For each user, return the name and the average rating of reviews given by them.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  avg(T2.rating) FROM useracct AS T1 JOIN review AS T2 ON T1.u_id  =  T2.u_id GROUP BY T2.u_id

text_query: Find the name of amenity that is most common in all dorms.
sql_command: SELECT T1.amenity_name FROM dorm_amenity AS T1 JOIN has_amenity AS T2 ON T1.amenid  =  T2.amenid GROUP BY T2.amenid ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the dog name, age and weight of the dogs who have been abandoned? 1 stands for yes, and 0 stands for no.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  age ,  weight FROM Dogs WHERE abandoned_yn  =  1

text_query: List the brands of lenses that took both a picture of mountains with range 'Toubkal Atlas' and a picture of mountains with range 'Lasta Massif'
sql_command: SELECT T3.brand FROM mountain AS T1 JOIN photos AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.mountain_id JOIN camera_lens AS T3 ON T2.camera_lens_id  =  T3.id WHERE T1.range  =  'Toubkal Atlas' INTERSECT SELECT T3.brand FROM mountain AS T1 JOIN photos AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.mountain_id JOIN camera_lens AS T3 ON T2.camera_lens_id  =  T3.id WHERE T1.range  =  'Lasta Massif'

text_query: Find the names of the visitors whose membership level is higher than 4, and order the results by the level from high to low.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM visitor WHERE Level_of_membership  >  4 ORDER BY Level_of_membership DESC

text_query: Show the names of employees with role name Editor.
sql_command: SELECT T1.employee_name FROM Employees AS T1 JOIN ROLES AS T2 ON T1.role_code  =  T2.role_code WHERE T2.role_name  =  "Editor"

text_query: What is the name of the youngest editor?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM editor ORDER BY Age ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: Which classrooms are used by grade 4?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT classroom FROM list WHERE grade  =  4

text_query: List name of all tracks in Balls to the Wall.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM albums AS T1 JOIN tracks AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.genre_id WHERE T1.title = "Balls to the Wall";

text_query: How many different addresses do the students currently live?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT current_address_id) FROM Students

text_query: Show names of teachers and the number of courses they teach.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name ,  COUNT(*) FROM course_arrange AS T1 JOIN teacher AS T2 ON T1.Teacher_ID  =  T2.Teacher_ID GROUP BY T2.Name

text_query: Show the apartment type codes and the corresponding number of apartments sorted by the number of apartments in ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT apt_type_code ,  COUNT(*) FROM Apartments GROUP BY apt_type_code ORDER BY COUNT(*) ASC

text_query: List the wheels and locations of the railways.
sql_command: SELECT Wheels ,  LOCATION FROM railway

text_query: How many customers are living in city "Lake Geovannyton"?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM customers AS t1 JOIN customer_addresses AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id JOIN addresses AS t3 ON t2.address_id  =  t3.address_id WHERE t3.city  =  "Lake Geovannyton"

text_query: What are the distinct states and create time of all votes?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT state ,  created FROM votes

text_query: How many countries speak both English and Dutch?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM (SELECT T1.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "English" INTERSECT SELECT T1.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "Dutch")

text_query: Find the number of investors in total.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM INVESTORS

text_query: How many acting statuses are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT temporary_acting) FROM management

text_query: Find the make and production time of the cars that were produced in the earliest year?
sql_command: SELECT T2.Make ,  T1.Year FROM CARS_DATA AS T1 JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.MakeId WHERE T1.Year  =  (SELECT min(YEAR) FROM CARS_DATA);

text_query: Return the names of songs for which format is mp3 and resolution is below 1000.
sql_command: SELECT T2.song_name FROM files AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.f_id  =  T2.f_id WHERE T1.formats  =  "mp3" INTERSECT SELECT song_name FROM song WHERE resolution  <  1000

text_query: What is the content of TV Channel with serial name "Sky Radio"?
sql_command: SELECT Content FROM TV_Channel WHERE series_name = "Sky Radio";

text_query: Find the id and last name of the student that has the most behavior incidents?
sql_command: SELECT T1.student_id ,  T2.last_name FROM Behavior_Incident AS T1 JOIN Students AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.student_id GROUP BY T1.student_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name of the department that offers the highest total credits?
sql_command: SELECT dept_name FROM course GROUP BY dept_name ORDER BY sum(credits) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the dates of transactions with at least 100 share count or amount bigger than 100?
sql_command: SELECT date_of_transaction FROM TRANSACTIONS WHERE share_count  >=  100 OR amount_of_transaction  >=  100

text_query: What is the description of the treatment type that costs the least money in total?
sql_command: SELECT T1.treatment_type_description FROM Treatment_types AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 ON T1.treatment_type_code  =  T2.treatment_type_code GROUP BY T1.treatment_type_code ORDER BY sum(cost_of_treatment) ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: When is the last day any resident moved in?
sql_command: SELECT max(date_moved_in) FROM Residents

text_query: Show each premise type and the number of premises in that type.
sql_command: SELECT premises_type ,  count(*) FROM premises GROUP BY premises_type

text_query: What are the ids of stations that have latitude above 37.4 and never had bike availability below 7?
sql_command: SELECT id FROM station WHERE lat  >  37.4 EXCEPT SELECT station_id FROM status GROUP BY station_id HAVING min(bikes_available)  <  7

text_query: Show different publishers together with the number of publications they have.
sql_command: SELECT Publisher ,  COUNT(*) FROM publication GROUP BY Publisher

text_query: Find the names of schools that have some players in the mid position but not in the goalie position.
sql_command: SELECT cName FROM  tryout WHERE pPos  =  'mid' EXCEPT SELECT cName FROM  tryout WHERE pPos  =  'goalie'

text_query: Report the number of students in each classroom.
sql_command: SELECT classroom ,  count(*) FROM list GROUP BY classroom

text_query: What are the average prices and cases of wines produced in the year of 2009 and made of Zinfandel grape?
sql_command: SELECT AVG(Price) ,  AVG(Cases) FROM WINE WHERE YEAR  =  2009 AND Grape  =  "Zinfandel"

text_query: Show total hours per week and number of games played for student David Shieber.
sql_command: SELECT sum(hoursperweek) ,  sum(gamesplayed) FROM Sportsinfo AS T1 JOIN Student AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  T2.StuID WHERE T2.Fname  =  "David" AND T2.Lname  =  "Shieber"

text_query: Show all dates of transactions whose type code is "SALE".
sql_command: SELECT date_of_transaction FROM TRANSACTIONS WHERE transaction_type_code  =  "SALE"

text_query: Show the name of the customer who has the most orders.
sql_command: SELECT T1.customer_name FROM customers AS T1 JOIN customer_orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id GROUP BY T1.customer_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many friends does the high school student Kyle have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Friend AS T1 JOIN Highschooler AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.id WHERE T2.name  =  "Kyle"

text_query: How many instruments does the song "Badlands" use?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT instrument) FROM instruments AS T1 JOIN songs AS T2 ON T1.songid  =  T2.songid WHERE title  =  "Badlands"

text_query: Of all the claims, what was the earliest date when any claim was made?
sql_command: SELECT Date_Claim_Made FROM Claims ORDER BY Date_Claim_Made ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the origins from which more than 1 train starts.
sql_command: SELECT origin FROM train GROUP BY origin HAVING count(*)  >  1

text_query: Show the document type code with fewer than 3 documents.
sql_command: SELECT document_type_code FROM Documents GROUP BY document_type_code HAVING count(*)  <  3

text_query: Find the maximum weight for each type of pet. List the maximum weight and pet type.
sql_command: SELECT max(weight) ,  petType FROM pets GROUP BY petType

text_query: Show the names of customers who have both an order in completed status and an order in part status.
sql_command: SELECT T1.customer_name FROM customers AS T1 JOIN customer_orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE T2.order_status_code  =  'Completed' INTERSECT SELECT T1.customer_name FROM customers AS T1 JOIN customer_orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE T2.order_status_code  =  'Part'

text_query: How many sections does course ACCT-211 has?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT class_section) FROM CLASS WHERE crs_code  =  'ACCT-211'

text_query: Find the name of project that continues for the longest time.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM projects ORDER BY hours DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the GDP and population of the city that already served as a host more than once?
sql_command: SELECT t1.gdp ,  t1.Regional_Population FROM city AS T1 JOIN hosting_city AS T2 ON T1.city_id  =  T2.host_city GROUP BY t2.Host_City HAVING count(*)  >  1

text_query: Show the name of the shop that have the largest quantity of devices in stock.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Shop_Name FROM stock AS T1 JOIN shop AS T2 ON T1.Shop_ID  =  T2.Shop_ID GROUP BY T1.Shop_ID ORDER BY SUM(T1.quantity) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many engineer visits are required at most for a single fault log? List the number and the log entry id.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  T1.fault_log_entry_id FROM Fault_Log AS T1 JOIN Engineer_Visits AS T2 ON T1.fault_log_entry_id  =  T2.fault_log_entry_id GROUP BY T1.fault_log_entry_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the names of journalists who have not reported any event.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM journalist WHERE journalist_ID NOT IN (SELECT journalist_ID FROM news_report)

text_query: How many kinds of enzymes are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM enzyme

text_query: Which third party companies have at least 2 maintenance engineers or have at least 2 maintenance contracts? List the company id and name.
sql_command: SELECT T1.company_id ,  T1.company_name FROM Third_Party_Companies AS T1 JOIN Maintenance_Engineers AS T2 ON T1.company_id  =  T2.company_id GROUP BY T1.company_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2 UNION SELECT T3.company_id ,  T3.company_name FROM Third_Party_Companies AS T3 JOIN Maintenance_Contracts AS T4 ON T3.company_id  =  T4.maintenance_contract_company_id GROUP BY T3.company_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: Show the names of products and the number of events they are in, sorted by the number of events in descending order.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Product_Name ,  COUNT(*) FROM Products AS T1 JOIN Products_in_Events AS T2 ON T1.Product_ID  =  T2.Product_ID GROUP BY T1.Product_Name ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC

text_query: What are the completion dates of all the tests that have result "Fail"?
sql_command: SELECT T1.date_of_completion FROM Student_Course_Enrolment AS T1 JOIN Student_Tests_Taken AS T2 ON T1.registration_id  =  T2.registration_id WHERE T2.test_result  =  "Fail"

text_query: How many draft copies does the document with id 2 have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Draft_Copies WHERE document_id = 2;

text_query: Show different types of ships and the average tonnage of ships of each type.
sql_command: SELECT TYPE ,  avg(Tonnage) FROM ship GROUP BY TYPE

text_query: What is the name of the artist who joined latest?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM artist ORDER BY year_join DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name and city of the airport which is the source for the most number of flight routes.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name ,  T1.city ,  T2.src_apid FROM airports AS T1 JOIN routes AS T2 ON T1.apid  =  T2.src_apid GROUP BY T2.src_apid ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the top 3 products which have the largest number of problems?
sql_command: SELECT T2.product_name FROM problems AS T1 JOIN product AS T2 ON T1.product_id = T2.product_id GROUP BY T2.product_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 3

text_query: Show the number of buildings with a height above the average or a number of floors above the average.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM building WHERE height_feet  >  (SELECT avg(height_feet) FROM building) OR floors  >  (SELECT avg(floors) FROM building)

text_query: What is the structure of the document with the least number of accesses?
sql_command: SELECT t2.document_structure_description FROM documents AS t1 JOIN document_structures AS t2 ON t1.document_structure_code  =  t2.document_structure_code GROUP BY t1.document_structure_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the names of programs that are never broadcasted in the morning.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM program EXCEPT SELECT t1.name FROM program AS t1 JOIN broadcast AS t2 ON t1.program_id  =  t2.program_id WHERE t2.Time_of_day  =  "Morning"

text_query: Show the name, location, open year for all tracks with a seating higher than the average.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  LOCATION ,  year_opened FROM track WHERE seating  >  (SELECT avg(seating) FROM track)

text_query: Show order ids and the total quantity in each order.
sql_command: SELECT order_id ,  sum(product_quantity) FROM Order_items GROUP BY order_id

text_query: What is the budget type code with most number of documents.
sql_command: SELECT budget_type_code FROM Documents_with_expenses GROUP BY budget_type_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find all invoice dates corresponding to customers with first name Astrid and last name Gruber.
sql_command: SELECT T2.InvoiceDate FROM CUSTOMER AS T1 JOIN INVOICE AS T2 ON T1.CustomerId  =  T2.CustomerId WHERE T1.FirstName  =  "Astrid" AND LastName  =  "Gruber"

text_query: What are the full name (first and last name) and salary for all employees who does not have any value for commission?
sql_command: SELECT first_name ,  last_name ,  salary FROM  employees WHERE commission_pct  =  "null"

text_query: Which of the airport names contains the word 'international'?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM airport WHERE name LIKE '%international%'

text_query: Find the names and phone numbers of customers living in California state.
sql_command: SELECT t1.customer_name ,  t1.customer_phone FROM customers AS t1 JOIN customer_addresses AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id JOIN addresses AS t3 ON t2.address_id  =  t3.address_id WHERE t3.state_province_county  =  'California'

text_query: Find the number of scientists involved for each project name.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  T1.name FROM projects AS T1 JOIN assignedto AS T2 ON T1.code  =  T2.project GROUP BY T1.name

text_query: How many different scientists are assigned to any project?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT scientist) FROM assignedto

text_query: What is the maximum stars and year for the most recent movie?
sql_command: SELECT max(T1.stars) ,  T2.year FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID WHERE T2.year  =  (SELECT max(YEAR) FROM Movie)

text_query: What are all the section titles of the document named "David CV"?
sql_command: SELECT t2.section_title FROM documents AS t1 JOIN document_sections AS t2 ON t1.document_code  =  t2.document_code WHERE t1.document_name  =  "David CV"

text_query: How many gas station are opened between 2000 and 2005?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM gas_station WHERE open_year BETWEEN 2000 AND 2005

text_query: Show all role codes and the number of employees in each role.
sql_command: SELECT role_code ,  count(*) FROM Employees GROUP BY role_code

text_query: Please show the names of the buildings whose status is "on-hold", in ascending order of stories.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM buildings WHERE Status  =  "on-hold" ORDER BY Stories ASC

text_query: What is the gender of the student Linda Smith?
sql_command: SELECT Sex FROM Student WHERE Fname = "Linda" AND Lname = "Smith";

text_query: What is the average GNP and total population in all nations whose government is US territory?
sql_command: SELECT avg(GNP) ,  sum(population) FROM country WHERE GovernmentForm  =  "US Territory"

text_query: Find the first names of all instructors who have taught some course and the course description.
sql_command: SELECT T2.emp_fname ,  T3.crs_description FROM CLASS AS T1 JOIN employee AS T2 ON T1.prof_num  =  T2.emp_num JOIN course AS T3 ON T1.crs_code  =  T3.crs_code

text_query: Find the distinct ages of students who have secretary votes in the fall election cycle.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Age FROM STUDENT AS T1 JOIN VOTING_RECORD AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  T2.Secretary_Vote WHERE T2.Election_Cycle  =  "Fall"

text_query: List players' first name and last name who have weight greater than 220 or height shorter than 75.
sql_command: SELECT name_first ,  name_last FROM player WHERE weight  >  220 OR height  <  75

text_query: What is the title of the course that was offered at building Chandler during the fall semester in the year of 2010?
sql_command: SELECT T1.title FROM course AS T1 JOIN SECTION AS T2 ON T1.course_id  =  T2.course_id WHERE building  =  'Chandler' AND semester  =  'Fall' AND YEAR  =  2010

text_query: List the types of competition and the number of competitions of each type.
sql_command: SELECT Competition_type ,  COUNT(*) FROM competition GROUP BY Competition_type

text_query: Please show the different record companies and the corresponding number of orchestras.
sql_command: SELECT Record_Company ,  COUNT(*) FROM orchestra GROUP BY Record_Company

text_query: How many problems are there for product voluptatem?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM product AS T1 JOIN problems AS T2 ON T1.product_id = T2.product_id WHERE T1.product_name = "voluptatem"

text_query: Show the names of pilots and the number of records they have.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Pilot_name ,  COUNT(*) FROM pilot_record AS T1 JOIN pilot AS T2 ON T1.pilot_ID  =  T2.pilot_ID GROUP BY T2.Pilot_name

text_query: What is the description for the budget type with code ORG?
sql_command: SELECT budget_type_description FROM Ref_budget_codes WHERE budget_type_code  =  "ORG"

text_query: Find the department name and room of the course INTRODUCTION TO COMPUTER SCIENCE.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Dname ,  T2.Room FROM COURSE AS T1 JOIN DEPARTMENT AS T2 ON T1.DNO  =  T2.DNO WHERE T1.CName  =  "INTRODUCTION TO COMPUTER SCIENCE"

text_query: How many players are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM player

text_query: List the camera lens names containing substring "Digital".
sql_command: SELECT name FROM camera_lens WHERE name LIKE "%Digital%"

text_query: How many ships ended up being 'Captured'?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM ship WHERE disposition_of_ship  =  'Captured'

text_query: Find the saving balance of the account with the highest checking balance.
sql_command: SELECT T3.balance FROM accounts AS T1 JOIN checking AS T2 ON T1.custid  =  T2.custid JOIN savings AS T3 ON T1.custid  =  T3.custid ORDER BY T2.balance DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many trains have 'Express' in their names?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM train WHERE name LIKE "%Express%"

text_query: Find the number of clubs where "Tracy Kim" is a member.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid JOIN student AS t3 ON t2.stuid  =  t3.stuid WHERE t3.fname  =  "Tracy" AND t3.lname  =  "Kim"

text_query: What is the total enrollment number of all colleges?
sql_command: SELECT sum(enr) FROM College

text_query: What are the names of countries that have both players with position forward and players with position defender?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Country_name FROM country AS T1 JOIN match_season AS T2 ON T1.Country_id  =  T2.Country WHERE T2.Position  =  "Forward" INTERSECT SELECT T1.Country_name FROM country AS T1 JOIN match_season AS T2 ON T1.Country_id  =  T2.Country WHERE T2.Position  =  "Defender"

text_query: Find the forename and surname of drivers whose nationality is German?
sql_command: SELECT forename ,  surname FROM drivers WHERE nationality = "German"

text_query: How many assets can each parts be used in? List the part name and the number.
sql_command: SELECT T1.part_name ,  count(*) FROM Parts AS T1 JOIN Asset_Parts AS T2 ON T1.part_id  =  T2.part_id GROUP BY T1.part_name

text_query: Find the last names of students studying in room 111.
sql_command: SELECT lastname FROM list WHERE classroom  =  111

text_query: Show the location codes and the number of documents in each location.
sql_command: SELECT location_code ,  count(*) FROM Document_locations GROUP BY location_code

text_query: What are first and last names of players participating in all star game in 1998?
sql_command: SELECT name_first ,  name_last FROM player AS T1 JOIN all_star AS T2 ON T1.player_id  =  T2.player_id WHERE YEAR  =  1998

text_query: Find the abbreviation and country of the airline that has fewest number of flights?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Abbreviation ,  T1.Country FROM AIRLINES AS T1 JOIN FLIGHTS AS T2 ON T1.uid  =  T2.Airline GROUP BY T1.Airline ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

text_query: Where does the staff member with the first name Elsa live?
sql_command: SELECT T2.address FROM staff AS T1 JOIN address AS T2 ON T1.address_id  =  T2.address_id WHERE T1.first_name  =  'Elsa'

text_query: How many dogs went through any treatments?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT dog_id) FROM Treatments

text_query: List the writers who have written more than one book.
sql_command: SELECT Writer FROM book GROUP BY Writer HAVING COUNT(*)  >  1

text_query: Find the payment method code used by more than 3 parties.
sql_command: SELECT payment_method_code FROM parties GROUP BY payment_method_code HAVING count(*)  >  3

text_query: How many orders have detail "Second time"?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM customer_orders WHERE order_details  =  "Second time"

text_query: How many days had both mean humidity above 50 and mean visibility above 8?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM weather WHERE mean_humidity  >  50 AND mean_visibility_miles  >  8

text_query: Find the last name and gender of the students who are playing both Call of Destiny and Works of Widenius games.
sql_command: SELECT lname ,  sex FROM Student WHERE StuID IN (SELECT T1.StuID FROM Plays_games AS T1 JOIN Video_games AS T2 ON T1.GameID  =  T2.GameID WHERE T2.Gname  =  "Call of Destiny" INTERSECT SELECT T1.StuID FROM Plays_games AS T1 JOIN Video_games AS T2 ON T1.GameID  =  T2.GameID WHERE T2.Gname  =  "Works of Widenius")

text_query: What is the number of states that has some college whose enrollment is larger than the average enrollment?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT state) FROM college WHERE enr  >  (SELECT avg(enr) FROM college)

text_query: display the ID for those employees who did two or more jobs in the past.
sql_command: SELECT employee_id FROM job_history GROUP BY employee_id HAVING COUNT(*)  >= 2

text_query: How many departments offer any degree?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT department_id) FROM Degree_Programs

text_query: What are the maximum, minimum and average home games each stadium held?
sql_command: SELECT max(home_games) ,  min(home_games) ,  avg(home_games) FROM stadium

text_query: What is the id, forname and surname of the driver who had the first position in terms of laptime at least twice?
sql_command: SELECT T1.driverid ,  T1.forename ,  T1.surname FROM drivers AS T1 JOIN laptimes AS T2 ON T1.driverid = T2.driverid WHERE POSITION  =  '1' GROUP BY T1.driverid HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: How many faculty do we have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Faculty

text_query: How many students are not involved in any behavior incident?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM STUDENTS WHERE student_id NOT IN ( SELECT student_id FROM Behavior_Incident )

text_query: Find the names of procedures which physician John Wen was trained in.
sql_command: SELECT T3.name FROM physician AS T1 JOIN trained_in AS T2 ON T1.employeeid  =  T2.physician JOIN procedures AS T3 ON T3.code  =  T2.treatment WHERE T1.name  =  "John Wen"

text_query: For each faculty rank, show the number of faculty members who have it.
sql_command: SELECT rank ,  count(*) FROM Faculty GROUP BY rank

text_query: Find the total amount claimed in the most recently created document.
sql_command: SELECT sum(t1.amount_claimed) FROM claim_headers AS t1 JOIN claims_documents AS t2 ON t1.claim_header_id  =  t2.claim_id WHERE t2.created_date  =  (SELECT created_date FROM claims_documents ORDER BY created_date LIMIT 1)

text_query: What are the weights of entrepreneurs in descending order of money requested?
sql_command: SELECT T2.Weight FROM entrepreneur AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID ORDER BY T1.Money_Requested DESC

text_query: How many assets does each maintenance contract contain? List the number and the contract id.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  T1.maintenance_contract_id FROM Maintenance_Contracts AS T1 JOIN Assets AS T2 ON T1.maintenance_contract_id  =  T2.maintenance_contract_id GROUP BY T1.maintenance_contract_id

text_query: Find all the songs performed by artist with last name "Heilo"
sql_command: SELECT T3.Title FROM Performance AS T1 JOIN Band AS T2 ON T1.bandmate  =  T2.id JOIN Songs AS T3 ON T3.SongId  =  T1.SongId WHERE T2.Lastname  =  "Heilo"

text_query: Show statement id, statement detail, account detail for accounts.
sql_command: SELECT T1.statement_id ,  T2.statement_details ,  T1.account_details FROM Accounts AS T1 JOIN Statements AS T2 ON T1.statement_id  =  T2.statement_id

text_query: Find the id and forenames of drivers who participated both the races with name Australian Grand Prix and the races with name Chinese Grand Prix?
sql_command: SELECT T2.driverid ,  T3.forename FROM races AS T1 JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.raceid = T2.raceid JOIN drivers AS T3 ON T2.driverid  =  T3.driverid WHERE T1.name = "Australian Grand Prix" INTERSECT SELECT T2.driverid ,  T3.forename FROM races AS T1 JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.raceid = T2.raceid JOIN drivers AS T3 ON T2.driverid  =  T3.driverid WHERE T1.name = "Chinese Grand Prix"

text_query: Find the person who has exactly one friend.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM PersonFriend GROUP BY name HAVING count(*)  =  1

text_query: Show the record companies shared by orchestras founded before 2003 and after 2003.
sql_command: SELECT Record_Company FROM orchestra WHERE Year_of_Founded  <  2003 INTERSECT SELECT Record_Company FROM orchestra WHERE Year_of_Founded  >  2003

text_query: How many flights depart from 'APG'?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM FLIGHTS WHERE SourceAirport  =  "APG"

text_query: find the name of driver who is driving the school bus with the longest working history.
sql_command: SELECT t1.name FROM driver AS t1 JOIN school_bus AS t2 ON t1.driver_id  =  t2.driver_id ORDER BY years_working DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show ids, customer ids, names for all accounts.
sql_command: SELECT account_id ,  customer_id ,  account_name FROM Accounts

text_query: what is the address of history department?
sql_command: SELECT dept_address FROM department WHERE dept_name  =  'History'

text_query: List top 10 employee work longest in the company. List employee's first and last name.
sql_command: SELECT first_name , last_name FROM employees ORDER BY hire_date ASC LIMIT 10;

text_query: Show the name and service for all trains in order by time.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  service FROM train ORDER BY TIME

text_query: What activities do we have?
sql_command: SELECT activity_name FROM Activity

text_query: How many teachers does the student named MADLOCK RAY have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM list AS T1 JOIN teachers AS T2 ON T1.classroom  =  T2.classroom WHERE T1.firstname  =  "MADLOCK" AND T1.lastname  =  "RAY"

text_query: Show all storm names except for those with at least two affected regions.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM storm EXCEPT SELECT T1.name FROM storm AS T1 JOIN affected_region AS T2 ON T1.storm_id  =  T2.storm_id GROUP BY T1.storm_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: What is the name of the tallest building?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM building ORDER BY height_feet DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the names of customers who never ordered product Latte.
sql_command: SELECT customer_name FROM customers EXCEPT SELECT t1.customer_name FROM customers AS t1 JOIN customer_orders AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id JOIN order_items AS t3 ON t2.order_id  =  t3.order_id JOIN products AS t4 ON t3.product_id  =  t4.product_id WHERE t4.product_details  =  'Latte'

text_query: What are the names and areas of countries with the top 5 largest area?
sql_command: SELECT Name ,  SurfaceArea FROM country ORDER BY SurfaceArea DESC LIMIT 5

text_query: List the codes of all courses that take place in room KLR209.
sql_command: SELECT class_code FROM CLASS WHERE class_room  =  'KLR209'

text_query: What is the product ID of the most frequently ordered item on invoices?
sql_command: SELECT Product_ID FROM INVOICES GROUP BY Product_ID ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the birthday of the staff member with first name as Janessa and last name as Sawayn?
sql_command: SELECT date_of_birth FROM Staff WHERE first_name = "Janessa" AND last_name = "Sawayn";

text_query: Which dogs are owned by someone who lives in Virginia? List the owner's first name and the dog's name.
sql_command: SELECT T1.first_name ,  T2.name FROM Owners AS T1 JOIN Dogs AS T2 ON T1.owner_id  =  T2.owner_id WHERE T1.state  =  'Virginia'

text_query: When are the birthdays of customer who are classified as 'Good Customer' status?
sql_command: SELECT date_of_birth FROM Customers WHERE customer_status_code  =  'Good Customer'

text_query: How many companies are headquartered in the US?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM company WHERE Headquarters  =  'USA'

text_query: What is the total number of people living in the nations that do not use English?
sql_command: SELECT sum(Population) FROM country WHERE Name NOT IN (SELECT T1.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "English")

text_query: What are the average fastest lap speed in races held after 2004 grouped by race name and ordered by year?
sql_command: SELECT avg(T2.fastestlapspeed) ,  T1.name ,  T1.year FROM races AS T1 JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.raceid = T2.raceid WHERE T1.year > 2014 GROUP BY T1.name ORDER BY T1.year

text_query: What is Astrid Gruber's email and phone number?
sql_command: SELECT email ,  phone FROM customers WHERE first_name = "Astrid" AND last_name = "Gruber";

text_query: Show the lieutenant governor and comptroller from the democratic party.
sql_command: SELECT Lieutenant_Governor ,  Comptroller FROM party WHERE Party  =  "Democratic"

text_query: What is the abbreviation of Airline "JetBlue Airways"?
sql_command: SELECT Abbreviation FROM AIRLINES WHERE Airline  =  "JetBlue Airways"

text_query: Find the employee id for all employees who earn more than the average salary.
sql_command: SELECT employee_id FROM employees WHERE salary  >  (SELECT AVG(salary) FROM employees)

text_query: What are the order details of the products with price higher than 2000?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Other_Item_Details FROM ORDER_ITEMS AS T1 JOIN Products AS T2 ON T1.Product_ID  =  T2.Product_ID WHERE T2.Product_price  >  2000

text_query: How many distinct courses are enrolled in by students?
sql_command: SELECT count(course_id) FROM Student_Course_Enrolment

text_query: Which Advisor has most of students? List advisor and the number of students.
sql_command: SELECT Advisor ,  count(*) FROM Student GROUP BY Advisor ORDER BY count(Advisor) DESC LIMIT 1;

text_query: list names of all departments ordered by their names.
sql_command: SELECT dept_name FROM department ORDER BY dept_name

text_query: Which allergy type has most number of allergies?
sql_command: SELECT allergytype FROM Allergy_type GROUP BY allergytype ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the name and count of each product in all orders.
sql_command: SELECT T3.product_name ,  count(*) FROM orders AS T1 JOIN order_items AS T2 JOIN products AS T3 ON T1.order_id = T2.order_id AND T2.product_id = T3.product_id GROUP BY T3.product_id

text_query: Find the salary and manager number for those employees who is working under a manager.
sql_command: SELECT salary ,  manager_id FROM employees WHERE manager_id != "null"

text_query: Return the apartment number and the number of rooms for each apartment.
sql_command: SELECT apt_number ,  room_count FROM Apartments

text_query: What is the average, minimum, maximum, and total transaction amount?
sql_command: SELECT avg(transaction_amount) ,  min(transaction_amount) ,  max(transaction_amount) ,   sum(transaction_amount) FROM Financial_transactions

text_query: List the names of all distinct medications, ordered in an alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT name FROM medication ORDER BY name

text_query: List the full name (first and last name), and salary for those employees who earn below 6000.
sql_command: SELECT first_name ,  last_name ,  salary FROM employees WHERE salary  <  6000

text_query: Find the names of states that have some college students playing in the mid position but not in the goalie position.
sql_command: SELECT T1.state FROM college AS T1 JOIN tryout AS T2 ON T1.cName  =  T2.cName WHERE T2.pPos  =  'mid' EXCEPT SELECT T1.state FROM college AS T1 JOIN tryout AS T2 ON T1.cName  =  T2.cName WHERE T2.pPos  =  'goalie'

text_query: What are the characters and duration of actors?
sql_command: SELECT Character ,  Duration FROM actor

text_query: Find the number of classes in each department.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  dept_code FROM CLASS AS T1 JOIN course AS T2 ON T1.crs_code  =  T2.crs_code GROUP BY dept_code

text_query: List all information about the assessment notes sorted by date in ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT * FROM Assessment_Notes ORDER BY date_of_notes ASC

text_query: Which distinct source system code includes the substring 'en'?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT source_system_code FROM cmi_cross_references WHERE source_system_code LIKE '%en%'

text_query: Eduardo Martins is a customer at which company?
sql_command: SELECT company FROM customers WHERE first_name = "Eduardo" AND last_name = "Martins";

text_query: List the height and weight of people in descending order of height.
sql_command: SELECT Height ,  Weight FROM people ORDER BY Height DESC

text_query: What are the first name, last name and id of the player with the most all star game experiences? Also list the count.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name_first , T1.name_last ,  T1.player_id ,   count(*) FROM player AS T1 JOIN all_star AS T2 ON T1.player_id  =  T2.player_id GROUP BY T1.player_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1;

text_query: Who are enrolled in 2 degree programs in one semester? List the first name, middle name and last name and the id.
sql_command: SELECT T1.first_name ,  T1.middle_name ,  T1.last_name ,  T1.student_id FROM Students AS T1 JOIN Student_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.student_id GROUP BY T1.student_id HAVING count(*)  =  2

text_query: What is the maximum enrollment across all schools?
sql_command: SELECT max(Enrollment) FROM university

text_query: How many distinct kinds of camera lenses are used to take photos of mountains in the country 'Ethiopia'?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT T2.camera_lens_id) FROM mountain AS T1 JOIN photos AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.mountain_id WHERE T1.country  =  'Ethiopia'

text_query: Give me the zip code where the average mean humidity is below 70 and at least 100 trips took place.
sql_command: SELECT zip_code FROM weather GROUP BY zip_code HAVING avg(mean_humidity)  <  70 INTERSECT SELECT zip_code FROM trip GROUP BY zip_code HAVING count(*)  >=  100

text_query: What is the id and trade name of the medicines can interact with at least 3 enzymes?
sql_command: SELECT T1.id ,  T1.trade_name FROM medicine AS T1 JOIN medicine_enzyme_interaction AS T2 ON T2.medicine_id  =  T1.id GROUP BY T1.id HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  3

text_query: Show flight number, origin, destination of all flights in the alphabetical order of the departure cities.
sql_command: SELECT flno ,  origin ,  destination FROM Flight ORDER BY origin

text_query: List the season, home team, away team of all the games.
sql_command: SELECT season ,  home_team ,  away_team FROM game

text_query: What is the car model with the highest mpg ?
sql_command: select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid  =  t2.id order by t2.mpg desc limit 1;

text_query: Which colleges do the tryout players whose name starts with letter D go to?
sql_command: SELECT T1.cName FROM  tryout AS T1 JOIN player AS T2 ON T1.pID  =  T2.pID WHERE T2.pName LIKE 'D%'

text_query: What are all the locations with a cinema?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT LOCATION FROM cinema

text_query: Find the campus fee of "San Jose State University" in year 2000.
sql_command: SELECT t1.campusfee FROM csu_fees AS t1 JOIN campuses AS t2 ON t1.campus  =  t2.id WHERE t2.campus  =  "San Jose State University" AND t1.year  =  2000

text_query: Report the total number of students for each fourth-grade classroom.
sql_command: SELECT classroom ,  count(*) FROM list WHERE grade  =  "4" GROUP BY classroom

text_query: How many airports are there per country? Order the countries by decreasing number of airports.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  country FROM airports GROUP BY country ORDER BY count(*) DESC

text_query: Show the price ranges of hotels with 5 star ratings.
sql_command: SELECT price_range FROM HOTELS WHERE star_rating_code  =  "5"

text_query: Find the number of dog pets that are raised by female students (with sex F).
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM student AS T1 JOIN has_pet AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid JOIN pets AS T3 ON T2.petid  =  T3.petid WHERE T1.sex  =  'F' AND T3.pettype  =  'dog'

text_query: Who is the director of movie Avatar?
sql_command: SELECT director FROM Movie WHERE title  = 'Avatar'

text_query: Find the maximum age of all the students.
sql_command: SELECT max(Age) FROM STUDENT

text_query: Find the average fee on a CSU campus in 1996
sql_command: SELECT avg(campusfee) FROM csu_fees WHERE YEAR  =  1996

text_query: Find the names of customers who have bought by at least three distinct products.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.customer_name FROM customers AS T1 JOIN customer_orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id JOIN order_items AS T3 ON T2.order_id  =  T3.order_id GROUP BY T1.customer_id HAVING COUNT (DISTINCT T3.product_id)  >=  3

text_query: Find courses that ran in Fall 2009 but not in Spring 2010.
sql_command: SELECT course_id FROM SECTION WHERE semester  =  'Fall' AND YEAR  =  2009 EXCEPT SELECT course_id FROM SECTION WHERE semester  =  'Spring' AND YEAR  =  2010

text_query: What are the average and minimum price (in Euro) of all products?
sql_command: SELECT avg(price_in_euros) ,  min(price_in_euros) FROM catalog_contents

text_query: Find all years that have a movie that received a rating of 4 or 5, and sort them in increasing order of year.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT YEAR FROM Movie AS T1 JOIN Rating AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID WHERE T2.stars  >=  4 ORDER BY T1.year

text_query: List the names of buildings in descending order of building height.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM buildings ORDER BY Height DESC

text_query: What are all distinct country for artists?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT country FROM artist

text_query: Find the number of funiture types produced by each manufacturer as well as the company names.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  t1.name FROM manufacturer AS t1 JOIN furniture_manufacte AS t2 ON t1.manufacturer_id  =  t2.manufacturer_id GROUP BY t1.manufacturer_id

text_query: Find the number of people whose age is greater than all engineers.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Person WHERE age  >  (SELECT max(age) FROM person WHERE job  =  'engineer')

text_query: Return all the committees that have delegates from Democratic party.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Committee FROM election AS T1 JOIN party AS T2 ON T1.Party  =  T2.Party_ID WHERE T2.Party  =  "Democratic"

text_query: What is the description of the marketing region China?
sql_command: SELECT Marketing_Region_Descriptrion FROM Marketing_Regions WHERE Marketing_Region_Name  =  "China"

text_query: List the writers of the books in ascending alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT Writer FROM book ORDER BY Writer ASC

text_query: What is the name of the body builder with the greatest body weight?
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name FROM body_builder AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.People_ID  =  T2.People_ID ORDER BY T2.Weight DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: When was the first asset acquired?
sql_command: SELECT asset_acquired_date FROM Assets ORDER BY asset_acquired_date ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the maximum and minimum budget of the departments?
sql_command: SELECT max(budget_in_billions) ,  min(budget_in_billions) FROM department

text_query: Return the unique name for stations that have ever had 7 bikes available.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.name FROM station AS T1 JOIN status AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.station_id WHERE T2.bikes_available  =  7

text_query: What is the film title and inventory id of the item in the inventory which was rented most frequently?
sql_command: SELECT T1.title ,  T2.inventory_id FROM film AS T1 JOIN inventory AS T2 ON T1.film_id  =  T2.film_id JOIN rental AS T3 ON T2.inventory_id  =  T3.inventory_id GROUP BY T2.inventory_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the name of the most common genre in all tracks?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name FROM GENRE AS T1 JOIN TRACK AS T2 ON T1.GenreId  =  T2.GenreId GROUP BY T2.GenreId ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the id and star rating of each hotel, ordered by its price from low to high.
sql_command: SELECT hotel_id ,  star_rating_code FROM HOTELS ORDER BY price_range ASC

text_query: What are the names of the heads who are born outside the California state?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM head WHERE born_state != 'California'

text_query: Show the names of pilots and fleet series of the aircrafts they have flied with in ascending order of the rank of the pilot.
sql_command: SELECT T3.Pilot_name ,  T2.Fleet_Series FROM pilot_record AS T1 JOIN aircraft AS T2 ON T1.Aircraft_ID  =  T2.Aircraft_ID JOIN pilot AS T3 ON T1.Pilot_ID  =  T3.Pilot_ID ORDER BY T3.Rank

text_query: Show the product ids and the number of unique orders containing each product.
sql_command: SELECT product_id ,  count(DISTINCT order_id) FROM Order_items GROUP BY product_id

text_query: Find the total access count of all documents in the most popular document type.
sql_command: SELECT sum(access_count) FROM documents GROUP BY document_type_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show flight number for all flights with more than 2000 distance.
sql_command: SELECT flno FROM Flight WHERE distance  >  2000

text_query: When did the web accelerator 'CACHEbox' and browser 'Internet Explorer' become compatible?
sql_command: SELECT T1.compatible_since_year FROM accelerator_compatible_browser AS T1 JOIN browser AS T2 ON T1.browser_id  =  T2.id JOIN web_client_accelerator AS T3 ON T1.accelerator_id  =  T3.id WHERE T3.name  =  'CACHEbox' AND T2.name  =  'Internet Explorer'

text_query: Show the names of members in ascending order of their rank in rounds.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name FROM member AS T1 JOIN round AS T2 ON T1.Member_ID  =  T2.Member_ID ORDER BY Rank_in_Round ASC

text_query: How many employees have certificate.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT eid) FROM Certificate

text_query: What are the actual delivery dates of orders with quantity 1?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Actual_Delivery_Date FROM Customer_Orders AS T1 JOIN ORDER_ITEMS AS T2 ON T1.Order_ID  =  T2.Order_ID WHERE T2.Order_Quantity  =  1

text_query: Which city does has most number of customers?
sql_command: SELECT T2.city FROM Customers AS T1 JOIN Addresses AS T2 ON T1.customer_address_id = T2.address_id GROUP BY T2.city ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1;

text_query: What is the maximum total amount paid by a customer? List the customer id and amount.
sql_command: SELECT customer_id ,  sum(amount_paid) FROM Payments GROUP BY customer_id ORDER BY sum(amount_paid) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the names of all of the high schooler Kyle's friends.
sql_command: SELECT T3.name FROM Friend AS T1 JOIN Highschooler AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.id JOIN Highschooler AS T3 ON T1.friend_id  =  T3.id WHERE T2.name  =  "Kyle"

text_query: Show the name of each county along with the corresponding number of delegates from that county.
sql_command: SELECT T1.County_name ,  COUNT(*) FROM county AS T1 JOIN election AS T2 ON T1.County_id  =  T2.District GROUP BY T1.County_id

text_query: List the names of all distinct wines ordered by price.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT Name FROM WINE ORDER BY price

text_query: What are the date of ceremony of music festivals with category "Best Song" and result "Awarded"?
sql_command: SELECT Date_of_ceremony FROM music_festival WHERE Category  =  "Best Song" AND RESULT  =  "Awarded"

text_query: How many schools have some students playing in goalie and mid positions.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM (SELECT cName FROM  tryout WHERE pPos  =  'goalie' INTERSECT SELECT cName FROM  tryout WHERE pPos  =  'mid')

text_query: Show the average, minimum, and maximum age for different majors.
sql_command: SELECT major ,  avg(age) ,  min(age) ,  max(age) FROM Student GROUP BY major

text_query: Find the names of females who are friends with Zach
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM Person AS T1 JOIN PersonFriend AS T2 ON T1.name  =  T2.name WHERE T2.friend  =  'Zach' AND T1.gender  =  'female'

text_query: How many premises are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM premises

text_query: Find the most popular room in the hotel. The most popular room is the room that had seen the largest number of reservations.
sql_command: SELECT T2.roomName FROM Reservations AS T1 JOIN Rooms AS T2 ON T1.Room  =  T2.RoomId GROUP BY T1.Room ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1;

text_query: What are the region names affected by the storm with a number of deaths of least 10?
sql_command: SELECT T2.region_name FROM affected_region AS T1 JOIN region AS T2 ON T1.region_id  =  T2.region_id JOIN storm AS T3 ON T1.storm_id  =  T3.storm_id WHERE T3.number_deaths  >=  10

text_query: What are the names of nations speak both English and French?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "English" INTERSECT SELECT T1.Name FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "French"

text_query: Find the number of patients who are not using the medication of Procrastin-X.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM patient WHERE SSN NOT IN ( SELECT T1.patient FROM Prescribes AS T1 JOIN Medication AS T2 ON T1.Medication  =  T2.Code WHERE T2.name  =  'Procrastin-X' )

text_query: Which building does the instructor who teaches the most number of courses live in?
sql_command: SELECT T2.Building FROM COURSE AS T1 JOIN FACULTY AS T2 ON T1.Instructor  =  T2.FacID GROUP BY T1.Instructor ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Which countries has the most number of airlines?
sql_command: SELECT country FROM airlines GROUP BY country ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the forename and surname of the driver who has the smallest laptime?
sql_command: SELECT T1.forename ,  T1.surname FROM drivers AS T1 JOIN laptimes AS T2 ON T1.driverid = T2.driverid ORDER BY T2.milliseconds LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the last and first name of students who are playing Football or Lacrosse.
sql_command: SELECT T2.lname ,  T2.fname FROM SportsInfo AS T1 JOIN Student AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  T2.StuID WHERE T1.SportName  =  "Football" OR T1.SportName  =  "Lacrosse"

text_query: How many clubs have total medals less than 10?
