sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM club_rank WHERE Total  <  10

text_query: Find the names of the customers who have order status both "On Road" and "Shipped".
sql_command: SELECT T1.customer_name FROM customers AS T1 JOIN orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id WHERE T2.order_status = "On Road" INTERSECT SELECT T1.customer_name FROM customers AS T1 JOIN orders AS T2 ON T1.customer_id = T2.customer_id WHERE T2.order_status = "Shipped"

text_query: How many students does KAWA GORDON teaches?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM list AS T1 JOIN teachers AS T2 ON T1.classroom  =  T2.classroom WHERE T2.firstname  =  "KAWA" AND T2.lastname  =  "GORDON"

text_query: Find the first names of all professors in the Accounting department who is teaching some course and the class room.
sql_command: SELECT T2.emp_fname ,  T1.class_room FROM CLASS AS T1 JOIN employee AS T2 ON T1.prof_num  =  T2.emp_num JOIN professor AS T3 ON T2.emp_num  =  T3.emp_num JOIN department AS T4 ON T4.dept_code  =  T3.dept_code WHERE T4.dept_name  =  'Accounting'

text_query: What is the song in the volume with the maximum weeks on top?
sql_command: SELECT Song FROM volume ORDER BY Weeks_on_Top DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many stores are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM store

text_query: Show the average price of hotels for each star rating code.
sql_command: SELECT star_rating_code ,  avg(price_range) FROM HOTELS GROUP BY star_rating_code

text_query: What are all the distinct participant ids who attended any events?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT participant_id) FROM participants_in_Events

text_query: What are the ids of the two department store chains with the largest number of department stores?
sql_command: SELECT dept_store_chain_id FROM department_stores GROUP BY dept_store_chain_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 2

text_query: How many rooms are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Rooms;

text_query: Find the total number of tours for each ranking date.
sql_command: SELECT sum(tours) ,  ranking_date FROM rankings GROUP BY ranking_date

text_query: Find all members of "Bootup Baltimore" whose major is "600". Show the first name and last name.
sql_command: SELECT t3.fname ,  t3.lname FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid JOIN student AS t3 ON t2.stuid  =  t3.stuid WHERE t1.clubname  =  "Bootup Baltimore" AND t3.major  =  "600"

text_query: What are the distinct types of the companies that have operated any flights with velocity less than 200?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.type FROM operate_company AS T1 JOIN flight AS t2 ON T1.id  =  T2.company_id WHERE T2.velocity  <  200

text_query: Show the product type codes that have at least two products.
sql_command: SELECT Product_Type_Code FROM Products GROUP BY Product_Type_Code HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  2

text_query: What are the id and details of the customers who have at least 3 events?
sql_command: SELECT T1.customer_id ,  T1.customer_details FROM Customers AS T1 JOIN Customer_Events AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id GROUP BY T1.customer_id HAVING count(*)  >=  3

text_query: Find the average weight for each pet type.
sql_command: SELECT avg(weight) ,  pettype FROM pets GROUP BY pettype

text_query: What are the names of mountains in ascending alphabetical order?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM mountain ORDER BY Name ASC

text_query: Find the first names of the faculty members who are playing Canoeing or Kayaking.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.lname FROM Faculty AS T1 JOIN Faculty_participates_in AS T2 ON T1.facID  =  T2.facID JOIN activity AS T3 ON T2.actid  =  T2.actid WHERE T3.activity_name  =  'Canoeing' OR T3.activity_name  =  'Kayaking'

text_query: What are the titles of all movies that have rating star is between 3 and 5?
sql_command: SELECT T2.title FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID WHERE T1.stars BETWEEN 3 AND 5

text_query: Find the day in which the difference between the max temperature and min temperature was the smallest. Also report the difference.
sql_command: SELECT date ,  max_temperature_f - min_temperature_f FROM weather ORDER BY max_temperature_f - min_temperature_f LIMIT 1

text_query: List the date the claim was made, the date it was settled and the amount settled for all the claims which had exactly one settlement.
sql_command: SELECT T1.claim_id ,  T1.date_claim_made ,  T1.Date_Claim_Settled FROM Claims AS T1 JOIN Settlements AS T2 ON T1.Claim_id  =  T2.Claim_id GROUP BY T1.claim_id HAVING count(*)  =  1

text_query: Which city does staff with first name as Janessa and last name as Sawayn live?
sql_command: SELECT T1.city FROM Addresses AS T1 JOIN Staff AS T2 ON T1.address_id = T2.staff_address_id WHERE T2.first_name = "Janessa" AND T2.last_name = "Sawayn";

text_query: What are the maximum, minimum, and average booked count for the products booked?
sql_command: SELECT max(booked_count) ,  min(booked_count) ,  avg(booked_count) FROM products_booked

text_query: What are airlines that have flights arriving at airport 'AHD'?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Airline FROM AIRLINES AS T1 JOIN FLIGHTS AS T2 ON T1.uid  =  T2.Airline WHERE T2.DestAirport  =  "AHD"

text_query: Show the flight number of flights with three lowest distances.
sql_command: SELECT flno FROM Flight ORDER BY distance ASC LIMIT 3

text_query: Give me the start station and end station for the trips with the three oldest id.
sql_command: SELECT start_station_name ,  end_station_name FROM trip ORDER BY id LIMIT 3

text_query: How many different templates do all document use?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT template_id) FROM Documents

text_query: Show storm name with at least two regions and 10 cities affected.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM storm AS T1 JOIN affected_region AS T2 ON T1.storm_id  =  T2.storm_id GROUP BY T1.storm_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2 INTERSECT SELECT T1.name FROM storm AS T1 JOIN affected_region AS T2 ON T1.storm_id  =  T2.storm_id GROUP BY T1.storm_id HAVING sum(T2.number_city_affected)  >=  10

text_query: display the employee number, name( first name and last name ), and salary for all employees who earn more than the average salary and who work in a department with any employee with a 'J' in their first name.
sql_command: SELECT employee_id ,  first_name ,  last_name ,  salary FROM employees WHERE salary  >  ( SELECT AVG (salary) FROM employees ) AND department_id IN ( SELECT department_id FROM employees WHERE first_name LIKE '%J%')

text_query: Find the name and capacity of the dorm with least number of amenities.
sql_command: SELECT T1.dorm_name ,  T1.student_capacity FROM dorm AS T1 JOIN has_amenity AS T2 ON T1.dormid  =  T2.dormid JOIN dorm_amenity AS T3 ON T2.amenid  =  T3.amenid GROUP BY T2.dormid ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

text_query: Which is the email of the party that has used the services the most number of times?
sql_command: SELECT t1.party_email FROM parties AS t1 JOIN party_services AS t2 ON t1.party_id  =  t2.customer_id GROUP BY t1.party_email ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the names of channels that are not owned by CCTV.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM channel WHERE OWNER != 'CCTV'

text_query: Which enzyme names have the substring "ALA"?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM enzyme WHERE name LIKE "%ALA%"

text_query: What is average enrollment of colleges in the state FL?
sql_command: SELECT avg(enr) FROM College WHERE state  =  'FL'

text_query: Show the title and publication dates of books.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Title ,  T2.Publication_Date FROM book AS T1 JOIN publication AS T2 ON T1.Book_ID  =  T2.Book_ID

text_query: Find the name of captains whose rank are either Midshipman or Lieutenant.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM captain WHERE rank  =  'Midshipman' OR rank  =  'Lieutenant'

text_query: Find the names of the artists who are from Bangladesh and have never received rating higher than 7.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT artist_name FROM artist WHERE country  =  "Bangladesh" EXCEPT SELECT DISTINCT artist_name FROM song WHERE rating  >  7

text_query: What is the description of document type 'Paper'?
sql_command: SELECT document_type_description FROM Ref_Document_Types WHERE document_type_code = "Paper";

text_query: List the type of the services in alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT service_type_code FROM services ORDER BY service_type_code

text_query: Find the first names and degree of all professors who are teaching some class in Computer Info. Systems department.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T2.emp_fname ,  T3.prof_high_degree FROM CLASS AS T1 JOIN employee AS T2 ON T1.prof_num  =  T2.emp_num JOIN professor AS T3 ON T2.emp_num  =  T3.emp_num JOIN department AS T4 ON T4.dept_code  =  T3.dept_code WHERE T4.dept_name  =  'Computer Info. Systems'

text_query: Find all airlines that have flights from both airports 'APG' and 'CVO'.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Airline FROM AIRLINES AS T1 JOIN FLIGHTS AS T2 ON T1.uid  =  T2.Airline WHERE T2.SourceAirport  =  "APG" INTERSECT SELECT T1.Airline FROM AIRLINES AS T1 JOIN FLIGHTS AS T2 ON T1.uid  =  T2.Airline WHERE T2.SourceAirport  =  "CVO"

text_query: Find the name, city, and country of the airport that has the highest latitude.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  city ,  country FROM airports ORDER BY elevation DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: display the department id and the total salary for those departments which contains at least two employees.
sql_command: SELECT department_id ,  SUM(salary) FROM employees GROUP BY department_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

text_query: Please show the employee first names and ids of employees who serve at least 10 customers.
sql_command: SELECT T1.FirstName ,  T1.SupportRepId FROM CUSTOMER AS T1 JOIN EMPLOYEE AS T2 ON T1.SupportRepId  =  T2.EmployeeId GROUP BY T1.SupportRepId HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  10

text_query: Show the names of journalists and the dates of the events they reported.
sql_command: SELECT T3.Name ,  T2.Date FROM news_report AS T1 JOIN event AS T2 ON T1.Event_ID  =  T2.Event_ID JOIN journalist AS T3 ON T1.journalist_ID  =  T3.journalist_ID

text_query: Show all distinct region names ordered by their labels.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT region_name FROM region ORDER BY Label

text_query: What is the name and open year for the branch with most number of memberships registered in 2016?
sql_command: SELECT T2.name ,  T2.open_year FROM membership_register_branch AS T1 JOIN branch AS T2 ON T1.branch_id  =  T2.branch_id WHERE T1.register_year  =  2016 GROUP BY T2.branch_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: find the pixel aspect ratio and nation of the tv channels that do not use English.
sql_command: SELECT Pixel_aspect_ratio_PAR ,  country FROM tv_channel WHERE LANGUAGE != 'English'

text_query: List document IDs, document names, and document descriptions for all documents.
sql_command: SELECT document_id ,  document_name ,  document_description FROM Documents

text_query: Show the rank, first name, and last name for all the faculty.
sql_command: SELECT rank ,  Fname ,  Lname FROM Faculty

text_query: What are flight numbers of flights arriving at City "Aberdeen"?
sql_command: SELECT T1.FlightNo FROM FLIGHTS AS T1 JOIN AIRPORTS AS T2 ON T1.DestAirport   =  T2.AirportCode WHERE T2.City  =  "Aberdeen"

text_query: What are the lot details of lots associated with transactions with share count smaller than 50?
sql_command: SELECT T1.lot_details FROM LOTS AS T1 JOIN TRANSACTIONS_LOTS AS T2 ON T1.lot_id  =  T2.transaction_id JOIN TRANSACTIONS AS T3 ON T2.transaction_id  =  T3.transaction_id WHERE T3.share_count  <  50

text_query: Find the first name and age of students who have a pet.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.fname ,  T1.age FROM student AS T1 JOIN has_pet AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid

text_query: How many bank branches are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM bank

text_query: Show the studios that have produced films with director "Nicholas Meyer" and "Walter Hill".
sql_command: SELECT Studio FROM film WHERE Director  =  "Nicholas Meyer" INTERSECT SELECT Studio FROM film WHERE Director  =  "Walter Hill"

text_query: Which events have the number of notes between one and three? List the event id and the property id.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Customer_Event_ID  ,  T1.property_id FROM Customer_Events AS T1 JOIN Customer_Event_Notes AS T2 ON T1.Customer_Event_ID  =  T2.Customer_Event_ID GROUP BY T1.customer_event_id HAVING count(*) BETWEEN 1 AND 3

text_query: Show the order ids and the number of items in each order.
sql_command: SELECT order_id ,  count(*) FROM Order_items GROUP BY order_id

text_query: What are the nationalities and ages of journalists?
sql_command: SELECT Nationality ,  Age FROM journalist

text_query: Show the hometowns shared by people older than 23 and younger than 20.
sql_command: SELECT Hometown FROM people WHERE Age  >  23 INTERSECT SELECT Hometown FROM people WHERE Age  <  20

text_query: How many accounts are there in total?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM accounts

text_query: Find the number of records of each policy type and its type code.
sql_command: SELECT policy_type_code ,  count(*) FROM policies GROUP BY policy_type_code

text_query: What is the id and last name of the driver who participated in the most races after 2010?
sql_command: SELECT T1.driverid ,  T1.surname FROM drivers AS T1 JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.driverid  =  T2.driverid JOIN races AS T3 ON T2.raceid = T3.raceid WHERE T3.year > 2010 GROUP BY T1.driverid ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is id of the staff who had a Staff Department Assignment earlier than any Clerical Staff?
sql_command: SELECT staff_id FROM Staff_Department_Assignments WHERE date_assigned_to  <  (SELECT max(date_assigned_to) FROM Staff_Department_Assignments WHERE job_title_code  =  'Clerical Staff')

text_query: List the grapes and appelations of all wines.
sql_command: SELECT Grape ,  Appelation FROM WINE

text_query: Find the student first and last names and grade points of all enrollments.
sql_command: SELECT T3.Fname ,  T3.LName ,  T2.gradepoint FROM ENROLLED_IN AS T1 JOIN GRADECONVERSION AS T2 JOIN STUDENT AS T3 ON T1.Grade  =  T2.lettergrade AND T1.StuID  =  T3.StuID

text_query: Please show the most common age of editors.
sql_command: SELECT Age FROM editor GROUP BY Age ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the official language spoken in the country whose head of state is Beatrix?
sql_command: SELECT T2.Language FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T1.HeadOfState  =  "Beatrix" AND T2.IsOfficial  =  "T"

text_query: Find the name of amenities of the dorm where the student with last name Smith is living in.
sql_command: SELECT T3.amenity_name FROM dorm AS T1 JOIN has_amenity AS T2 ON T1.dormid  =  T2.dormid JOIN dorm_amenity AS T3 ON T2.amenid  =  T3.amenid JOIN lives_in AS T4 ON T4.dormid  =  T1.dormid JOIN student AS T5 ON T5.stuid  =  T4.stuid WHERE T5.lname  =  'Smith'

text_query: Find the country of origin for the artist who made the least number of songs?
sql_command: SELECT T1.country FROM artist AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.artist_name  =  T2.artist_name GROUP BY T2.artist_name ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the status of the city that has hosted the greatest number of competitions.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Status FROM city AS T1 JOIN farm_competition AS T2 ON T1.City_ID  =  T2.Host_city_ID GROUP BY T2.Host_city_ID ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many customers have email that contains "gmail.com"?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM CUSTOMER WHERE Email LIKE "%gmail.com%"

text_query: What are the ids, names and FDA approval status of medicines in descending order of the number of enzymes that it can interact with.
sql_command: SELECT T1.id ,  T1.Name ,  T1.FDA_approved FROM medicine AS T1 JOIN medicine_enzyme_interaction AS T2 ON T2.medicine_id  =  T1.id GROUP BY T1.id ORDER BY count(*) DESC

text_query: What is the average attendance of stadiums with capacity percentage higher than 100%?
sql_command: SELECT average_attendance FROM stadium WHERE capacity_percentage  >  100

text_query: Find distinct cities of address of students?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.city FROM addresses AS T1 JOIN people_addresses AS T2 ON T1.address_id = T2.address_id JOIN students AS T3 ON T2.person_id = T3.student_id

text_query: List the total scores of body builders in ascending order.
sql_command: SELECT Total FROM body_builder ORDER BY Total ASC

text_query: A list of the top 8 countries by gross/total invoice size. List country name and gross invoice size.
sql_command: SELECT billing_country ,  SUM(total) FROM invoices GROUP BY billing_country ORDER BY SUM(total) DESC LIMIT 8;

text_query: Find the name of the most expensive hardware product.
sql_command: SELECT product_name FROM products WHERE product_type_code  =  'Hardware' ORDER BY product_price DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many different winners both participated in the WTA Championships and were left handed?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT winner_name) FROM matches WHERE tourney_name  =  'WTA Championships' AND winner_hand  =  'L'

text_query: What is draft detail of the document with id 7?
sql_command: SELECT draft_details FROM Document_Drafts WHERE document_id = 7;

text_query: Find the number of trains starting from each origin.
sql_command: SELECT origin ,  count(*) FROM train GROUP BY origin

text_query: What is the name of the highest mountain?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM mountain ORDER BY Height DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Can you return all detailed info of jobs which was done by any of the employees who is presently earning a salary on and above 12000?
sql_command: SELECT * FROM  job_history AS T1 JOIN employees AS T2 ON T1.employee_id  =  T2.employee_id WHERE T2.salary  >=  12000

text_query: List all employees in the circulation history of the document with id 1. List the employee's name.
sql_command: SELECT Employees.employee_name FROM Employees JOIN Circulation_History ON Circulation_History.employee_id = Employees.employee_id WHERE Circulation_History.document_id = 1;

text_query: How many colleges has more than 15000 students?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM College WHERE enr  >  15000

text_query: Find the name, checking balance and saving balance of all accounts in the bank.
sql_command: SELECT T2.balance ,  T3.balance ,  T1.name FROM accounts AS T1 JOIN checking AS T2 ON T1.custid  =  T2.custid JOIN savings AS T3 ON T1.custid  =  T3.custid

text_query: How many orders does Lucas Mancini has?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM customers AS T1 JOIN invoices AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.customer_id WHERE T1.first_name = "Lucas" AND T1.last_name = "Mancini";

text_query: List the document type code, document name, and document description for the document with name 'Noel CV' or name 'King Book'.
sql_command: SELECT document_type_code ,  document_name ,  document_description FROM Documents WHERE document_name  =  'Noel CV' OR document_name  =  'King Book'

text_query: What is detail of the student who registered the most number of courses?
sql_command: SELECT T1.student_details FROM students AS T1 JOIN student_course_registrations AS T2 ON T1.student_id = T2.student_id GROUP BY T1.student_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the names of the students who are in the position of striker and got a yes tryout decision.
sql_command: SELECT T1.pName FROM player AS T1 JOIN tryout AS T2 ON T1.pID  =  T2.pID WHERE T2.decision  =  'yes' AND T2.pPos  =  'striker'

text_query: List all the distinct stations from which a trip of duration below 100 started.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT start_station_name FROM trip WHERE duration  <  100

text_query: What are the maximum and minimum number of cities in all markets.
sql_command: SELECT max(Number_cities) ,  min(Number_cities) FROM market

text_query: List the names of wrestlers and the teams in elimination in descending order of days held.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name ,  T1.Team FROM elimination AS T1 JOIN wrestler AS T2 ON T1.Wrestler_ID  =  T2.Wrestler_ID ORDER BY T2.Days_held DESC

text_query: What is the name of the patient who made the most recent appointment?
sql_command: SELECT T1.name FROM patient AS T1 JOIN appointment AS T2 ON T1.ssn = T2.patient ORDER BY T2.start DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Which claim incurred the most number of settlements? List the claim id, the date the claim was made, and the number.
sql_command: SELECT T1.claim_id ,  T1.date_claim_made ,  count(*) FROM Claims AS T1 JOIN Settlements AS T2 ON T1.claim_id  =  T2.claim_id GROUP BY T1.claim_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the average, minimum, and maximum capacity for all the cinemas opened in year 2011 or later.
sql_command: SELECT avg(capacity) ,  min(capacity) ,  max(capacity) FROM cinema WHERE openning_year  >=  2011

text_query: What is the name and capacity of the stadium with the most concerts after 2013 ?
sql_command: select t2.name ,  t2.capacity from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id  =  t2.stadium_id where t1.year  >  2013 group by t2.stadium_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

text_query: What are the unique block codes that have available rooms?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT blockcode FROM room WHERE unavailable  =  0

text_query: Find products with max page size as "A4" or pages per minute color smaller than 5.
sql_command: SELECT product FROM product WHERE max_page_size  =  "A4" OR pages_per_minute_color  <  5

text_query: What is the color description of the product with name "catnip"?
sql_command: SELECT t2.color_description FROM products AS t1 JOIN ref_colors AS t2 ON t1.color_code  =  t2.color_code WHERE t1.product_name  =  "catnip"

text_query: What are the id and first name of the student whose addresses have the highest average monthly rental?

sql_command: SELECT T2.name ,  T1.category_id ,  count(*) FROM film_category AS T1 JOIN category AS T2 ON T1.category_id  =  T2.category_id GROUP BY T1.category_id

sql_command: SELECT donator_name ,  sum(amount) FROM endowment GROUP BY donator_name ORDER BY sum(amount) DESC

sql_command: SELECT T1.state_province_county FROM Addresses AS T1 JOIN Staff AS T2 ON T1.address_id = T2.staff_address_id GROUP BY T1.state_province_county HAVING count(*) BETWEEN 2 AND 4;

text_query: List the distinct director of all films.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT Director FROM film

text_query: What are names of patients who made an appointment?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM appointment AS T1 JOIN patient AS T2 ON T1.patient  =  T2.ssn

text_query: Find the number of students that have at least one grade "B".
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT StuID) FROM ENROLLED_IN WHERE Grade  =  "B"

text_query: What is the maximum capacity and the average of all stadiums ?
sql_command: select max(capacity), average from stadium

text_query: Find the name of the tryout players who are from the college with largest size.
sql_command: SELECT T2.pName FROM  tryout AS T1 JOIN player AS T2 ON T1.pID  =  T2.pID WHERE T1.cName  =  (SELECT cName FROM college ORDER BY enr DESC LIMIT 1)

text_query: How many faculty lines are there in the university that conferred the most number of degrees in year 2002?
sql_command: SELECT T2.faculty FROM campuses AS T1 JOIN faculty AS T2 ON T1.id  =  t2.campus JOIN degrees AS T3 ON T1.id  =  t3.campus AND t2.year  =  t3.year WHERE t2.year  =  2002 ORDER BY t3.degrees DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Show the different countries and the number of members from each.
sql_command: SELECT Country ,  COUNT(*) FROM member GROUP BY Country

text_query: How many apartment bookings are there in total?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Apartment_Bookings

text_query: Show the season, the player, and the name of the team that players belong to.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Season ,  T1.Player ,  T2.Name FROM match_season AS T1 JOIN team AS T2 ON T1.Team  =  T2.Team_id

text_query: For each director, return the director's name together with the title of the movie they directed that received the highest rating among all of their movies, and the value of that rating. Ignore movies whose director is NULL.
sql_command: SELECT T2.title ,  T1.stars ,  T2.director ,  max(T1.stars) FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID WHERE director != "null" GROUP BY director

text_query: Give me a list of distinct product ids from orders placed between 1975-01-01 and 1976-01-01?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T2.product_id FROM orders AS T1 JOIN order_items AS T2 ON T1.order_id = T2.order_id WHERE T1.date_order_placed >= "1975-01-01" AND T1.date_order_placed <= "1976-01-01"

text_query: What are the regions that use English or Dutch?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Region FROM country AS T1 JOIN countrylanguage AS T2 ON T1.Code  =  T2.CountryCode WHERE T2.Language  =  "English" OR T2.Language  =  "Dutch"

text_query: For each advisor, report the total number of students advised by him or her.
sql_command: SELECT Advisor ,  count(*) FROM STUDENT GROUP BY Advisor

text_query: What is last date created of votes from the state 'CA'?
sql_command: SELECT max(created) FROM votes WHERE state  =  'CA'

text_query: What are all info of students who registered courses but not attended courses?
sql_command: SELECT * FROM student_course_registrations WHERE student_id NOT IN (SELECT student_id FROM student_course_attendance)

text_query: Find the first names of all instructors who have taught some course and the course code.
sql_command: SELECT T2.emp_fname ,  T1.crs_code FROM CLASS AS T1 JOIN employee AS T2 ON T1.prof_num  =  T2.emp_num

text_query: What is the party of the representative that has the smallest number of votes.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Party FROM election AS T1 JOIN representative AS T2 ON T1.Representative_ID  =  T2.Representative_ID ORDER BY votes ASC LIMIT 1

text_query: How many trips did not end in San Francisco?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM trip AS T1 JOIN station AS T2 ON T1.end_station_id  =  T2.id WHERE T2.city != "San Francisco"

text_query: What are the names of representatives whose party is not "Republican"?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM Representative WHERE Party != "Republican"

text_query: Show all locations with only 1 station.
sql_command: SELECT LOCATION FROM station GROUP BY LOCATION HAVING count(*)  =  1

text_query: Give me the times and numbers of all trains that go to Chennai, ordered by time.
sql_command: SELECT TIME ,  train_number FROM train WHERE destination  =  'Chennai' ORDER BY TIME

text_query: Find the number of students in each major.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  major FROM student GROUP BY major

text_query: Show the average age for male and female students.
sql_command: SELECT avg(age) ,  sex FROM Student GROUP BY sex

text_query: Find the titles of papers whose first author is affiliated with an institution in the country "Japan" and has last name "Ohori"?
sql_command: SELECT t3.title FROM authors AS t1 JOIN authorship AS t2 ON t1.authid  =  t2.authid JOIN papers AS t3 ON t2.paperid  =  t3.paperid JOIN inst AS t4 ON t2.instid  =  t4.instid WHERE t4.country  =  "Japan" AND t2.authorder  =  1 AND t1.lname  =  "Ohori"

text_query: How many lessons taken by customer with first name as Rylan and last name as Goodwin were completed?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Lessons AS T1 JOIN Customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  = T2.customer_id WHERE T2.first_name = "Rylan" AND T2.last_name = "Goodwin" AND T1.lesson_status_code = "Completed";

text_query: What are the names and ages of editors?
sql_command: SELECT Name ,  Age FROM editor

text_query: How many transaction does each account have? Show the number and account id.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  account_id FROM Financial_transactions

text_query: Find the name of all the cities and states.
sql_command: SELECT town_city FROM addresses UNION SELECT state_province_county FROM addresses

text_query: How many students enrolled in class ACCT-211?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM CLASS AS T1 JOIN enroll AS T2 ON T1.class_code  =  T2.class_code WHERE T1.crs_code  =  'ACCT-211'

text_query: What are the country codes of countries where people use languages other than English?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT CountryCode FROM countrylanguage WHERE LANGUAGE != "English"

text_query: What is the average points of players from club with name "AIB".
sql_command: SELECT avg(T2.Points) FROM club AS T1 JOIN player AS T2 ON T1.Club_ID  =  T2.Club_ID WHERE T1.name  =  "AIB"

text_query: Show the name of singers whose birth year is either 1948 or 1949?
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM singer WHERE Birth_Year  =  1948 OR Birth_Year  =  1949

text_query: Find names of colleges with enrollment greater than that of some (at least one) college in the FL state.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT cName FROM college WHERE enr  >  (SELECT min(enr) FROM college WHERE state  =  'FL')

text_query: Find the numbers of different majors and cities.
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT major) ,  count(DISTINCT city_code) FROM student

text_query: Find the country of all appelations who have at most three wines.
sql_command: SELECT T1.County FROM APPELLATIONS AS T1 JOIN WINE AS T2 ON T1.Appelation  =  T2.Appelation GROUP BY T2.Appelation HAVING count(*)  <=  3

text_query: Show the most common location of performances.
sql_command: SELECT LOCATION FROM performance GROUP BY LOCATION ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the total salary paid by team Boston Red Stockings in 2010?
sql_command: SELECT sum(T1.salary) FROM salary AS T1 JOIN team AS T2 ON T1.team_id  =  T2.team_id_br WHERE T2.name  = 'Boston Red Stockings' AND T1.year  =  2010

text_query: What is the code of the school where the accounting department belongs to?
sql_command: SELECT school_code FROM department WHERE dept_name  =  "Accounting"

text_query: What is detail of the student who most recently registered course?
sql_command: SELECT T2.student_details FROM student_course_registrations AS T1 JOIN students AS T2 ON T1.student_id = T2.student_id ORDER BY T1.registration_date DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Which cities have 2 to 4 parks?
sql_command: SELECT city FROM park GROUP BY city HAVING count(*) BETWEEN 2 AND 4;

text_query: How many aircrafts do we have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM Aircraft

text_query: What are the titles and directors of the movies whose star is greater than the average stars of the movies directed by James Cameron?
sql_command: SELECT T2.title ,  T2.director FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID WHERE T1.stars  >  (SELECT avg(T1.stars) FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID WHERE T2.director  =  "James Cameron")

text_query: What is the number of artists for each gender?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  gender FROM artist GROUP BY gender

text_query: Find the name of the document that has been accessed the greatest number of times, as well as the count of how many times it has been accessed?
sql_command: SELECT document_name ,  access_count FROM documents ORDER BY access_count DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the id of the trip that has the shortest duration?
sql_command: SELECT id FROM trip ORDER BY duration LIMIT 1

text_query: List all payment methods and number of payments using each payment methods.
sql_command: SELECT payment_method_code ,  count(*) FROM Customer_Payments GROUP BY payment_method_code;

text_query: Which fault log included the most number of faulty parts? List the fault log id, description and record time.
sql_command: SELECT T1.fault_log_entry_id ,  T1.fault_description ,  T1.fault_log_entry_datetime FROM Fault_Log AS T1 JOIN Fault_Log_Parts AS T2 ON T1.fault_log_entry_id  =  T2.fault_log_entry_id GROUP BY T1.fault_log_entry_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: what is the GDP of the city with the largest population.
sql_command: SELECT gdp FROM city ORDER BY Regional_Population DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find all types of store and number of them.
sql_command: SELECT TYPE ,  count(*) FROM store GROUP BY TYPE

text_query: Show all company names with a movie directed in year 1999.
sql_command: SELECT T2.company_name FROM movie AS T1 JOIN culture_company AS T2 ON T1.movie_id  =  T2.movie_id WHERE T1.year  =  1999

text_query: What is the average time span of contact channels in the database?
sql_command: SELECT avg(active_to_date - active_from_date) FROM customer_contact_channels

text_query: Find the personal name, family name, and author ID of the course author that teaches the most courses.
sql_command: SELECT T1.personal_name ,  T1.family_name ,  T2.author_id FROM Course_Authors_and_Tutors AS T1 JOIN Courses AS T2 ON T1.author_id  =  T2.author_id GROUP BY T2.author_id ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: List the name of actors in ascending alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT Name FROM actor ORDER BY Name ASC

text_query: What are the order dates of orders with price higher than 1000?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Order_Date FROM Customer_Orders AS T1 JOIN ORDER_ITEMS AS T2 ON T1.Order_ID  =  T2.Order_ID JOIN Products AS T3 ON T2.Product_ID  =  T3.Product_ID WHERE T3.Product_price  >  1000

text_query: List the names and buildings of all departments sorted by the budget from large to small.
sql_command: SELECT dept_name ,  building FROM department ORDER BY budget DESC

text_query: What are the name, height and prominence of mountains which do not belong to the range 'Aberdare Range'?
sql_command: SELECT name ,  height ,  prominence FROM mountain WHERE range != 'Aberdare Range'

text_query: What is ids of the songs whose resolution is higher than the average resolution of songs in modern genre?
sql_command: SELECT f_id FROM song WHERE resolution  >  (SELECT avg(resolution) FROM song WHERE genre_is  =  "modern")

text_query: how many airports are there in each country?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) ,  country FROM airport GROUP BY country

text_query: Find the name of the stadium that has the maximum capacity.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM stadium ORDER BY capacity DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the date of the performance with the highest number of attendees?
sql_command: SELECT Date FROM performance ORDER BY Attendance DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the founded year of the newest non public school.
sql_command: SELECT founded FROM university WHERE affiliation != 'Public' ORDER BY founded DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What is the average age of all gymnasts?
sql_command: SELECT avg(T2.Age) FROM gymnast AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.Gymnast_ID  =  T2.People_ID

text_query: What is the id and detail of the vehicle used in lessons for most of the times?
sql_command: SELECT T1.vehicle_id ,  T1.vehicle_details FROM Vehicles AS T1 JOIN Lessons AS T2 ON T1.vehicle_id  =  T2.vehicle_id GROUP BY T1.vehicle_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Find the name of companies that do not make DVD drive.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM manufacturers EXCEPT SELECT T2.name FROM products AS T1 JOIN manufacturers AS T2 ON T1.Manufacturer  =  T2.code WHERE T1.name  =  'DVD drive'

text_query: Which flag is most widely used among all ships?
sql_command: SELECT flag FROM ship GROUP BY flag ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: Return the text of tweets about the topic 'intern'.
sql_command: SELECT text FROM tweets WHERE text LIKE '%intern%'

text_query: Show the name of aircraft which fewest people have its certificate.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM Certificate AS T1 JOIN Aircraft AS T2 ON T2.aid  =  T1.aid GROUP BY T1.aid ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the names of races held between 2009 and 2011?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM races WHERE YEAR BETWEEN 2009 AND 2011

text_query: List all manufacturer names and ids ordered by their opening year.
sql_command: SELECT name ,  manufacturer_id FROM manufacturer ORDER BY open_year

text_query: What are the average score and average staff number of all shops?
sql_command: SELECT avg(num_of_staff) ,  avg(score) FROM shop

text_query: What are the first and last name of the president of the club "Bootup Baltimore"?
sql_command: SELECT t3.fname ,  t3.lname FROM club AS t1 JOIN member_of_club AS t2 ON t1.clubid  =  t2.clubid JOIN student AS t3 ON t2.stuid  =  t3.stuid WHERE t1.clubname  =  "Bootup Baltimore" AND t2.position  =  "President"

text_query: How many different software platforms are there for devices?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT Software_Platform) FROM device

text_query: Show names of technicians and the number of machines they are assigned to repair.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name ,  COUNT(*) FROM repair_assignment AS T1 JOIN technician AS T2 ON T1.technician_ID  =  T2.technician_ID GROUP BY T2.Name

text_query: Find the total population of the districts where the area is bigger than the average city area.
sql_command: SELECT sum(city_population) FROM district WHERE city_area  >  (SELECT avg(city_area) FROM district)

text_query: Find all the players' first name and last name who have empty death record.
sql_command: SELECT name_first ,  name_last FROM player WHERE death_year = '';

text_query: List the forenames of all distinct drivers in alphabetical order?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT forename FROM drivers ORDER BY forename ASC

text_query: Find the name and training hours of players whose hours are below 1500.
sql_command: SELECT pName ,  HS FROM Player WHERE HS  <  1500

text_query: Show the names of aircrafts that are associated with both an airport named "London Heathrow" and an airport named "London Gatwick"
sql_command: SELECT T1.Aircraft FROM aircraft AS T1 JOIN airport_aircraft AS T2 ON T1.Aircraft_ID  =  T2.Aircraft_ID JOIN airport AS T3 ON T2.Airport_ID  =  T3.Airport_ID WHERE T3.Airport_Name  =  "London Heathrow" INTERSECT SELECT T1.Aircraft FROM aircraft AS T1 JOIN airport_aircraft AS T2 ON T1.Aircraft_ID  =  T2.Aircraft_ID JOIN airport AS T3 ON T2.Airport_ID  =  T3.Airport_ID WHERE T3.Airport_Name  =  "London Gatwick"

text_query: Show the names of members and the location of the performances they attended.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name ,  T3.Location FROM member_attendance AS T1 JOIN member AS T2 ON T1.Member_ID  =  T2.Member_ID JOIN performance AS T3 ON T1.Performance_ID  =  T3.Performance_ID

text_query: Which of the mill names contains the french word 'Moulin'?
sql_command: SELECT name FROM mill WHERE name LIKE '%Moulin%'

text_query: List the age of all music artists.
sql_command: SELECT Age FROM artist

text_query: Find the players' first name and last name who won award both in 1960 and in 1961.
sql_command: SELECT T1.name_first , T1.name_last FROM player AS T1 JOIN player_award AS T2 WHERE T2.year  =  1960 INTERSECT SELECT T1.name_first , T1.name_last FROM player AS T1 JOIN player_award AS T2 WHERE T2.year  =  1961

text_query: Find the locations where have both tracks with more than 90000 seats and tracks with less than 70000 seats.
sql_command: SELECT LOCATION FROM track WHERE seating  >  90000 INTERSECT SELECT LOCATION FROM track WHERE seating  <  70000

text_query: Find the names and number of works of all artists who have at least one English songs.
sql_command: SELECT T1.artist_name ,  count(*) FROM artist AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.artist_name  =  T2.artist_name WHERE T2.languages  =  "english" GROUP BY T2.artist_name HAVING count(*)  >=  1

text_query: List the hardware model name for the phones that were produced by "Nokia Corporation" or whose screen mode type is "Graphics."
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T2.Hardware_Model_name FROM screen_mode AS T1 JOIN phone AS T2 ON T1.Graphics_mode = T2.screen_mode WHERE T1.Type  =  "Graphics" OR t2.Company_name  =  "Nokia Corporation"

text_query: How many devices are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM device

text_query: List singer names and number of concerts for each singer.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name ,  count(*) FROM singer_in_concert AS T1 JOIN singer AS T2 ON T1.singer_id  =  T2.singer_id GROUP BY T2.singer_id

text_query: Find the number of female students (with F sex) living in Smith Hall
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM student AS T1 JOIN lives_in AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid JOIN dorm AS T3 ON T3.dormid  =  T2.dormid WHERE T3.dorm_name  =  'Smith Hall' AND T1.sex  =  'F'

text_query: Hom many musicians performed in the song "Flash"?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM performance AS T1 JOIN band AS T2 ON T1.bandmate  =  T2.id JOIN songs AS T3 ON T3.songid  =  T1.songid WHERE T3.Title  =  "Flash"

text_query: What is the detail of the location UK Gallery?
sql_command: SELECT Other_Details FROM LOCATIONS WHERE Location_Name  =  "UK Gallery"

text_query: For each player, show the team and the location of school they belong to.
sql_command: SELECT T1.Team ,  T2.Location FROM player AS T1 JOIN school AS T2 ON T1.School_ID  =  T2.School_ID

text_query: List the contestant numbers and names, ordered by contestant name descending.
sql_command: SELECT contestant_number ,  contestant_name FROM contestants ORDER BY contestant_name DESC

text_query: What is "the date in location from" and "the date in location to" for the document with name "Robin CV"?
sql_command: SELECT T1.date_in_location_from ,  T1.date_in_locaton_to FROM Document_locations AS T1 JOIN All_documents AS T2 ON T1.document_id  =  T2.document_id WHERE T2.document_name  =  "Robin CV"

text_query: What are the line 1 and average monthly rentals of all student addresses?
sql_command: SELECT T1.line_1 ,  avg(T2.monthly_rental) FROM Addresses AS T1 JOIN Student_Addresses AS T2 ON T1.address_id  =  T2.address_id GROUP BY T2.address_id

text_query: Show the locations that have both performances with more than 2000 attendees and performances with less than 1000 attendees.
sql_command: SELECT LOCATION FROM performance WHERE Attendance  >  2000 INTERSECT SELECT LOCATION FROM performance WHERE Attendance  <  1000

text_query: List lesson id of all lessons taught by staff with first name as Janessa, last name as Sawayn and nickname containing letter 's'.
sql_command: SELECT T1.lesson_id FROM Lessons AS T1 JOIN Staff AS T2 ON T1.staff_id = T2.staff_id WHERE T2.first_name = "Janessa" AND T2.last_name = "Sawayn" AND nickname LIKE "%s%";

text_query: Compute the average price of all the products.
sql_command: SELECT avg(price) FROM products

text_query: What is the phone and email for customer with first name Aniyah and last name Feest?
sql_command: SELECT customer_phone ,  customer_email FROM Customers WHERE customer_first_name  =  "Aniyah" AND customer_last_name  =  "Feest"

text_query: Show all destinations and the number of flights to each destination.
sql_command: SELECT destination ,  count(*) FROM Flight GROUP BY destination

text_query: What are the elimination moves of wrestlers whose team is "Team Orton"?
sql_command: SELECT Elimination_Move FROM Elimination WHERE Team  =  "Team Orton"

text_query: List the distinct region of clubs in ascending alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT Region FROM club ORDER BY Region ASC

text_query: Show first name, last name, age for all female students. Their sex is F.
sql_command: SELECT Fname ,  Lname ,  Age FROM Student WHERE Sex  =  'F'

text_query: What are the distinct visit dates?
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT Visit_Date FROM VISITS

text_query: What is the name and building of the departments whose budget is more than the average budget?
sql_command: SELECT dept_name ,  building FROM department WHERE budget  >  (SELECT avg(budget) FROM department)

text_query: How many games were played in city Atlanta in 2000?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM home_game AS T1 JOIN park AS T2 ON T1.park_id  =  T2.park_id WHERE T1.year  =  2000 AND T2.city  =  'Atlanta';

text_query: Give me the names of members whose address is in Harford or Waterbury.
sql_command: SELECT name FROM member WHERE address  =  'Harford' OR address  =  'Waterbury'

text_query: What is the average number of votes of representatives from party "Republican"?
sql_command: SELECT avg(T1.Votes) FROM election AS T1 JOIN representative AS T2 ON T1.Representative_ID  =  T2.Representative_ID WHERE T2.Party  =  "Republican"

text_query: Show the name and distance of the aircrafts with more than 5000 distance and which at least 5 people have its certificate.
sql_command: SELECT T2.name FROM Certificate AS T1 JOIN Aircraft AS T2 ON T2.aid  =  T1.aid WHERE T2.distance  >  5000 GROUP BY T1.aid ORDER BY count(*)  >=  5

text_query: what are the names of the channels that broadcast in both morning and night?
sql_command: SELECT t1.name FROM channel AS t1 JOIN broadcast AS t2 ON t1.channel_id  =  t2.channel_id WHERE t2.time_of_day  =  'Morning' INTERSECT SELECT t1.name FROM channel AS t1 JOIN broadcast AS t2 ON t1.channel_id  =  t2.channel_id WHERE t2.time_of_day  =  'Night'

text_query: How many parties are there?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM party

text_query: Find the category descriptions of the products whose descriptions include letter 't'.
sql_command: SELECT T1.product_category_description FROM ref_product_categories AS T1 JOIN products AS T2 ON T1.product_category_code  =  T2.product_category_code WHERE T2.product_description LIKE '%t%'

text_query: How many parks are there in the state of NY?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM park WHERE state  =  'NY';

text_query: Show ids for all students who have advisor 1121.
sql_command: SELECT StuID FROM Student WHERE Advisor  =  1121

text_query: display the full name (first and last name ) of employee with ID and name of the country presently where (s)he is working.

text_query: How many distinct students have been in detention?
sql_command: SELECT count(DISTINCT student_id) FROM Students_in_Detention

text_query: Please list the name and id of all artists that have at least 3 albums in alphabetical order.
sql_command: SELECT T2.Name ,  T1.ArtistId FROM ALBUM AS T1 JOIN ARTIST AS T2 ON T1.ArtistId  =  T2.ArtistID GROUP BY T1.ArtistId HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  3 ORDER BY T2.Name

text_query: Find the names of customers who either have an deputy policy or uniformed policy.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT t2.customer_details FROM policies AS t1 JOIN customers AS t2 ON t1.customer_id  =  t2.customer_id WHERE t1.policy_type_code  =  "Deputy" OR t1.policy_type_code  =  "Uniform"

text_query: Find the address and staff number of the shops that do not have any happy hour.
sql_command: SELECT address ,  num_of_staff FROM shop WHERE shop_id NOT IN (SELECT shop_id FROM happy_hour)

text_query: What is the average rating stars and title for the oldest movie?
sql_command: SELECT avg(T1.stars) ,  T2.title FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID WHERE T2.year  =  (SELECT min(YEAR) FROM Movie)

text_query: Which dogs have not cost their owner more than 1000 for treatment ? List the dog names .
sql_command: select name from dogs where dog_id not in ( select dog_id from treatments group by dog_id having sum(cost_of_treatment)  >  1000 )

text_query: Show each apartment type code, and the maximum and minimum number of rooms for each type.
sql_command: SELECT apt_type_code ,  max(room_count) ,  min(room_count) FROM Apartments GROUP BY apt_type_code

text_query: Find the first name of students who have cat or dog pet.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Fname FROM student AS T1 JOIN has_pet AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid JOIN pets AS T3 ON T3.petid  =  T2.petid WHERE T3.pettype  =  'cat' OR T3.pettype  =  'dog'

text_query: Find id of candidates whose assessment code is "Pass"?
sql_command: SELECT candidate_id FROM candidate_assessments WHERE asessment_outcome_code = "Pass"

text_query: Find the ids of the departments where any manager is managing 4 or more employees.
sql_command: SELECT DISTINCT department_id FROM employees GROUP BY department_id ,  manager_id HAVING COUNT(employee_id)  >= 4

text_query: Find the number of professors in accounting department.
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM professor AS T1 JOIN department AS T2 ON T1.dept_code  =  T2.dept_code WHERE DEPT_NAME  =  "Accounting"

text_query: What is the document id, template id and description for document named "Robbin CV"?
sql_command: SELECT document_id ,  template_id ,  Document_Description FROM Documents WHERE document_name  =  "Robbin CV"

text_query: How many characteristics does the product named "sesame" have?
sql_command: SELECT count(*) FROM products AS t1 JOIN product_characteristics AS t2 ON t1.product_id  =  t2.product_id WHERE t1.product_name  =  "sesame"

sql_command: SELECT product_name FROM products AS t1 JOIN product_characteristics AS t2 ON t1.product_id  =  t2.product_id JOIN CHARACTERISTICS AS t3 ON t2.characteristic_id  =  t3.characteristic_id JOIN ref_colors AS t4 ON t1.color_code  =  t4.color_code WHERE t4.color_description  =  "red" AND t3.characteristic_name  =  "fast"

text_query: What is the average amount due for all the payments?
sql_command: SELECT avg(amount_due) FROM payments

text_query: What is the zip code in which the average mean sea level pressure is the lowest?
sql_command: SELECT zip_code FROM weather GROUP BY zip_code ORDER BY avg(mean_sea_level_pressure_inches) LIMIT 1

text_query: Please show the most common status of roller coasters.
sql_command: SELECT Status FROM roller_coaster GROUP BY Status ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

text_query: What are the countries having at least one car maker? List name and id.
sql_command: SELECT T1.CountryName ,  T1.CountryId FROM COUNTRIES AS T1 JOIN CAR_MAKERS AS T2 ON T1.CountryId  =  T2.Country GROUP BY T1.CountryId HAVING count(*)  >=  1;

text_query: What are the product id and product type of the cheapest product?

text_query: Find the number of students in total.

text_query: Please show different denominations and the corresponding number of schools.

text_query: What is the average high temperature for each day of week?

text_query: List the name of enzymes in descending lexicographical order.

text_query: Which makers designed more than 3 car models? List full name and the id.

text_query: On average, when were the transcripts printed?

text_query: List the maximum scores of the team Boston Red Stockings when the team won in postseason?

text_query: Show the citizenship shared by singers with birth year before 1945 and after 1955.

text_query: What is the average number of bedrooms of all apartments?
sql_command: SELECT avg(bedroom_count) FROM Apartments

text_query: What are the ids and makers of all car makers that produce at least 2 models and make more than 3 cars?
sql_command: SELECT T1.Id ,  T1.Maker FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker GROUP BY T1.Id HAVING count(*)  >=  2 INTERSECT SELECT T1.Id ,  T1.Maker FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T3 ON T2.model  =  T3.model GROUP BY T1.Id HAVING count(*)  >  3;

text_query: Find the name and college of students whose decisions are yes in the tryout.

text_query: How many editors are there?

sql_command: SELECT T1.Aircraft FROM aircraft AS T1 JOIN MATCH AS T2 ON T1.Aircraft_ID  =  T2.Winning_Aircraft GROUP BY T2.Winning_Aircraft HAVING COUNT(*)  >=  2
